Job Title: Associate Business Intelligence Developer (South of Milwauke...
Description:
Associate Business Intelligence Developer
Corporate Headquarters
12575 Uline Drive, Pleasant Prairie, WI 53158
Real work. Real training. Real growth. There's no limit to what you can accomplish through our unique LearnIT program, with 6 weeks of orientation to set you up for professional and technical success at Uline.

Better together than apart. This position is on-site, and we are looking for good people who share our passion.

Uline is proud to operate as a drug-free workplace. All new hires must complete a pre-employment hair follicle drug screening.

Position Responsibilities
Collaborate with Senior Business Intelligence team members to develop reports and advanced analytics using data warehousing concepts and technologies.
Partner with business leaders to develop innovative ways to deliver dashboards, reports and queries using tools such as Python and Microsoft’s BI Stack (Power BI, Power Apps, Power Automate, SSAS, SSRS).
Effectively communicate with business partners to understand business needs and translate to BI solutions.
Create and maintain documentation including requirements, designers, user manuals and data dictionaries.
Minimum Requirements
Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Information Technology or related field.
Strong critical / analytical thinking and problem-solving skills.
Excellent facilitation and organizational skills.
Proficient at writing and executing SQL statements.
Benefits
Complete insurance coverage that includes medical, dental, vision and life insurance, Flexible Spending Accounts and wellness programs.
401(k) with 5% employer match.
Paid holidays and generous paid time off.
Bonus programs that include annual performance, sales goals and profit sharing.
Scholarship program for children of employees.
Employee Perks
On-site cafe with executive chefs and seasonal dinner-to-go options.
First-class fitness center with complimentary personal trainers.
Over four miles of beautifully maintained walking trails.
Numerous employee appreciation events throughout the year.
Professional development classes and monthly in-house speakers.
About Uline

Uline is North America's leading distributor of shipping, industrial and packaging materials. We're a family-owned company known for incredible service, our 800+ page catalog of over 38,500 quality products and same-day shipping of our huge in-stock inventory. With over 8,000 employees across 12 locations, it's time you joined Uline.

Each resume submitted gets individually reviewed by our team and retained for 24 months in case a great opportunity opens for you to join our Uline family.

Applicants must be authorized to work lawfully in the US without sponsorship.

Join our dynamic Analytics team supporting high level strategic priorities directly connected to Executive Leadership's top priorities. The Business Intelligence Developer role is responsible for understanding and gathering business requirements, solution design, implementation and testing. Utilizing data visualization best practices is a must to ensure that the message is communicated in the most effective way possible.
Using Epic to help your stakeholders improve their performance, and understand the who, what, where, when and why behind their outcomes.Understanding your business stakeholders’ objectives, the metrics that are the most important to them, and how they measure their performance.Turning business requirements into technical requirements.Finding and understanding the correct data sources for a given analysis.Learning from, and sharing knowledge and skills with your teammates to grow impact to the organization.QA Audits and troubleshooting issues
What we need from you:
Bachelor Degree
Epic EHR experience
SQL Proficiency
Knowledge of business intelligence tools and methodologies (Tableau, Business Objects, PowerBI, OBIEE, Qlikview, etc)
3+ years experience in report building and dashboard creation
About Lakeland Regional Health
Since our beginnings as Morrell Memorial Hospital, Lakeland Regional Health has provided more than a century of service to Lakeland and all communities across Central Florida. For the last 100 years, we have honored traditions, planned for the future and delivered healthcare our patients can count on.
As a catalyst for community health, not-for-profit Lakeland Regional Health is reaching beyond our hospital walls to promote wellness, education and discovery in new places and new ways, providing a wide range of inpatient and outpatient healthcare services at our Medical Center, Hollis Cancer Center and outpatient care locations.
We are constantly looking for ways to provide you with the safest, most advanced and very best care, because your story is our story.
Information Technology
Lakeland Regional Health offers business and IT professionals the opportunity to grow and innovate.
Our workplace is ideal for you if you enjoy or seek:
A progressive environment that has earned Most Wired and Most Wired Advanced status from the American Hospital Association four times over the last five years
Educational and professional development opportunities
Access to state-of-the-art technology
Flexible work schedule (every other Friday off)
Organizational Excellence
We actively invest in advancing our team members' career, personal and financial health in exceptional ways.
Lakeland Regional Health is consistently recognized as a workplace of excellence, honored in 2020 as a recipient of the Gold Workplace Wellbeing Award from Aetna.
Among our recent workforce honors:
Florida’s Best Caregiver, Florida Hospital Association, 2019

Company Name: California Department of Managed Health Care
Description: INSTRUCTIONS FOR APPLYINGIt is imperative you read our Job Flyer (linked below) and follow the instructions carefully in order to be considered for this Opportunity!https://www.dmhc.ca.gov/Portals/0/Docs/OTI/BID-Senior-BI-Database-Developer-ITSII-Flyer.pdfYou must reside in California and be eligible to work in the United States without visa sponsorship.THE OPPORTUNITYThis is your opportunity to join a newly energized and highly innovative Business Intelligence team, eager to embrace new technologies to effect digital transformation at the California Department of Managed Health Care (DMHC).REMOTE TELEWORKThis job is a remote telework position. You must reside in the State of California, preferably near Sacramento, to qualify for this opportunity.THE JOB AND DUTIESAs our Senior Analytic Database Developer, you will leverage new and existing technologies to deliver high quality analytic databases that are required to deploy analytic and reporting solutions in support of program office decision making processes. You will deliver within a Data Management framework that will include Data Governance, Master Data Management and Meta Data Management. Our current technology stack includes Tableau, Microsoft SQL Server (with Integration Services and Reporting Services), MarkLogic Platform (NoSQL), ArcGIS geo-spatial data visualization platform! You will participate in exploring Microsoft PowerBI and Azure cloud-based Data Analytics platforms for future consideration and possible implementation.WHAT IS THE DEPARTMENT'S MISSION?Your work will support DMHC’s mission to protect consumers’ health care rights and ensure a stable health care delivery system for California's 27 million consumers!Job Type: Full-timePay: $7,700.00 - $10,318.00 per monthBenefits:Dental insuranceEmployee assistance programFlexible spending accountHealth insurancePaid time offProfessional development assistanceRetirement planVision insuranceSchedule:Monday to FridayApplication Question(s):REQUIRED: Do you require Visa Sponsorship?REQUIRED: Do you currently live in the State of California?REQUIRED: If you DO NOT live in California, are you willing to relocate at your own expense?Experience:Analytic Database Modeling: 4 years (Preferred)Analytic Database Development: 5 years (Preferred)Work Location: Remote

As a UW employee, you have a unique opportunity to change lives on our campuses, in our state and around the world. UW employees offer their boundless energy, creative problem solving skills and dedication to build stronger minds and a healthier world.


UW faculty and staff also enjoy outstanding benefits, professional growth opportunities and unique resources in an environment noted for diversity, intellectual excitement, artistic pursuits and natural beauty.


The Department of Emergency Medicine within the School of Medicine at the University of Washington is comprised of core faculty, contracted faculty, courtesy faculty, resident physicians, and fellows spread across three major sites: Harborview Medical Center (HMC), University of Washington Medical Center (UWMC & NW), and Seattle Children's Hospital (SCH). Emergency Medicine (EM) faculty represents the front line in HMC and UWMC hospital emergency departments and serve the City of Seattle, King County, and WWAMI (Washington/Wyoming/Alaska/Montana/Idaho).


The Department of Emergency Medicine has an outstanding opportunity for a Business Intelligence Developer. The incumbent in this role will be responsible for managing all of the clinical data requests from the Department of Emergency Medicine. The Data Analyst will manage and develop databases for research projects in addition to creating systems to be used for departmental administrative purposes. This position will work with faculty to determine feasibility and execute research projects by providing computing and database support. The BI Developer works closely with the Department Director of Data Science and other DEM leadership to provide analysis, recommend appropriate solutions, and develop those solutions using the best BI solutions available. The BI Developer will create analytics content for the Department of Emergency Medicine users that require data from the electronic health record system. Data analytics is a strategic function within Emergency Medicine with a large set of growing demands. The proper execution of the BI Developer function is essential to both tactical and strategic success of UW Medicine overall. This role provides crucial support to the Department and its partners. The analytics solutions developed by this role are used to support clinical, operational, research, and financial reporting and analysis and are key to the success of the Department and organization as a whole. Adhering to best practices and standards helps support Department and enterprise-wide goals and ensures data standardization across the Department.


This position will collaborate with the partners of UW Medicine and the Department of Emergency Medicine to develop reporting applications, functions, processes, and solutions, to support analysis for clinical, research, financial, operational, and strategic activities. The BI Developer needs to work with many different Department customers, prioritizing their requests, meeting the customers’ analytics needs, validating data to ensure data quality, and communicating status and progress to customers.


The BI Developer provides technical guidance and maintains a high level of awareness of the current and future BI technologies and best practices and must fully understand the various organizational structures of UW Medicine and their unique requirements.


The primary responsibilities of the BI Developer are to: design, code, test, and maintain BI reporting and analytics objects, including extracts utilizing industry best practices. Additionally, this position will be responsible for data queries from department faculty, trainees, and staff. This work includes performing data cleaning, conducting exploratory data extractions, and gathering data for feasibility. The analyst will manage all data requests from faculty as requested for preparatory research activities, current research studies, department quality improvement/assurance data, and clinical operations data. This position will partner with UW Medicine Information Technology Services & Analytics and Epic ASAP Analysts to troubleshoot and develop metrics, workflows and reports.


Position Responsibilities:


BI Solutions Implementation

Provide technical guidance to various cross-functional BI stakeholders.

Perform design and code reviews of developed solutions for quality assurance.

Collaborate with team members to develop BI solutions in a proficient and timely manner, consistent with estimates created during design.

Test solutions developed prior to any external reviews or testing.

Develop and maintain supporting documentation (technical design documents, report inventory, promotion requests, etc.).

Participate in interactions with Department “customers” to communicate status, resolve issues, and obtain signoffs (design complete, testing complete/ready for promotion).

Perform efficient, complete hand-offs to other developers when required.

Report project status and issues to Department Director of Data Science in a timely manner.


Planning and Documentation

Maintain a high level of awareness of the current and future BI technologies and best practices and fully understand the various organizational structures of UW Medicine and their unique requirements.

Coordinate with Business Analysts, Data Architects, Structured Quality Language (SQL) Administrators, BI Administrators and others to understand and document technical requirements, capabilities, and limitations.

Collaborate with Business Analysts, Data Architects, SQL Administrators, BI Administrators and others to design appropriate BI solutions based on business and technical requirements.

Perform project planning related to BI solutions development tasks including effort and completion date estimates.

Work with minimal supervision on assigned tasks and complete tasks in agreed upon timelines.

Obtain and transfer knowledge appropriately when new software or hardware are implemented.


BI Solutions Production Support

Research questions and issues involving BI solutions.

Work with data architects, SQL administrators, BI administrators, BI Developers, and others as needed to resolve to production issues.


Skills Overview

Knowledge of or ability to learn Epic/ASAP, Reporting Workbench, Radar, SlicerDicer and Tableau;

Intermediate SQL skills as desired, ability to build data marts, dashboards, navigate a data warehouse and share central data resources;

Ability to support regular Epic upgrades and data changes and to identify opportunities for improved capability for EM in EHR

Strong communication skills

Critical thinking and an analytical mind

Proficiency and demonstrated experience with analytics tools

Familiarity with Epic applications and database structure, through training that occurs early in the implementation

Ability to gain an in-depth understanding of the data model through data model classes geared toward content areas

Ability to understand data structures that could benefit the entire data environment

Prior experience working with an EMR system is desirable, but not required.

Partner with Chair’s office and Director of finance on clinical data extraction for clinical operations


As a UW employee, you will enjoy generous benefits and work/life programs. For a complete description of our benefits for this position, please visit our website, click here.


REQUIREMENTS

Bachelor’s degree in health informatics, computer information systems, information technology, computer science, math, engineering, statistics, or healthcare related field AND four to five years of relevant work experience with analyst or developer responsibilities to include a minimum of 2 years with the following:

Experience with Business Objects Enterprise and/or Crystal Reports.

Experience with SQL.

Experience with Epic Clarity Clinical Data Model and Reporting.

Experience working through the complete report development lifecycle.

A minimum of one (1) Epic Data Model certifications, or completion of certification within first 6 months of employment.


Equivalent education/experience will substitute for all minimum qualifications except when there are legal requirements, such as a license/certification/registration.

Overview:

We are seeking an Epic Cogito Business Intelligence Developer- Clinical Informatics in Information Services. This position is responsible for identifying workflows, defining requirements and implementing data visualization tools within the Epic system. Understands current, future and present system functionality of clinical information systems through design, configuration, and testing procedures. This role will have opportunities to expand knowledge and skills but will focus on the data, analytics and reporting needs of the clinical informatics team.
**Mostly remote but onsite required for Go-Lives and meetings when needed**
Why Nationwide Children's Hospital?:

Why Nationwide Children’s Hospital
The moment you walk through our doors, you can feel it. When you meet one of our patient families, you believe it. And when you talk with anyone who works here, you want to be part of it, too. Welcome to Nationwide Children’s Hospital, where Passion Meets Purpose.
Here, Everyone Matters. We’re 12,000 strong. And it takes every single one of us to improve the lives of the kids we care for, and the kids from around the world we’ll never even meet. Kids who are living healthier, fuller lives because of the knowledge we share. We know it takes a Collaborative Culture to deliver on our promise to provide the very best, innovative care and to foster new discoveries, made possible by the most groundbreaking research. Anywhere.
Ask anyone with a Nationwide Children’s badge what they do for a living. They’ll tell you it’s More Than a Job. It’s a calling. It’s a chance to use and grow your talent to make an impact that truly matters. Because here, we exist simply to help children everywhere.
Nationwide Children’s Hospital. A Place to Be Proud
Responsibilities:
The Clinical Informatics Application Coordinator will work collaboratively with clinicians and business units to identify solutions to a variety of problems of modest scope and complexity and to identify system enhancements and integration of clinical information systems and workflows.
This role will develop communication, analytical, problem-solving, multi-tasking, and decision-making skills – leveraging both logic and creativity. Competencies for each of the areas below are outlined in the Clinical Informatics Career Ladder.
SYSTEM DESIGN
Understand the business functionality relating to Clinical Information System configuration and workflow
Participate in design alternatives decisions
Participate in the design, configuration and validation of new or modified functionality
Basic awareness of the application of Population Health tools and strategies
DATA, ANALYTICS AND REPORTING
Understand the format of external data definitions documentation and mapping process
Develop understanding of user business practices, concepts and terminology sufficient to support data mapping identification
Develop understanding of mapping medical, laboratory and any other health-related data in compliance with HIPAA policies and procedures
Basic experience with dashboard development including concept design and build
Basic experience with database management, report validation methods and data aggregation strategies
CLINICAL DECISION SUPPORT
Basic experience observing designing solutions to achieve the best clinical outcomes promoting optimal care that reduces errors and achieves organizational goals and objectives
Participate in supporting the development and enhancement of a comprehensive systems to monitor, evaluate, and improve the quality and appropriateness of clinical care
CONSULTATION
Develop client relationships by ensuring timely and effective resolution of issues and communicate recommendations for system modifications and enhancements to the appropriate teams
Understand appropriate use of technology to optimize care delivery process and assist care providers to create and record the evidence of their practice within the Electronic Health record
Work with leadership to create detailed application designs that conform to application guidelines
Qualifications:

To fulfill this role successfully, you must possess these minimum qualifications and experience:
A clinical background in any discipline is highly desired.
Nursing or Pediatric experience preferred.
An operational background in Health Information Technology or Revenue Cycle Management desired for the non-clinical applicants
Experience interacting with clinical or business areas to gather and understand workflow and technical requirements
Bachelor Degree or equivalent experience required. Clinical Licensure and/or other certifications preferred
Epic certification desired
Exceptional interpersonal, presentation, and communication skills required to interact effectively with all levels of the organization and external contacts
Strong skills in use of PC desktop applications such as MS Word, Excel, PowerPoint, and Project
Ability to work flexible schedules to meet job requirements; requires occasional after-hours support and overnight travel.
Epic certification in Cogito, Clarity, Caboodle, Inpatient Clin Doc, Ambulatory or Healthy Planet desirable
Minimum Physical Requirements:
Position requires ability to talk, listen and type.
Position requires the ability to interact effectively with customers and information systems personnel across the organization.

Within the Office of Information Technology (OIT), we currently seek a Business Intelligence (BI) Developer to support and grow our enterprise data and analytics environment. This position will be focused on creating and maintaining the data models (conceptual, logical and physical) for the University’s enterprise data warehouse and creating associated semantic models providing non-IT professionals access to enterprise information. The BI Developer will serve as a member of one or more development or enhancement teams providing a common business vocabulary, capture data requirements, create integrated designs to meet these requirements, and align those designs with enterprise data strategy. Ideal candidates will have excellent technical and interpersonal skills as well as a passion for the University’s mission of research, education, and outreach.
We Offer:
University paid contribution (10% of your salary) to your retirement account - vested immediately.
22 paid vacation days per year, in addition to sick leave and 11 paid holidays.
Reduced tuition opportunities covering 75% - 100% of eligible tuition.
Excellent and affordable health care benefits.
Wellness program with opportunity to earn lower health care rates.
Free disability insurance.
Annual merit increase program.
Flexible work location options, including hybrid and remote work arrangements.
Job Responsibilities:
Create conceptual, logical, and physical data models for our enterprise data warehouse.
Create user semantic layer structures to provide end users with efficient access to transformed data.
Implement data architecture and data governance standards to ensure consistency across subject areas and models.
Perform data analysis activities to capture data requirements clearly, completely, and correctly, and represent them through a logical data model.
Coordinate with clients, data users and key stakeholders to develop and achieve long- term objectives for data architecture and data quality.

Job Title: Sr Business Intelligence Developer- Rev Cycle - Remote
Description:
Why Mayo Clinic

Diversity and inclusion are integral to Mayo Clinic's mission to provide excellent, culturally relevant care in a welcoming environment to patients from a wide variety of backgrounds and creating an inclusive work environment where differences are valued, allowing individuals to achieve and contribute to their fullest potential. This commitment to diversity is woven into the fabric of Mayo Clinic — we embrace these values as we serve our patients, employees, students, suppliers and communities.


Position description
Actively partner with team members by fostering an inclusive work environment and respecting others with different backgrounds, experiences and perspectives.


Develops customized Rev Cycle reporting content using Epic’s Clarity database, specializing in Hospital and Professional Billing.
Distribute and maintain analytics content within Epic Hyperspace, including Reporting Workbench, Radar Dashboards, and Epic-Crystal integrated content.

Uses various software applications such as desktop tools, spreadsheets, report writing software, statistical software, graphical presentation tools, and Business Intelligence applications to assemble, manipulate and/or format data. Maintain Business Intelligence models to design, develop and generate both standard and ad-hoc reports.
Generate reports for internal and external customers for business performance monitoring and business decision making. Works within controls to ensure the accuracy, timeliness and confidentiality of all reports, views, dashboards, analyses and user data. Adherence to all development standards and protocols including the likes of Change Management, Code Review, Documentation and Testing
Educate and advise internal customers on how to leverage available data for consumption. Must be able to develop, maintain, review and explain data models. Stay updated with business operations and Business Intelligence processes. Build relationships with Business Intelligence partners to understand data needs in order to execute with excellence on documented user requirements and prototypes
Demonstrated SQL skills with extensive experience in developing Business Intelligence solutions. Design, develop and troubleshoot extract packages that implement complex programming processes. Extracts operational, performance, statistical and other data from various information systems. Experience with dashboard design and delivery. Must be able to manage multiple tasks simultaneously and react to problems quickly. Must be able to translate concepts and directions into practical solutions.
Must have development experience with relational database structures, multi-dimensional database, and data warehouse design architecture. Determine business intelligence and data warehousing solutions to meet business needs. Identify and resolve data reporting issues in a timely fashion.

Qualifications

Bachelor's degree and a minimum of eight years' revenue cycle, system, or data delivery experience required.

Additional qualifications

Proficiency or certification in Epic’s Revenue Cycle Data Models, including PB, HB. or Claims/Remittance.
Previous experience with Crystal reports preferred.
Knowledge of Epic’s analytics platforms, such as Custom SQL metrics and SlicerDicer preferred.



License or certification

Epic Certification is required within first year of job acceptance.

Exempt

Required education, experience, and tenure may be considered along with internal equity when job offers are extended. The salary range every 2 weeks is approx. $3,035 - $4,555 based on a full-time position.

Yes

Monday - Friday, 8a - 5p

Performs other duties as directed
Leads, plans, and executes projects, small initiatives

Demonstrated experience as a business intelligence developer utilizing DAX and Power Query to tell stories with data using appropriate data and visualization capabilities in Power BI Desktop
4+ years of Power BI cloud service and MS SQL Server experience.
4+ years of database development experience in Oracle or MS SQL Server environments strongly desired.
Strong technical knowledge of data management systems, dimensional modeling, data quality, data governance, analytics, and predictive modeling.
Office 365 and Azure cloud experience is a plus.

Solid presentation skills

Concise reporting to management / peers
Proven experience developing solutions to a variety of challenging problems of broader scope and complexity, using established procedures
A history that illustrates flexibility and adaptability to changing business needs and shows exposure to overcoming fundamental change obstacles
Lean-Agile mindset proficient in the understanding and becoming familiar with the Lean-Agile mindset
NOTE: This role can be supported remotely via telecommute.

Position Title: Senior IT Business Data AnalystDepartment: Information TechnologyA. Primary Purpose of Job: Enable QT to derive value from data by working with assigned business units to understand opportunities where data solutions can support business objectives, improve process efficiency, or support data driven decision making. To deliver on these opportunities, the Senior IT Business Data Analyst analyzes business requirements and associated data, and provides subject matter expertise on systems, data, and business processes to teams tasked with building data solutions. To mitigate risks associated with data usage, the Senior IT Business Data Analyst facilitates data and BI stewardship to ensure data is used consistently and accurately throughout the organization, leading to confident decisions based on trusted data. Additionally, Senior IT Business Data Analysts develop BI data models as well as BI applications (e.g. reports, dashboards, data visualizations) to enable valuable usage of QT data assets. As a senior member of the Data Analyst team, the Senior IT Business Data Analyst assists the Data Engineering Manager in development of new processes, templates, and mentoring of less experienced analysts.B. The major functions for this position: 1. Create, manage, and maintain performant BI and reporting solutions – 30%a. Develop, enhance, and support BI models and applications (e.g. reports, dashboards, data visualizations) in support of customer needs in assigned business areas.b. Partner with assigned business areas to ensure that BI applications and workspaces are optimized for business purpose and aligned with relevant data governance policies.c. Gather and forward customer feedback and suggestions for product improvement.d. Resolve BI issues utilizing excellent customer service, problem solving, and technical thinking/reasoning skills following established support process and metrics guidelines.e. Measure and analyze incoming issues to determine root cause and develop technical and training solutions to minimize reoccurrences and severity; report results to management.f. Accurately document all customer issues, resolution steps, and gather feedback in support tracking software to enhance identifying and reporting trends leading to recurring problems.g. Develop and publish support documentation for internal users for troubleshooting, training and other areas as needed.2. Maintain advanced proficiency with Power BI tools, technology, and concepts - 20%a. Primary BI technology stack in use at QuikTrip is Microsoft, which includes SSAS, SSRS, Power BI, and Excel BI components. Other technologies could be required due to changing business or technical needs.b. Reach and maintain proficiency in all technologies relevant to position. Learn new features as they become available in technology stack utilized by Data Analyst team,c. Stay current on emerging industry capabilities related to data management and business intelligence that could provide ongoing value to assigned business units.3. Business analysis and requirements gathering – 20%a. Analyze and document requirements as well as current state reporting, business rules, and other variables relevant to building proposed data solutions.b. Assist PTOs and developers building data solutions by clarifying business intelligence requirements and performing quality assurance (QA) testing of published data sets, ensuring accuracy and adherence to business rules.c. Act as Data PTO when needed with support of Data Engineering Manager to support team workload. Provide leadership to less experienced team members on projects as well as user workgroups (centers of excellence).4. Assist in documenting and maintaining Power BI governance strategies and standards – 10%a. Capture and maintain information for QT Data Inventory as well as metadata for published data sets.b. Assist the team with the design processes and develop supporting materials such as document templates to assist Data Analyst team in effective support of the company’s data strategy.c. Could also include researching how technology could be better leveraged by analyst team (e.g. Azure DevOps, SharePoint, etc.) and performing implementation tasks.d. Assist Data Engineering Manager on objective to provide consistent, quality BI applications by developing templates, guidelines, and standards for the Data Analyst team to utilize.5. Identify opportunities for data driven solutions – 10%a. Lead data stewardship processes, working with Data Owners, Stewards, and other stakeholders to recommend data sources, definitions, business rules, and data quality rules.b. Facilitate discussions with management and staff in assigned business units to understand challenges and opportunities, which can be addressed with data solutions.c. Develop and maintain knowledge of processes, objectives, systems, and data of assigned business units to pro-actively propose solutions and serve as SME on development efforts.6. Assist in mentorship and training of less experienced team members – 10%a. Mentor and train users in assigned business areas in use of BI tools, which enable them to access and analyze data efficiently to support their job functions and decision making.b. Train and mentor less experienced analysts on relevant data technologies.C. Position in OrganizationReports to:  Data Engineering ManagerDirectly supervises: N/AIndirectly supervises: N/AD. As a UW employee, you have a unique opportunity to change lives on our campuses, in our state and around the world. UW employees offer their boundless energy, creative problem solving skills and dedication to build stronger minds and a healthier world.


UW faculty and staff also enjoy outstanding benefits, professional growth opportunities and unique resources in an environment noted for diversity, intellectual excitement, artistic pursuits and natural beauty.


The Department of Emergency Medicine within the School of Medicine at the University of Washington is comprised of core faculty, contracted faculty, courtesy faculty, resident physicians, and fellows spread across three major sites: Harborview Medical Center (HMC), University of Washington Medical Center (UWMC & NW), and Seattle Children's Hospital (SCH). Emergency Medicine (EM) faculty represents the front line in HMC and UWMC hospital emergency departments and serve the City of Seattle, King County, and WWAMI (Washington/Wyoming/Alaska/Montana/Idaho).


The Department of Emergency Medicine has an outstanding opportunity for a Business Intelligence Developer. The incumbent in this role will be responsible for managing all of the clinical data requests from the Department of Emergency Medicine. The Data Analyst will manage and develop databases for research projects in addition to creating systems to be used for departmental administrative purposes. This position will work with faculty to determine feasibility and execute research projects by providing computing and database support. The BI Developer works closely with the Department Director of Data Science and other DEM leadership to provide analysis, recommend appropriate solutions, and develop those solutions using the best BI solutions available. The BI Developer will create analytics content for the Department of Emergency Medicine users that require data from the electronic health record system. Data analytics is a strategic function within Emergency Medicine with a large set of growing demands. The proper execution of the BI Developer function is essential to both tactical and strategic success of UW Medicine overall. This role provides crucial support to the Department and its partners. The analytics solutions developed by this role are used to support clinical, operational, research, and financial reporting and analysis and are key to the success of the Department and organization as a whole. Adhering to best practices and standards helps support Department and enterprise-wide goals and ensures data standardization across the Department.


This position will collaborate with the partners of UW Medicine and the Department of Emergency Medicine to develop reporting applications, functions, processes, and solutions, to support analysis for clinical, research, financial, operational, and strategic activities. The BI Developer needs to work with many different Department customers, prioritizing their requests, meeting the customers’ analytics needs, validating data to ensure data quality, and communicating status and progress to customers.


The BI Developer provides technical guidance and maintains a high level of awareness of the current and future BI technologies and best practices and must fully understand the various organizational structures of UW Medicine and their unique requirements.


The primary responsibilities of the BI Developer are to: design, code, test, and maintain BI reporting and analytics objects, including extracts utilizing industry best practices. Additionally, this position will be responsible for data queries from department faculty, trainees, and staff. This work includes performing data cleaning, conducting exploratory data extractions, and gathering data for feasibility. The analyst will manage all data requests from faculty as requested for preparatory research activities, current research studies, department quality improvement/assurance data, and clinical operations data. This position will partner with UW Medicine Information Technology Services & Analytics and Epic ASAP Analysts to troubleshoot and develop metrics, workflows and reports.


Position Responsibilities:


BI Solutions Implementation

Provide technical guidance to various cross-functional BI stakeholders.

Perform design and code reviews of developed solutions for quality assurance.

Collaborate with team members to develop BI solutions in a proficient and timely manner, consistent with estimates created during design.

Test solutions developed prior to any external reviews or testing.

Develop and maintain supporting documentation (technical design documents, report inventory, promotion requests, etc.).

Participate in interactions with Department “customers” to communicate status, resolve issues, and obtain signoffs (design complete, testing complete/ready for promotion).

Perform efficient, complete hand-offs to other developers when required.

Report project status and issues to Department Director of Data Science in a timely manner.


Planning and Documentation

Maintain a high level of awareness of the current and future BI technologies and best practices and fully understand the various organizational structures of UW Medicine and their unique requirements.

Coordinate with Business Analysts, Data Architects, Structured Quality Language (SQL) Administrators, BI Administrators and others to understand and document technical requirements, capabilities, and limitations.

Collaborate with Business Analysts, Data Architects, SQL Administrators, BI Administrators and others to design appropriate BI solutions based on business and technical requirements.

Perform project planning related to BI solutions development tasks including effort and completion date estimates.

Work with minimal supervision on assigned tasks and complete tasks in agreed upon timelines.

Obtain and transfer knowledge appropriately when new software or hardware are implemented.


BI Solutions Production Support

Research questions and issues involving BI solutions.

Work with data architects, SQL administrators, BI administrators, BI Developers, and others as needed to resolve to production issues.


Skills Overview

Knowledge of or ability to learn Epic/ASAP, Reporting Workbench, Radar, SlicerDicer and Tableau;

Intermediate SQL skills as desired, ability to build data marts, dashboards, navigate a data warehouse and share central data resources;

Ability to support regular Epic upgrades and data changes and to identify opportunities for improved capability for EM in EHR

Strong communication skills

Critical thinking and an analytical mind

Proficiency and demonstrated experience with analytics tools

Familiarity with Epic applications and database structure, through training that occurs early in the implementation

Ability to gain an in-depth understanding of the data model through data model classes geared toward content areas

Ability to understand data structures that could benefit the entire data environment

Prior experience working with an EMR system is desirable, but not required.

Partner with Chair’s office and Director of finance on clinical data extraction for clinical operations


As a UW employee, you will enjoy generous benefits and work/life programs. For a complete description of our benefits for this position, please visit our website, click here.


REQUIREMENTS

Bachelor’s degree in health informatics, computer information systems, information technology, computer science, math, engineering, statistics, or healthcare related field AND four to five years of relevant work experience with analyst or developer responsibilities to include a minimum of 2 years with the following:

Experience with Business Objects Enterprise and/or Crystal Reports.

Experience with SQL.

Experience with Epic Clarity Clinical Data Model and Reporting.

Experience working through the complete report development lifecycle.

A minimum of one (1) Epic Data Model certifications, or completion of certification within first 6 months of employment.


Equivalent education/experience will substitute for all minimum qualifications except when there are legal requirements, such as a license/certification/registration.

Job Title: Jr Business Intelligence Developer - Early Career

Company / Location Information
Water technology is one of the fastest-growing industries in the world. As a leading global water technology company, A. O. Smith Corporation (NYSE: AOS) is at the center of the trend. We are a $3 billion company with over 140 years of history and 15,000+ employees. Our emphasis is on hot water and clean water; we are one of the world’s largest manufacturers of residential and commercial water heating equipment as well as a supplier of water purification products in a number of emerging countries. With manufacturing operations in the United States, Canada, Mexico, China, India, and Europe, we have the reach to serve customers worldwide. A. O. Smith is committed to continuous improvement and maintaining a culture that values and respects our employees.
Recognized by The Tennessean as one of the top Nashville Workplaces, we have programs in place to help our team members achieve their potential. When you join our team, you will receive rewards and recognition for your contributions, training and professional development opportunities, as well as a variety of benefits to support you and your family's health, well-being, and financial future. If you are inspired to learn, take risks, and succeed as a team, you can build an amazing career at A. O. Smith.
This role is located in our modern Nashville Metro Center office, located just minutes from downtown with easy interstate access and free parking.
Primary Function
Innovation has a name, and it is A.O. Smith, the global leader in water technology. We have a unique opportunity on our Analytics solutions team for a recent or upcoming (Fall 2021) graduate with a career interest in Analytics.
The position will start as part of a cross-functional leadership development program receiving 3 months of training and exposure across the broader A.O. Smith organization before transitioning to the role on the Analytics solutions team.
Responsibilities
Analytics Development (SAP Web Intelligence, Tableau, and SAP Analysis for Excel)
Analyze, cleanse, transform, and join data sources
Complete visualization, dashboard, and reporting projects
Community Building
Engage with Divisional Analysts to provide mentoring on visualization best practices, analytics tools, data warehouse access, and data transformation techniques
Facilitate BI Community of Practice events
Participate in development and maintenance of an Analyst Certification program
Help Desk
Administer Tableau and SAP Business Objects servers
Provide first-line Analytics support for Divisional Analysts and Analytics Consumers.
Maintain help desk tickets and support metrics
Develop and maintain a knowledge base of production support solutions
Qualifications
Naturally curious, a quick learner and strong problem solver
Degree in Business, Information Technology, Mathematics, or related discipline
consideration will be given to other graduates whose degree included a minor in mathematics, statistics, quantitative methods, or data science
Experience with visualization tools like Tableau, Power BI, or Cognos
Academic exposure to data warehousing, data analysis, database management, SQL, scripting (R or Python), software development, or business would be beneficial
Good organizational skills with exceptional attention to detail
Excellent written and verbal communication
Demonstrated experience with Microsoft Word, and Microsoft Excel
We Offer
Great people make our organization great and because of that, we offer an A. O. Smith Company merchandise store for our employees, employee discounts on water filtration products, a competitive compensation plan, comprehensive medical benefits and a retirement security savings plan.

The primary role of this position is to improve processes and facilitate deeper business insight and discovery within the Finance organization through automation, reporting, and interactive dashboards.

The position is responsible for contributing to the design of the Asurion’s Finance information architecture, across all data types (structured, semi-structured and unstructured), balancing the need for access against security and performance requirements.

To succeed in this role, the candidate should know how to elicit and examine data requirements and implement data models, dashboards, and other reporting solutions based on those requirements. The ideal candidate will also have proven experience in data analysis, creating data insight/discovery solutions, and possess excellent analytical and problem-solving abilities.
Essential Functions
Combines knowledge of Microsoft Power BI, Presto, SSRS and SSIS programming in addition to other programming tools and techniques to produce innovative, automated, efficient data related solutions.
Contribute to the migration of data from legacy SQL Server systems to solutions based on the AWS cloud platform.
Collaborates with client teams to gather project requirements, align/adjust requirements to available resources, deliver and maintain within agreed SLA’s.
Proactively seeks out opportunities for both process and insight improvement and makes recommendations for implementation
Ability to communicate complex analytical and technical information and recommendations to project sponsors and senior level audiences
Maintain a working knowledge of Asurion's applications and system integration.
Act as a subject matter expert in the assigned area of responsibility.
Excellent organizational and analytical skills.
Required Qualifications
Education Requirements: Minimum 4-year college degree in related field (Computer Science, Mathematics, Finance/Accounting) or relevant experience
Minimum four years of data analysis, preferably in the insurance industry or telecom.
Experience with Cloud based reporting tools on the AWS platform
Experience working with cloud based data including data modeling, and writing complex SQL statements
Ability to master complicated data models quickly and comprehensively
Strong analytic/problem-solving skills, writing skills, organization skills, prioritization skills and communication skills
Capability to participate in multiple concurrent projects
Desired Qualifications
Experience with Windows based application development (VB, C#, .NET)
Demonstrated experience in understanding of general ledger accounts and journal entries a plus but not required

PURPOSE AND SCOPE:
The ETL (Extract, Transform, Load) Developer designs, develops and supports ETL process and tools. The ETL Developer is responsible for data loading and manipulation to ensure that the data sources are efficiently and effectively loaded into the data warehouse. Participates in data acquisition and transformation delivery and may provide oversight and technical checkpoints to enforce standards and quality of BI solutions. Researches new technologies, tools and methodologies as they emerge that may be applicable. Responsible for collaborating with the IT support teams to ensure that technical architecture complies with guidelines and restrictions for applicable environments.
PRINCIPAL RESPONSIBILITIES AND DUTIES:
Assist in the ongoing development of technical best practices for data movement, data quality, data cleansing and other ETL-‐related activities.
Provide technical knowledge of Extract/Transform/Load (ETL) solutions for Business Intelligence projects.
Excellent written and verbal communication skills and be able to lead meetings with technical peers regarding the solution designs. Ability to communicate with the Business Analysts, Data Modelers and Solution Architects when it comes to converting the ETL design into specific development activities
Ability to do ETL development and to supervise and guide ETL development activities of other developers
Understands and implements best practices, tuning and optimization for commonly used BI tools
Serve as the Lead Designer of all ETL activities for a specific project
Work closely with project Business Analyst, Data Modeler and BI Lead to ensure that the end to end designs meet the business and data requirements
Work closely with Project Manager to develop and update the task plan for ETL work and to keep the manager aware of any critical task issues and dependencies on other teams
Develop the task plan for ETL developers for a specific project
Supervise, lead and assist the creation of the data layer
Perform checkpoints/reviews on presentation layer designs and code being created by the ETL developers
Ensure that developers are applying Schumacher Group standards in all deliverables
Lead Unit and Integration Testing activities and assist in User Acceptance Testing as needed

CUSTOMER SERVICE:
Responsible for driving the HXG culture through values and customer service standards.
Accountable for outstanding customer service to all external and internal contacts.
Develops and maintains positive relationships through effective and timely communication.
Takes initiative and action to respond, resolve and follow up regarding customer service issues with all customers in a timely manner
EXPERIENCE AND REQUIRED SKILLS:
Experience designing and developing with ETL Tools
Designing and developing with Relational Reporting Tools
Managing or coordinating the time and activities of other people and other groups
Experience with tools such as Oracle SQL, PL SQL, Microsoft SSIS, Informatica, or other similar ETL tool
Demonstrated experience working on strategy projects and evaluating software in the Business Intelligence, Data Warehouse and/or Data Management space
Willingness to accept and navigate political situations to ensure the program continues to make progress

EDUCATION:
Bachelor's degree in computer science, information technology, other computer-based discipline or equivalent combination of education and relevant experience
PHYSICAL DEMANDS AND WORKING CONDITIONS:
The physical demands and work environment characteristics described here are representative of those an employee encounters while performing the essential functions of this job. Reasonable accommodations may be made to enable individuals with disabilities to perform the essential functions.
While performing the duties of this position, the employee is frequently required to sit, either in an office environment, or in the context of operating a vehicle. The position is also required to: talk, hear, taste, smell, stand, walk; use hands and fingers to handle, operate, or operate objects, tools, or controls; reach with hands and arms; and occasionally climb and/or balance their body; and stoop, kneel, crouch, crawl. The employee must intermittently lift and/or move objects that weigh approximately 10-25 pounds, and on rare occasions lift and/or move objects that weigh approximately 100 pounds. This job is responsible for all stages of the business intelligence cycle: understanding business objective, collecting business requirements and translating them into data requirements, designing and developing reports or dashboards (code and visualization), scheduling and deployment of business intelligence components in accordance with supplied standards and best practices, and completing accurate and timely documentation. Maintains and develops documentation to identify and define processes or procedures. Manages data by following best practices. Supports and monitors business intelligence systems and processes. Administers business intelligence server(s) and/or processes. Serves as a technical resource and support to multiple teams. Other related duties as required.

Salary: $92,394 to $129,480 per year

Education Requirement: Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science or related IT field.

Other Requirements: Must have either: (a) 60 months of progressive experience as a Computer Programmer or related IT occupation plus a Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Computer Applications, Computer Information Systems or related IT field; or (b) a Master's degree in computer science, computer applications, Computer Information Systems or related IT field plus 36 months of progressive experience as a computer programmer or related IT occupation. Experience must include three years of experience as a business intelligence analyst, using SQL for daily tasks, creating reports and visualizations using Oracle Business Intelligence Enterprise Edition, Tableau, Crystal Reports, or similar business intelligence tool and administering business intelligence server or process (i.e. Tableau Server or Epic Cogito Admin).

George Mason University, Information Technology Services (ITS) – located on the Fairfax, Va., campus—invites applications for a Business Intelligence Report Developer position within the Enterprise Applications, Business Intelligence Services team. George Mason University has a strong institutional commitment to the achievement of excellence and diversity among its faculty and staff, and strongly encourages candidates to apply who will enrich Mason’s academic and culturally inclusive environment.

Responsibilities:


This position will be responsible for developing complex reports, modifying existing reports and providing technical support to University report writers. Additionally, this position will assist the data mart team in functional and performance testing strategies for new and existing reports. The BI Report Developer will also develop training material and conduct training sessions for users of the various University data marts and reports. This individual must have significant working knowledge of SQL, preferably with Oracle databases, knowledge of data warehouse architecture, and experience with business intelligence reporting tools including MicroStrategy.

Required Qualifications:

Demonstrates significant working knowledge of SQL queries;
Experience developing reports in a Business Intelligence tool or a reporting tool, such as MicroStrategy, Power BI, Cognos, Crystal Reports or Microsoft Access;
Excellent communication skills for supporting both functional area users and ITS technical staff;
Ability to multi-task; and
BS or higher degree in computer science or related field; or equivalent combination of education and experience.



Preferred Qualifications:

Understanding of MicroStrategy reporting, architecture and operations;
Demonstrates working knowledge of Data Warehouse design and Star Schema methodology;
Experience with Oracle Databases; and
Performance tuning of SQL queries.


Salary is commensurate with education and experience.

George Mason University is a great place to work where employees are given an opportunity to develop skills and expand horizons. We have tuition waivers; telecommuting (typically one day a week) and flextime schedules; facilities that will meet your physical fitness needs; and the campus environment is dynamic and ethnically and culturally diverse.

Company Name: Blue Cross and Blue Shield of North Carolina
Description:
Act as a liaison between the business and technical communities for reporting/analytic development purposes. Design and develop Business Intelligence content (reports, dashboards, scorecards, analytic solutions) by identifying reporting/analytic requirements and determining business rules through a structured elicitation process. Ensure that information and BI content satisfies Enterprise business needs and the needs of individual departments.
Elicit and review business reporting and analytic requirements from the business groups through formal interviews or facilitated sessions and translate into technical designs for enterprise business intelligence implementation.
Develop BI content (reports, dashboards, scorecards, analytic solutions) through the entire development life-cycle to provide data necessary to effectively make business decisions and measure goal attainment and overall performance.
Participate in work-stream planning process including inception, technical design, development, testing and delivery of BI solutions that emphasize speed to market results.
Perform analysis for a wide range of requests using data in different formats and from various platforms
Assist in BI tool evaluation including the development of proof-of-concept and pilot solutions.
Develop knowledge of business area processes and information needs and apply that knowledge in designing BI content for our users.
Coordinate user acceptance testing with the business community to ensure accurate delivery of data from the business requirements with the goal of receiving sign off.
Guide and advise business areas in identifying new data needs and delivery mechanisms for reporting information as well as self-service solutions.
Provide assistance to business areas in understanding enterprise data content, definitions and usage and the available BI tools.
Work with business areas to adapt their business processes to effectively use enterprise data sources for information and analytical needs.
Hiring Requirements
Bachelor’s degree with 5 years of proven Business Intelligence development skills.
If no degree, 7 years of proven Business Intelligence development skills
The majority of our roles will continue working from home until at least the end of 2021. Once it is safe to begin working onsite, employees can choose where they work – from home, in the office, or a hybrid of the two. During the interview process, our Talent Advisors will walk through our virtual-first approach and answer questions you may have.

Job Title: Sr Business Intelligence Developer- Rev Cycle - Remote
Description:
The primary role of this position is to improve processes and facilitate deeper business insight and discovery within the Finance organization through automation, reporting, and interactive dashboards.

The position is responsible for contributing to the design of the Asurion’s Finance information architecture, across all data types (structured, semi-structured and unstructured), balancing the need for access against security and performance requirements.

To succeed in this role, the candidate should know how to elicit and examine data requirements and implement data models, dashboards, and other reporting solutions based on those requirements. The ideal candidate will also have proven experience in data analysis, creating data insight/discovery solutions, and possess excellent analytical and problem-solving abilities.
Essential Functions
Combines knowledge of Microsoft Power BI, Presto, SSRS and SSIS programming in addition to other programming tools and techniques to produce innovative, automated, efficient data related solutions.
Contribute to the migration of data from legacy SQL Server systems to solutions based on the AWS cloud platform.
Collaborates with client teams to gather project requirements, align/adjust requirements to available resources, deliver and maintain within agreed SLA’s.
Proactively seeks out opportunities for both process and insight improvement and makes recommendations for implementation
Ability to communicate complex analytical and technical information and recommendations to project sponsors and senior level audiences
Maintain a working knowledge of Asurion's applications and system integration.
Act as a subject matter expert in the assigned area of responsibility.
Excellent organizational and analytical skills.
Required Qualifications
Education Requirements: Minimum 4-year college degree in related field (Computer Science, Mathematics, Finance/Accounting) or relevant experience
Minimum four years of data analysis, preferably in the insurance industry or telecom.
Experience with Cloud based reporting tools on the AWS platform
Experience working with cloud based data including data modeling, and writing complex SQL statements
Ability to master complicated data models quickly and comprehensively
Strong analytic/problem-solving skills, writing skills, organization skills, prioritization skills and communication skills
Capability to participate in multiple concurrent projects
Desired Qualifications
Experience with Windows based application development (VB, C#, .NET)
Demonstrated experience in understanding of general ledger accounts and journal entries a plus but not required

Position: IT Business Intelligence (BI) Developer


Location: Hendersonville, USA


Reporting to: Development BI Team Lead
Genus PLC:


Genus is a FTSE 250 company, headquartered in the UK and listed on the London Stock Exchange. With

revenues of around $600 million, it has a workforce of approximately 3,000 employees throughout the

world. Genus has been one of the best performing stocks on the London Stock Exchange.


Genus is a global market leader in bovine and porcine genetic improvement, Genus helps its customers in

the dairy, beef and porcine supply chains around the world. Genus’ vision of “pioneering animal genetic

improvement to help nourish the world” is supported by its core values to be customer-centric, results-
driven, pioneering, people-focused and responsible.



Overview:


Reporting to the Development BI Team Lead role is an excellent opportunity for someone seeking to gain

experience in BI development for a growing team to help shape how we support our customers within a

people centric, global business working as part of the global BI team.


The ideal candidate:


Ideally you will be experienced in working closely with key business partners and other team members to

ensure that our data and BI Reporting Solutions meet and as much as possible exceed business expectations.

The successful candidate will be key to delivery of our Azure based enterprise data warehouse and reporting

capability at Genus, using tools including; SSIS, SSAS, Power BI and more specific Azure tools such Data Factory

and Data Bricks. Working as part of a team to enhance our extraction, transformation, and load processes and

increase data quality and value across our different platforms. They will also work with our QA team write

robust and reusable testing scripts for our BI solutions and develop self-serve, self-development capability as

well as undertaking advanced data visualization for different business units across the enterprise.


Key Accountabilities:
Owning and completing project tasks as part of the digital transformation of Genus within timescales;
including development and testing of change in the data warehouse, Analysis Services, Power BI

dataset and reporting areas. This will also require active planning support for development work with

stakeholder management activities.
Ensure that all work is carried through the environments, source controlled with regularity and
deployments packages are robust and well organised. Ensuring all conflicts in this area are

merged/escalated effectively.
Undertake/support the monitoring of BAU processes as directed, including undertaking root cause
analysis, advising remediation options and if required delivering a solution including delivering any

early lifecycle support as needed.

2
Supporting operational and BAU change requests and issues, completing change request tasks as
assigned, through to completion of Early life support.
Work closely with data architects, data modeller, and software developers to ensure data lineage is
properly designed and captured for BI solutions.
Working with developers, architects, analysts, and product owners to ensure the testing script is
understood and that the acceptance tests track the desired functionality
Identify, report, and fix material bugs and deficiencies in the tools used, utilising internal and external
resources
Map and document our BI processes and environment
Develop, maintain, and document our BI development standards
Architect BI solutions for new and existing BI reporting solutions for different business units.
Upskilling Genus resource where required


Desired Skills/qualifications/Experience:

Proven experience development and architectural design of a MS SQL Server based BI environment.
This includes, but is not limited to, the design and development of Data Warehouse based on

dimensional modelling.
Proven experience using MS SQL in Azure to access, query, and manipulate data, and proven
experience using MS SSIS and Azure Data Factory to develop, implement, and maintain ETL processes
Ideally experience with delivering datasets using various Power BI model types and Azure Analysis for
user self-serve. With proven experience utilising Power BI to create impactful visualisations, if not

then ideally demonstrate experience with a similar visualisation tool.
Ideally experience of using Data Bricks or Azure Synapse
Proven experience in gathering low level requirements
Working knowledge of a system development methodology and project management
Relevant Certifications and prove of continuous professional development
Proficient in using Microsoft Word, Excel and Power Point is essential
A self-motivated team player

Ability to work in and manage multiple projects and meet established deadlines.
Proven business analytical skills
Excellent oral and writing skills with ability to communicate in an organised and concise manner

Job Description & Qualifications
At Ford Motor Company, we believe freedom of movement drives human progress. We also believe in providing you with the freedom to define and realize your dreams. With our incredible plans for the future of mobility, we have a wide variety of opportunities for you to accelerate your career potential as you help us define tomorrow’s transportation.

Creating the future of smart mobility requires the highly intelligent use of data, metrics and analytics. That’s where you can make an impact as part of our Global Data Insight & Analytics team. We are the trusted advisers that enable Ford to clearly see business conditions, customer needs and the competitive landscape. With our support, key decision makers can act in meaningful, positive ways. Join us and use your data expertise and analytical skills to drive evidence-based, timely decision making.
What you’ll be able to do:
We are seeking expert Business Intelligence professionals to add to our team to drive the metrics and analytics capability in Business Intelligence. Business Intelligence Analysts work in a Product Management Delivery model working end-to-end with business managers, product owners, product designers, data engineers, software developers to deliver next-gen analytics innovation.

Requires outstanding organization skills combined with critical thinking, problem-solving and agile management tools to support team success.
Facilitates meetings with business subject matter experts, decision makers, systems owners, and end users to define goals and requirements for reports, dashboards, and analytics; mentor business users on reporting design
Analyzes business requirements and translates them into high level design based on BI best practices.
Design, develop, deliver reporting instruments, dashboards and ad-hoc solutions using BI tools (semantic layer, analytics, dashboards, report definitions)
Become a Subject Matter Expert in the commercial vehicle business by being able to understand the business operations, metrics definitions to deliver insights that will drive the business forward
Ensures quality data creation, presentation, and data flow across systems
Develop and implement BI report objects supporting end-user business requirements
You will work on a business team of talented BI/Data professionals driven to provide scalable, automated solutions around the globe.
Collaborates within the technical stakeholder teams such as Data Architects, Data Modelers, ETL Developers, Enterprise Architects, BI Developers, Project Managers, Platform Architects, Data Science Managers for implementation of the large-scale data analytics/BI solution.
Clearly articulates rationale for design decisions to various user groups from business to technical

The minimum requirements we seek:
Bachelor’s degree
5+ years of experience in Microsoft Office products
3+ years in Data Visualization or Business Intelligence tools (e.g. Tableau, Qlik, Looker, Cognos or Power BI)
3 + years of experience in Data Engineering (e.g. ETL, SQL, Python or Alteryx)

Our preferred requirements:
Strong SQL skills and various BI/Reporting tools to build self-serve reports, analytic dashboards and ad-hoc packages leveraging our enterprise data warehouse.
Strong experience consuming data models, developing SQL, addressing data quality issues, proposing BI solution architecture, articulating best practices in end-user visualizations, coupled with hardworking
Development delivery experience.
Candidates for this position are expert business intelligence and analytics developers
Solid understanding of BI tools, architectures and visualization solutions.

What you’ll receive in return:
As part of the Ford family, you’ll enjoy excellent compensation and a comprehensive benefits package that includes generous PTO, retirement, savings and stock investment plans, incentive compensation and much more. You’ll also experience exciting opportunities for professional and personal growth and recognition.

If you have what it takes to help us redefine the future of mobility, we’d love to have you join us.

The Business Analyst 2, GPS (Global People Services) serves as a primary interface between our between our COE and Regional customers and the solution leads (platform developers). Serves as an internal consultant and change agent for assigned HR digital platforms to manage project demand, refine requirements with requestors, balance request priority, set delivery timing expectations, and schedule run the business platform maintenance with our Nissan Digital counterparts. This position easily transitions between technical discussions with developers and business language for requestors to ensure the appropriate solutions are provided on time. This position regularly reviews enhancement backlogs and delivery timelines with Internal GPS teams, Customers, and Nissan Digital to ensure priority requests are moving appropriately and collaborates to ensure global programs are completed on time. This position reviews release cycles and ensures business users are available to perform UAT and confirm successful solution delivery within a narrow time window.

This position also supports program management activities supporting overall management of the project portfolio for GPS and the meeting governance of GPS as a whole. Some of these PMO activities include but are not limited to collaboration meetings among various stakeholders, project status reviews, team performance metrics, global change management, and audit coordination.

Job Functions

The following job function statements describe the general nature and level of work being performed. They are not to be construed as an exhaustive list of all responsibilities, duties and skills required of personnel so classified. The job function statements reflect expectations of the fully trained, proficient incumbent who meets all performance criteria.

The position is an internal consultancy role that is responsible for leading investigation of processes, technology, cost, and strategy while identifying options for improving and bridging the needs of the business with the use of systems and technology while working with the Solutions team to propose appropriate resolution.

Serves as the conduit between the customer community (internal and external customers) and the solutions team through which requirements flow. (business units, technology teams and support teams)

Gains and maintains a working knowledge of high-level product functionality, to aid in interface with business users and collection of technical requirement documents.

Manage client and customer expectations through timely checkpoints to provide status on issues, roadblocks, risks, changes and accomplishments

Escalate issues to management appropriately to support timely resolution and ensure continued progress to project completion

The position will understand, interpret and suggest resolution to technical systematic issues in collaboration with the Solutions Team and communicates these issues effectively to management and peers.

Facilitates and participates in continuous improvement efforts outlined by platform owners.

The position interfaces within several domains, including cross-functional and cross-regional business functions.

Documents maintenance needs and submits technical specifications to the Service Delivery team for execution.

Manages the governance of key GPS responsibilities such as governance meetings, platform audits, knowledge management and enhancement creation access.

Develops and coordinates change management on global program plans aligning with product owners and HR functional users, communications, training, and awareness activities.

Coordinates with other teams on the communication of new product releases and knowledge of new product features and enhancements to support digital HR platforms.

Serves in a product/project management capacity:
Leads system programs that require global coordination and timing alignment.

Coordinates UAT for required configuration changes.

Aids adoption of platform technologies.

Manages project deliverables and deadlines including changes, enhancements, upgrades and implementations.

Supports all activities within assigned area and works closely with peers to support and ensure alignment.

As necessary, performs other related duties of which the above are representative.

Minimum Qualifications

The following qualification statements reflect the minimum skills and abilities required of the qualified applicant.

Bachelor’s degree in Business Administration/Strategy, Information Systems, Finance, Mathematics/Statistics or related field. Advanced degree in related discipline (MBA) preferred.

3+ years of directly related professional level experience.

2+ years of experience in business analyst, product/project management leadership required.

2+ years platform experience including Workday, ServiceNow, or Cornerstone required.

V-Up or Six Sigma certifications are preferred.

Occasional day or overnight travel; global travel may be necessary to support projects.

Ability to work outside standard business hours to collaborate with global counterparts required.

Job Knowledge and Skill:
The candidate must possess the skills to read, understand, lead interpretation of, and communicate technical systematic issues effectively to management and peers.

Possesses excellent communication skills in both written and verbal communication with both technical and non-technical audiences.

Strong analytical and product management skills required, including a thorough understanding of how to interpret customer business needs and translate them into application and operational requirements.

Drive and challenge business units on their assumptions of how they will successfully execute their plans

Ability to lead the teams efforts to establish deliverables and detail customer requirements, constraints, and assumptions with stakeholders and service providers in order to establish the deliverables for the service providers, eliciting requirements using interviews, document analysis, requirements workshops, surveys, site visits, business process descriptions, use cases, scenarios, business analysis, task and workflow analysis.

Supports team building through mutual trust and encourages respect and cooperation among team members.

Demonstrates high ethics and values by inspiring loyalty and trust, handles oneself ethically following core values and beliefs.

Successfully engage in multiple initiatives simultaneously

Experience with cross-functional, cross-affiliate, multi-cultural/global teams on activities/projects

Self-motivated, results-oriented, self-starter with a successful track record, able to manage multiple assignments concurrently with minimal supervision.

Strong emotional intelligence and demonstrated ability to handle highly sensitive and confidential information.

Ability to think critically about a problem and provide a solution. Knowledge and use of PDCA process.

Project management skills help the candidate manage projects, resources, risk, and change.

Interpersonal skills help the candidate work with end users as well as with other Analysts, developers, and other systems professionals.

Must be detail-oriented.

Must be flexible and possess the ability to adapt to changing priorities.
