Job Title: Jr Business Intelligence Developer - Early Career
Description:
Company / Location Information
Water technology is one of the fastest-growing industries in the world. As a leading global water technology company, A. O. Smith Corporation (NYSE: AOS) is at the center of the trend. We are a $3 billion company with over 140 years of history and 15,000+ employees. Our emphasis is on hot water and clean water; we are one of the world’s largest manufacturers of residential and commercial water heating equipment as well as a supplier of water purification products in a number of emerging countries. With manufacturing operations in the United States, Canada, Mexico, China, India, and Europe, we have the reach to serve customers worldwide. A. O. Smith is committed to continuous improvement and maintaining a culture that values and respects our employees.
Recognized by The Tennessean as one of the top Nashville Workplaces, we have programs in place to help our team members achieve their potential. When you join our team, you will receive rewards and recognition for your contributions, training and professional development opportunities, as well as a variety of benefits to support you and your family's health, well-being, and financial future. If you are inspired to learn, take risks, and succeed as a team, you can build an amazing career at A. O. Smith.
This role is located in our modern Nashville Metro Center office, located just minutes from downtown with easy interstate access and free parking.
Primary Function
Innovation has a name, and it is A.O. Smith, the global leader in water technology. We have a unique opportunity on our Analytics solutions team for a recent or upcoming (Fall 2021) graduate with a career interest in Analytics.
The position will start as part of a cross-functional leadership development program receiving 3 months of training and exposure across the broader A.O. Smith organization before transitioning to the role on the Analytics solutions team.
Responsibilities
Analytics Development (SAP Web Intelligence, Tableau, and SAP Analysis for Excel)
Analyze, cleanse, transform, and join data sources
Complete visualization, dashboard, and reporting projects
Community Building
Engage with Divisional Analysts to provide mentoring on visualization best practices, analytics tools, data warehouse access, and data transformation techniques
Facilitate BI Community of Practice events
Participate in development and maintenance of an Analyst Certification program
Help Desk
Administer Tableau and SAP Business Objects servers
Provide first-line Analytics support for Divisional Analysts and Analytics Consumers.
Maintain help desk tickets and support metrics
Develop and maintain a knowledge base of production support solutions
Qualifications
Naturally curious, a quick learner and strong problem solver
Degree in Business, Information Technology, Mathematics, or related discipline
consideration will be given to other graduates whose degree included a minor in mathematics, statistics, quantitative methods, or data science
Experience with visualization tools like Tableau, Power BI, or Cognos
Academic exposure to data warehousing, data analysis, database management, SQL, scripting (R or Python), software development, or business would be beneficial
Good organizational skills with exceptional attention to detail
Excellent written and verbal communication
Demonstrated experience with Microsoft Word, and Microsoft Excel
We Offer
Great people make our organization great and because of that, we offer an A. O. Smith Company merchandise store for our employees, employee discounts on water filtration products, a competitive compensation plan, comprehensive medical benefits and a retirement security savings plan.

The ETL Developer is responsible for data loading and manipulation to ensure that the data sources are efficiently and effectively loaded into the data warehouse. Researches new technologies, tools and methodologies as they emerge that may be applicable. Responsible for collaborating with the IT support teams to ensure that technical architecture complies with guidelines and restrictions for applicable environments.

Excellent written and verbal communication skills and be able to lead meetings with technical peers regarding the solution designs. Supervise, lead and assist the creation of the data layer

Ensure that developers are applying Schumacher Group standards in all deliverables
Lead Unit and Integration Testing activities and assist in User Acceptance Testing as needed

Xylem, a leading global water technology company dedicated to solving the world’s most challenging water issues, is the leading global provider of efficient, innovative and sustainable water technologies improving the way water is used, managed, conserved and re-used. Our international team is unified in a common purpose: creating advanced technology and other trusted solutions to solve the world’s water challenges. We are committed to creating an organization of inclusion and diversity, where everyone feels involved, respected, valued and connected, and where everyone is free to bring their authentic selves and ideas.

Employee Networks – Our Employee Networks provide a professional, supportive network for employees from diverse backgrounds, including Women’s, LGBT+ and Allies, Veteran’s, People of Color and Allies, Hispanic Origin & Latin Affinity, Emerging Leaders, and Working Parents Networks.

Classification Title: Database Developer, E26

Location: 400 South Fort Harrison Avenue, Clearwater, FL 33756 (remote option available)

Does data intrigue you and customer questions inspire you? Do you want to transform the way decision makers use information? Do you find yourself dreaming up ways to help customers visualize pathways through problems or understand root cause? If yes to any, join our team to use your skills and imagination to enable technology solutions that help government organizations deliver critical services to the local residents, help us to level up services for citizens, creating easier way to access services.

The Office of Technology and Innovation (OTI) is seeking a savvy database developer to help us forge new ways to enable higher level business decisions in government departments and deliver more effective application solutions. OTI is seeking a professional with sound understanding and skill in databases (relational and non-relational), data design for applications and for business intelligence, data visualization, business intelligence, application design and software development. Experience with AWS and cloud computing is a plus.

Essential Job Functions

Understands and implements development best practices (ITIL, DevOps, Agile, Scrum, etc.)
Able to develop professional project artifacts to enable system design, team communication, and project efficiencies: Analysis, Design, Business Process Improvement, Data Modeling, Development, Planning, Implementation, Test Script Development, Monitoring/Controls, Troubleshooting/Problem Solving, Documentation, and Service Motivation
Organized, prepares and takes responsibility for project plans/schedules, and outlines requirements, tasks, work assignments, resources and critical milestones.
Makes and delivers informal and formal presentations, both verbally and in writing, to peers, managers, and customers at various levels of the organization using clear, concise and effective communication.
Counsels, evaluates, and rates organizational and employee performance.
Performs other related job duties as assigned.

Position Specific Responsibilities

Developing data-driven business application solutions.
Database maintenance, development
Overseeing project deliverables for software applications with a data focus
Database, data warehouse or data lakes design, development, and support.
Develop reports, dashboards, data visualizations.
Design and implement data security requirements for HIPAA or CJIS systems.
Work with business customers on understanding and documenting requirements, creating specifications, and prioritizing work.
Position Specific Requirements

Seven (7) years of technical and professional experience in information technology in four (4) of the responsibility areas above that includes customer service and one (1) year of professional team leadership or supervision; or an Associate’s degree in information technology, computer science, computer technology, or related field and five (5) years of experience in four (4) of the responsibility areas above that includes customer service and one (1) year of professional team leadership or supervision; or a Bachelor’s degree in information technology, computer science, computer technology, or related field and three (3) years of experience in four (4) of the responsibility areas above that includes customer service and one (1) year of professional team leadership or supervision; or an equivalent combination of education, training, and/or experience.
Must be able to travel to frequent meetings held in a variety of locations across the County.
Assignment to work a variety of work schedules including compulsory work periods in special, emergency, and/or disaster situations.

Highly Desirable

Master’s degree and 8+ years of experience.

Knowledge, Skills, and Abilities
Database and data warehouse systems (SQL Server, Oracle, MySQL, Maria DB, Redshift, Athena, S3, etc.)
Software Development Languages (e.g., Python, Java, C#, SQL, JavaScript, etc.)
Data Security (CJIS, HIPAA, etc.)
Business Intelligence & Analytics Systems (Power BI, OBIEE, Tableau, etc.)
ETL Tools (FME, Glue, etc.)
Ability to lead or mentor teams and facilitate groups to achieve success.
Ability to prepare and deliver effective presentations at various levels.
Ability to use diplomacy in dealing with difficult customers and delivery of services.
Ability to communicate with tact, patience and courtesy at all levels of the organization.
Ability to identify, to take ownership of, and to lead efforts to solve complex problems.
Physical/Mental Demands

The work is sedentary work which requires exerting up to 10 pounds of force occasionally and/or negligible amount of force frequently or constantly to lift, carry, push, pull, or otherwise move objects, including the human body. Additionally, the following physical abilities are required:
Fingering: Picking, pinching, typing, or otherwise working, primarily with fingers rather than with the whole hand as in handling.
Visual ability: Sufficient to effectively operate office equipment including copier, computer, etc.; and to read and write reports, correspondence, instructions, etc.
Hearing ability: Sufficient to hold a conversation with other individuals both in person and over a telephone; and to hear recording on transcription device.
Speaking ability: Sufficient to communicate effectively with other individuals in person and over a telephone.
Mental acuity: Ability to make rational decisions through sound logic and deductive processes.
Talking: Expressing or exchanging ideas by means of the spoken word including those activities in which they must convey detailed or important spoken instructions to other workers accurately, loudly, or quickly.
Repetitive motion: Substantial movements (motions) of the wrist, hands, and/or fingers.
Walking: Moving about on foot to accomplish tasks, particularly for long distances or moving from one work site to another.

Working Conditions

Work is performed in a dynamic environment that requires sensitivity to change and responsiveness to changing goals, priorities, and needs.

About the job:

The Red Hat North America (NA) Services Operations team is looking for a Reports Dashboard Developer to join us. In this role, you'll join the NA Services Operations team that is responsible for managing the tools, systems, processes, and data that make the Red Hat Consulting organization more efficient, effective, and data-driven. You’ll develop reporting dashboards which enable analysis on the performance of services deliveries across global and regional services teams. You'll also work closely with the Services Enterprise Data Analytics team, Global Services team, and other internal teams to design dashboards which are used to measure and optimize global Red Hat consulting performance. Successful applicants must reside in a state where Red Hat is registered to do business.
What you will do:
Develop reports through business intelligence tooling, including, but not limited to, Tableau dashboards, focused on answering key business questions
Incorporate advanced Tableau functionality into dashboards including: parameters to change dashboard layouts, level of detail calculations, sets, dual axis charts, and dashboard actions
Present dashboards and ad hoc analyses to key stakeholders in order to increase adoption and understanding of key performance indicators (KPIs) and business drivers
Enable self-service reporting through development and training of our dashboards
Own the data quality assurance process through adoption of proper data hygiene efforts, potentially leading to “services operations-certified” data delivery
Consult with stakeholders to define standard reporting requirements, and work with Consulting Services, Services Operations, and IT to implement changes and enhancements
Work with cross-functional teams and data owners to gather data as required to enable reporting and analysis needed by key stakeholders
What you will bring:
Bachelor's degree in mathematics, statistics, marketing, business administration, or computer science
2+ years of relevant experience in data analysis, statistics, or data modeling
Recent experience using Tableau Desktop to build interactive dashboards using advanced calculated fields like level of detail calculations and parameter or set actions
Recent experience building Tableau Server data sources and publishing content to Tableau Server or Online
Experience with business intelligence, SQL, and statistical analysis tools
Good spreadsheet skills with proven experience managing large data sets and performing analysis
Good communication skills to share and present dashboards with global services teams and leadership
About Red Hat:

Red Hat is the world’s leading provider of enterprise open source software solutions, using a community-powered approach to deliver reliable and high-performing Linux, hybrid cloud, container, and Kubernetes technologies. Red Hat helps customers integrate new and existing IT applications, develop cloud-native applications, standardize on our industry-leading operating system, and automate, secure, and manage complex environments. Award-winning support, training, and consulting services make Red Hat a trusted adviser to the Fortune 500. As a strategic partner to cloud providers, system integrators, application vendors, customers, and open source communities, Red Hat can help organizations prepare for the digital future.

Comprehensive medical, dental, and vision coverage

Paid parental leave plans for all new parents
Leave benefits including disability, paid family medical leave, and paid military leave
Additional benefits including employee stock purchase plan, family planning reimbursement, tuition reimbursement, transportation expense account, employee assistance program, and more!
Note: These benefits are only applicable to full time, permanent associates at Red Hat located in the United States.

Description:
FullStack Labs is the fastest-growing software consultancy in the Americas. We help organizations like Uber, GoDaddy, MGM, Siemens, Stanford University, and the State of California, build distributed software development teams, and deliver transformational digital solutions. As an employee-first company, we focus on hiring the most talented software designers and developers in the western hemisphere, by creating a positive, respectful, and supportive work environment where they can achieve their greatest potential.

FullStack Labs is a leading software consultancy seeking a skilled Business Intelligence Analyst to join our fast-growing team. Our mission is to design and develop technology that improves the lives of its users while providing an exceptionally high level of service to our clients.
We are looking for Business Intelligence Analysts who want to be part of a fast-paced, dynamic environment, where everyone’s opinions and efforts are valued. We hire outstanding individuals and give them the opportunity to thrive in a collaborative atmosphere that values learning, growth, and hard work.
Our team of 100+ professionals is distributed across the United State and Central / South America. If you have the desire to be a part of an exciting, challenging, and rapidly-growing software development consultancy, and if you are passionate about software development and creating the finest apps in the marketplace, please apply below.
What You'll Be Doing
Your primary responsibilities will be to work with clients to analyze their data and processes so you can build dashboards to expose their KPIs.
You will provide solutions to organizational difficulties and identify areas to help improve the company’s bottom line.
You will play a major role in improving decision-making and resource optimization.
You will understand their business model and strategies, and utilize a number of data sources and analytical techniques to provide the company with insights concisely and effectively.
Experience Required
Mus have meaningful experience with Looker.

Should have experience in creating database architectures
Should have experience in developing and managing Azure SQL Data Warehouse based system
Should have sound experience in creating multidimensional cubes and Tabular models
Customer-facing with strong communication skills

3+ years experience building and administering ETL, Analysis Services, tabular, and multi-dimensional reporting models using Power BI, Tableau, SSAS, SSRS, and SSIS that are compatible with data-warehousing industry standards
3+ years experience generating reporting solutions including Power BI and Tableau
Demonstrated expertise using advanced-level calculations on data sets including the use of PowerQuery, M, R, and DAX
Excellent analytical thinking demonstrated by translating data into informative visual reports, dashboards, and KPI scorecards in Power BI and Tableau
A four-year college degree is required, with a BS/MS in Computer Science or Information Systems preferred
Familiarity with JavaScript, CSS, React Web, and other JavaScript libraries desired
Strong work ethic and the ability to focus and single-task throughout the day
Ability to work well with team members within an agile development team
Strong written and verbal communication skills
Roles & Responsibilities
Gathering detailed requirements from the Client for building cubes
Interact with Business and IT stakeholders to gather requirements for building a multi-dimensional cube
Design and develop multi-dimensional cubes and tabular models as per industry standards to satisfy business requirements
Collaborate with Business and get sign-off on the developed components
Job Duties
Connect to data sources, import data, and transform data for Business Intelligence
Implement row-level data security and application security-layer models in Power BI and Tableau
Develop responsive, intuitive, and visually stunning dashboards and reports in both Power BI and Tableau
Integrate Power BI and Tableau reports into other applications using embedded analytics like Power BI service (SaaS), API automation, and JavaScript/React Web

Walt Disney Studios (WDS) has created one of the most powerful brands by bringing memorable, life-changing storytelling to the world through incredible characters. WDS has worked to redefine the movie-making process focusing on creativity, innovation, and collaboration. At WDS, you will be part of a team that helps propel our legacy into the future with a vision as far-reaching as our stories. You will support development, maintenance and deployment of tools for teams that are bringing characters from Loki and Wandavision to Cruella and the upcoming Jungle Cruise, starring Dwayne Johnson and Emily Blunt!

We are looking for a Software Developer with a passion for learning, the aptitude for dealing with changing priorities and quick turnarounds, and a desire to help create the best tools for our pipeline and filmmaking applications. If you are an engineer interested in working across the full stack of software development and across multiple languages with all of our Studios, then this may be a great fit for you!

General Dynamics Mission Systems has an immediate opening for an Advanced Business Intelligence Developer. This position provides an opportunity to further advance the cutting-edge technology that supports some of our nation’s core defense/intelligence services and systems. General Dynamics Mission Systems employees work closely with esteemed customers to develop solutions that allow them to carry out high-stakes national security missions.
Duties and Tasks:
Work with stakeholders to define business and system requirements for new information technologies, particularly in the areas of BI, analytics, and data warehousing.
Development in a variety of tools including Power BI, T-SQL, DAX and Power Query in an MS SQL Server and Oracle database environment.
Responsibilities include requirements specification, solution design, prototype plans, developing and testing code, solution release, and supporting issue analysis and resolution
Ensure best practices are established and followed for effective dataset and report design and development.
Account for the accuracy of data presented to BI users through the execution of validation processes and testing procedures.
Analyzes and determines informational needs and elements, data relationships and attributes,proposed manipulation, data flow, data output and reporting capabilities
Designs creative prototypes according to specifications
Ensures interoperability with IT infrastructure components while ensuring compliance with wide-ranging information security requirements
Ensures application integration interoperability with other applications or subsystems (e.g. interface management, data integration systems, job automation)
Develops technical documents to accurately represent application design and code
Educate business stakeholders on intelligence reporting strategies and capabilities.
Analyze existing operations and make recommendations for the improvement and growth of the BI/EDW architecture.
Performs other duties as directed
Leads, plans, and executes projects, small initiatives
Knowledge, Skills and Abilities:
Demonstrated experience as a business intelligence developer utilizing DAX and Power Query to tell stories with data using appropriate data and visualization capabilities in Power BI Desktop
4+ years of Power BI cloud service and MS SQL Server experience.
4+ years of database development experience in Oracle or MS SQL Server environments strongly desired.
Strong technical knowledge of data management systems, dimensional modeling, data quality, data governance, analytics, and predictive modeling.
Office 365 and Azure cloud experience is a plus.
Understands business stakeholder requirements, gain a thorough understanding of their desired business outcomes, and how they translate in application features
Ability act independently on tasks and wide-ranging initiatives
Fully proficient understanding of software design and programming principles
Fully proficient of solutions development methodologies (e.g. DevOps, Agile, Software Development Lifecycle, etc.)
Demonstrated analytical thinking and problem-solving capability
A track record of high-level personal performance
Shows significant contribution within diverse teams across multiple projects or small initiatives to successfully achieve deliverables
Solid presentation skills
Clear & concise oral & written communication skills
Concise reporting to management / peers
Proven experience developing solutions to a variety of challenging problems of broader scope and complexity, using established procedures
A history that illustrates flexibility and adaptability to changing business needs and shows exposure to overcoming fundamental change obstacles
Lean-Agile mindset proficient in the understanding and becoming familiar with the Lean-Agile mindset
NOTE: This role can be supported remotely via telecommute.

An experienced Microsoft Power BI developer will build report/dashboards and have a good understanding of typical business intelligence reporting concepts and processes, such as data integration, data warehousing, data modeling, and relational databases.

Responsibilities include, but not limited to:
Developing dynamic MS Power BI reports enabling the end users to define numerous parameters that allow users to filter and aggregate as required. Also creates custom reports that allow end users to drill down for more detail.

Completing thorough unit testing of all builds prior to handoff for functional and/or integrated testing. Also facilitates functional and integrated testing as requested as well as Creates and provides documentation as required to the testing and training team.

Collaborating with IT team members on difficult tasks.

Experience building complex reports directly with MS Power BI.
MCSA in BI Reporting or BI Development.
Strong Collaboration Skills in a shared development environment.
Good understanding of Analysis Services reporting models, data warehouse concepts and terminology.
Familiarity with analytical programming languages such as T-SQL, M, DAX.
Knowledge of row-level security on data along with an understanding of application security layer models in Power BI.

The Jr BI Developer is an entry level position that is responsible for designing, developing, and unit testing scripts, reports and dashboards that rely heavily on the data visualizations to uncover trends and insight. Work with both Power BI and MicroStrategy as well as SQL, R and Python to enable business teams to meet their reporting and analytics needs.

Work iteratively with business users to continually develop, demonstrate and refine using agile methodology.

Collaborate and work iteratively with business stakeholders to develop and unit test reports and dashboards that rely heavily on data visualizations. Present ideas and actively participate in ideation/brainstorming sessions.

Build proof-of-concepts in collaboration with business teams including light data profiling, data preparation and data modeling in BI tools, and build with guidance from technical leads or supervisor.

To enable business teams, provide first-line support for ad-hoc requests in relation to answering questions on BI tool functionality, M code or DAX support, troubleshooting data issues, and building ad-hoc reports and dashboards.

Tune and maintain reports and dashboards in MicroStrategy and Power BI Desktop and scripts per defined standards.

Troubleshoot functionality and data related issues related to BI generated reports and dashboards.

BS Degree in Computer Science, Information Systems, or other related fields with specific emphasis on database design, object-oriented programming concepts, software design and development; or equivalent combination of education and experience working with report and dashboard design that rely heavily on data visualizations.

1+ years experience in an internship or entry level job related to data warehousing or BI reporting with hands-on data visualization development experience in Power BI. Includes manipulating data using M code and DAX expressions.

Understanding of the different visualization types and data visualization best practices.

Basic understanding of relational databases, data models, and concept of common datasets as it relates to Power BI. Familiarity with different data exchange types and protocols (json, xml, soap, rest) a plus.

Experience working with AWS Cloud platform tools a plus.

Ability to thrive in cross-functional matrix work environment that uses Agile methodology.

Basic understanding of the Software Development Life Cycle.

Strong analytical and critical thinking skills with ability to find resolution.

Well-balanced interpersonal skills and strong verbal and written communications skills are required.

Must be accountable and take direction from supervisor, follow work rules, and keep required work schedules, which include regular and predictable job attendance.

Must be flexible and able to work effectively in a team environment and consistently maintain a professional and respectful demeanor/attitude with co-workers, clients, and vendors.

Ability to work iteratively in a semi-structured environment where requirements and priorities are dynamic.

Must be able to interact with individuals at all levels in the organization.

Organizational skills and the ability to prioritize tasks are essential.

Self-motivated to perform with minimal support from others.

Responsible for design, development, testing,
implementation, and maintenance of enterprise analytics, reporting and data
warehousing needs. Design, innovate,
and implement solutions as needed to improve systems and processes. Assists customers in identifying
reporting/data extraction solutions to meet functional needs, streamline or
assist with operations, and ensure patient safety and confidentiality. Possesses critical thinking skills to
assess analytical needs and determine the appropriate course of action. Use of performance improvement, project
management, cost accounting, industrial engineering, and technology skills
will be employed to work with all levels of WVUHS management and medical
staff. Continuous learning of current
data base structure, tools, and extraction methods are required to confer
with customers and other members of the application teams.

MINIMUM

QUALIFICATIONS:
EDUCATION,

CERTIFICATION, AND/OR LICENSURE:
1.

Bachelors
degree in Information Technology/Computer Science, Engineering, Business
Management, Business Administration, Accounting, or Hospital Administration OR 4 years of data analytics experience required

2.

This position will require an EPIC
official designation of Proficient within the new hire probationary period.

3.

Internal employees must meet all
mandatory competencies in current position in order to qualify for promotion
within IT.

PREFERRED

QUALIFICATIONS:
EDUCATION,

CERTIFICATION, AND/OR LICENSURE:
1.

Masters degree in Information
Technology/Computer Science, Engineering, Business Management, Business
Administration, Accounting, or Hospital Administration

EXPERIENCE:
1.

Experience working with relational
data base structures including design, testing, troubleshooting problems
and/or training preferred.

2.

Experience in data analysis and/or
health care planning background preferred.

3.

Experience with reporting tools such
as Crystal Reports preferred.

4.

Experience with Structured Query
Language (SQL/Oracle) and/or Business Objects preferred

CORE DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES: The statements described here are intended to
describe the general nature of work being performed by people assigned to
this position. They are not intended
to be constructed as an all-inclusive list of all responsibilities and
duties. Other duties may be assigned.

1.

Business Requirements, Process
Analysis and Report Writing: Serves as first point of contact for enterprise
reporting and data analytic needs. Performs data analysis and creates
queries, programs and automation under direction of an experienced analyst.
Gathers requirements and prepares analysis based on information from internal
and external sources to evaluate and demonstrate program effectiveness and
efficiency. Uses basic analytical methods to ensure reported data is
meaningful and useful. Works with experienced analyst to meet with customers
to understand business process. Assumes responsibility for data integrity
among various internal groups and/or between internal and external sources.
Demonstrates knowledge of upgrades and application changes. Responsible for
development and creation of Business Objects Universes, Oracle Views, or Data
Marts to simplify the analytical process and/or allow more flexibility to our
customers to access data. Develops technical expertise in data extraction and
manipulation using various systems and tools. Utilizes reporting
tools/software such as Access, Sequel Developer, SAP Tools to create reports.
Develops and maintains technical expertise to support performance improvement
processes and technical requirements as it applies to healthcare. Attends
courses in PI activities, system design, technical training, statistical
analysis, and other appropriate health related educational courses.

2.

Operations Analysis: Analyzes
production problems, takes appropriate corrective action, and follows up on
problems to ensure resolution. Evaluates and documents operational
performance. Diagnoses and resolves issues and/or incidents for basic, most
common business systems or processes. Completes service requests for
basic, most common business systems or processes. Replaces, deletes, or
modifies code to correct errors. Notifies appropriate contact
person(s) concerning problems. Accepts on-call responsibilities and
responds with action, either by phone call/remote access or on-site.

3.

Systems Analysis and Integration:
Assists experienced analyst in system upgrades and enhancements. Completes
basic functional testing as assigned. Assists in the development of solutions
by applying knowledge of data structures and data extraction techniques.

4.

Project Coordination: Reviews,
identifies and documents any issues, barriers, or risks and brings them to
managements attention. Provides Project/Task Coordination Services to
customers as assigned. Participates in joint application and/or technical development
sessions. Appraises status, schedule variances, and outstanding issues with
team members and project managers. Manages workload and balances quality of
work with deadlines. Completes proper documentation of work tasks per policy.
Assists in controlling project costs and communicates any project-related
expenses (as assigned). Suggests ways to better accomplish assigned tasks.
Successfully meets deadlines, users expectations and project goals.
Participates in departmental and project teams as requested in a support role
and reports all relevant information and/or notes back to the rest of the
team. Manages expectations and engages management to review/resolve any
potential changes to project scope, expected deliverables, etc. Participates
in post implementation review of projects. Implement changes while adhering
to the change control policy and procedures for the project in order to
deliver a successful solution to the customer. Communicates to all parties
the natures, significance and risk factors of corresponding projects.

5.

Team
Building: Performs the following
core duties: participates in mentoring, training, and development of other
employees. Participates in training and professional development sessions.
Participates in departmental teams. Travels independently to remote sites and
communicates back to the team while working offsite (if assigned). Exhibits
objectivity and openness to the view of others, including patients/families
and customers. Offers assistance and support to co-workers. Contributes to
building positive team spirit and cohesiveness. Balances team and individual
responsibilities. Works proactively and cooperatively in group
problem-solving situations. Proactively works to resolve conflicts.
Encourages peers to seek innovative approaches to solve problems. Engages
peers/ employees in improving the quality of the work.

6.

Adheres to
the established policies of the West Virginia United Health System (WVUHS) as
well as the policies of the entity or entities where the IT team member is
assigned to work and/or employed.

7.

This
position may require travel to other West Virginia United Health System
(WVUHS) facilities or affiliated sites to assist with implementations,
training, and/or support

8.

Accepts
on-call responsibilities and responds with action, either by phone call or
on-site as defined by Department Policy.

9.

Other duties
may be assigned.

Ability to
handle and maintain confidential information.

3.

Ability to
work independently or cooperatively as a team member.

4.

Ability to
adapt to various workloads and assignments.

5.

Ability to
work with multi-disciplinary groups and facilitate meetings

6.

Must have
reading and comprehension ability.

Must be able
to type.

Possess good
oral and written communication skills.

Ability to

Business Intelligence (BI) Developer

Work You’ll do:
As a BI Developer, you will be an integral part of multidisciplinary Agile teams building high-quality data analytical solutions for Healthcare organizations across the U.S. You will create solutions which generate insights from connected data, enabling the advancement of complex decision-making capabilities for large healthcare enterprises. You will function as the data and reporting expert for specific domain areas in order to support key stakeholders across the organization. To thrive in this job, you will understand the stakeholder’s data and information needs, provide expert consultation on available tools, design options, and relevant data elements, and will provide high quality and reliable data products.
About Impact Advisors:

We deliver Best in KLAS advisory, implementation and optimization services to healthcare organizations. At Impact Advisors, we are committed to exceeding our clients’ expectations. We are a nationally recognized partner to many of the nation’s top healthcare organizations. Our commitment to patient-centered, value-driven outcomes has earned us some of the industry’s most prestigious awards. Please visit our website at www.impact-advisors.com for additional information.

About You:
Intrigued and driven by the challenge of creating information from data and skilled at organizing the presentation of quantitative information to facilitate understanding, illuminate decision making, and to “tell a story”
Intermediate to advanced/expert experience and knowledge developing complex SQL scripts as a SQL programmer
Strong hands-on working knowledge of analytical & BI tools (MS SQL Server, SAP, Tableau, Power BI) with knowledge of statistical packages as a plus
Experience documenting and analyzing clinical workflows and processes and foundational understanding of relational and dimensional data models
Ability to produce data flow diagrams which show data lineage and experience with data sourcing, data mapping, and managing metadata
Proven ability to translate business requirements into data and information deliverables using relevant business intelligence tools
Authorized to work in the U.S. and able to travel as required by client

Our People and Culture:

We believe in a caring, fun, honest and autonomous work environment and we recognize that our dedication to our associates drives our success. Our mission to create a Positive Impact fuels our associates to innovate and deliver high value services to our clients.

In healthcare, many of the greatest ideas and discoveries come from a diverse mix of minds, backgrounds and experiences, and we are committed to cultivating an inclusive work environment. Become a key competitive advantage as we capitalize on it, guiding our strategic direction. Provide expertise for the design and requirements for both executive and client facing reports, scorecards, and dashboards.
Build relationships and work cross functionally within stakeholder teams (including Data Services, Marketing, Sales and Revenue, Finance, Product, and Support teams).
Support the evaluation, analysis, and implementation of research that will drive intimate insight and knowledge of market dynamics and needs.
Field and provide support for ad hoc data analysis requests/recommendations from the Director of Strategic Insights & Analytics and others on the leadership team.
Qualifications/Requirements
3 years of experience in data analysis, design and development of reporting and business intelligence solutions in a data warehouse environment.
Minimum of 1-3 years development experience with SSRS with the following components: data sets, shared data sources, report part, report builder, and security.

Advanced knowledge of performance management solutions for BI architecture and components.Well versed in normalization/de-normalization techniques for optimum performance in relational and dimensional database environments.

SSRS Certification.UNIX/Linux command knowledge.

You will report to the Director of Business Intelligence, and will play an important role in Ping's commitment to continuously evolve primary business intelligence systems. As a BI Developer/Data Scientist you will perform a range of project activities as assigned including Data Engineering, Data Warehousing, Data Modeling, and Data Visualization. The ability to work with all levels of management, gain a quick understanding of new business process areas and technologies, and create successes out of unstructured challenges will determine your success.

You Will:

Design, develop and implement Store Procedures, Functions and other artifacts in TSQL
Design, develop and implement the ETL process using SSIS, Airflow, Python, including data quality and testing
Design, develop and implement solutions using the Microsoft BI stack (SSIS, SSAS, SSRS, SSMS) and AWS micro-services such as Python, Airflow and Lambda functions
Experience using SSMS for design of tables, views, common table expressions, foreign key constraints, and stored procedures
Data Science using R Studio and Python
Experience with Power BI, Tableau or advanced visualization software
Could Experience (AWS, Azure or GCP)
***Experience with PII and Sensitive Data required
Functional/Technical Design documents
Develop Training materials focused on end-users for multiple departments
Support the install and configuration of various MS-SQL BI infrastructure, using referenced project documentation
Work with other team members to implement solutions in a timely manner
Assist management with prioritization of projects and establishing accurate timelines for implementation
Enforce best technical practices for the BI infrastructure to enhance user experience
Coach and mentor BI team members on BI development/Data Science
Other duties and responsibilities performed as assigned., policies, tools, and partnerships expand and mature these capabilities

You Have:

6+ years of professional experience in BI or Data Science field
Experience implementing business intelligence or financial systems
2+ Years of experience working with Salesforce
Experience in all phases of Waterfall and Agile software development lifecycle methodologies
Motivated and comfortable adapting to change and competing demands
Bachelor's Degree in Computer Science, IT, Engineering, Physics, Business, or related field

Desired Qualifications:

Master's or other advanced degree in Data Science, Computer Science, Engineering, Physics, or related field
Experience mentoring more junior BI resources
Experience implementing business intelligence best practices

Job Title:
Business Intelligence Engineer - Developer
Location:
Thousand Oaks, CA
What you'll do:
The Business Intelligence and Data Engineering team at AmeriHome is the hub for all things “Data” at AmeriHome. We believe the best analytic solutions and applications depend on solid well designed data platforms that are built by asking the right questions, having a solid understanding of our business and most importantly - understanding our data. We are looking for a few dynamic and energetic individuals with fresh ideas to join our team.
What we are looking for:
What you will do:
Design, develop and maintain core databases that support the company with whole loan bulk purchases, early buyouts, and servicing operations.
Maintain and enhance reports associated with whole loan bulk purchases, early buyouts, and servicing operations.
Develop and maintain tools and analytic solutions.
Develop and maintain programs associated with communicating data between third-party providers via various protocols (e.g. SFTP, HTTPS, Email, etc.).
Design, develop and maintain generic tools that can be used in a proprietary data management platform that allows for rapid application development and implementation.
Create, maintain, and deliver ETL process.
What you will need:
Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Management Information Systems or some other technically equivalent degree plus two years of on-the-job experience in a programming related role, OR
Requires strong background in object oriented programming; C# or C++ a plus
Requires strong background in relational databases, Microsoft SQL Server a plus
Demonstrated experience in handling large datasets and relational databases
Must be able to clearly and effectively communicate with various groups and roles within the company, including the CEO.
Demonstrated in past experiences that the candidate can perform well in a fast paced environment; e.g. experience on or supporting a trading desk.
What will really catch our eye:
Mortgage industry experience preferred
Master’s degree in Computer Science, Management Information Systems or some other technically equivalent curriculum and 1+ years related experience
Benefits you’ll love:
We offer all the important things you'd want — like competitive salaries, an ownership stake in the company, medical and dental insurance, time off, a great 401k matching program, tuition assistance program, an employee volunteer program, and a wellness program. In addition, you’ll have the opportunity to bolster your business knowledge, learning the ins and outs of how successful companies operate and manage their finances, giving you invaluable hands-on experience to help grow your career!

Job Description
We are seeking a Analyst of Business Intelligence.The primary responsibility of Analyst, Business Intelligence is to (1) Provide data analysis to drive business decisions aimed at meeting departmental and organizational objectives. (2) Support the organization to make data-driven business decisions (3) Collaborate with other team members to maintain, develop, execute, and analyze targeted offers and database marketing campaigns. (4) Generate insights and testing methodologies based on consumer behavior and campaign performance. (5) Develop Business Intelligence visualizations, dashboards and solutions to optimize and automate daily, weekly and monthly delivery of reports. (6) Use state-of-the-art technologies and advanced analytics to implement predictive models and decision engines to drive email and web personalization and targeted offers. (7) Collaborate with IT to design data sources that meet reporting and analytical needs of business teams.
ESSENTIAL FUNCTIONS
Data Analysis, Reports and Dashboards: Work with business teams to review processes and develop data and reporting requirements. Develop queries and analyze data sets. Develop dashboards, reports and prepare presentations of analysis, insights, trends, metrics and results for management and senior leadership. Support business users in developing reports, tools and automation.
Database Marketing, Advanced Analytics and Automated Solutions: Develop automated solutions to collect guest and transactional data from diverse set of sources. Perform data visualization to explore trends and relationships in data. Design, develop, automate, maintain and enhance predictive models to prioritize guests for targeted offers and to personalize emails and web experience. Develop code to generate lists of scored guests for targeted offers, prioritized call lists and database marketing campaigns. Analyze campaign response rates and adjust code for future campaigns
QUALIFICATIONS
Bachelor's Degree in Information Systems, Computer Science, Business Administration, Mathematics or Statistics
2+ years of experience working in the Business Intelligence, Analytics and Data Science area or equivalent
2+ years of developer experience with a BI tool or equivalent coursework. 1+ years of experience with SQL and Databases or equivalent coursework. Experience with SAS Discover, Tableau, SAS, SSRS, Enterprise Miner, R, Python, Google Analytics, Hadoop is a plus.
Strong analytical and problem solving skills, written and verbal communication skills. Ability to clearly understand business processes, drivers and KPIs. Clear understanding of BI and Data Warehousing concepts. Clear understanding of dimensional data models and SQL, systems integration and automation

Business Requirements, Process
Analysis and Report Writing: Serves as first point of contact for enterprise

The Role: The Business Automation BI and Reporting Developer is responsible for providing data management and critical design, support, and management of key internal business applications.
Essential Duties/Principal Responsibilities:
Partner with Business Units, Global/Regional Process Owners and IT on aspects of global and local data continually evolving business processes to streamline efficiencies.
Expert in data visualization and creating analytic solutions that are user intuitive and visually appealing
Excellent in analytical thinking for translating data into informative visuals and reports
Excellent oral and written communication skills in English
Knowledgeable in enterprise business processes and data such as finance, sales, inventory, etc.
Assist team members in resolving technical and internal customer issues
Shares information cross-functionally to improve workflow processes. Interacts peers in management to share information and improve cross-departmental financial processes
Stays abreast of industry leading best practices and brings them to the attention of the leadership team for innovative application. Develops and leverages partnerships (and relationships) with internal and external stakeholders to meet business needs.
Monitor and troubleshoot critical issues and outages related to team applications
Document and develop business automation processes to optimize process efficiency
Develop an understanding of operational and financial processes and data flows at it pertains to different areas of the business.
Work closely with stakeholders to identify needs, gather detailed business requirements, and translate those requirements to technical specifications.
Develop and maintain scalable, automated dashboards and reports that satisfy the requirements of end users.
Develop and test complex SQL queries to automate business processes and integrate data from multiple ERP systems.
Partner with cross-functional leaders to ensure metrics and KPIs are thoughtfully designed to provide meaningful and actionable insights and are tracked accurately
Minimum Qualifications: Education, Experience, Skills, Abilities, License/Certification:
Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Mathematics, Statistics or Business Information Systems
2-3 years relevant work experience in a technology and/or business environment
Programming experience (SQL, Python, JavaScript preferred)
Knowledge of modern or legacy database management systems (DB2, PostgreSQL preferred)
Knowledge of business intelligence systems (Tableau, Cognos preferred)
Understanding of business processes and related software applications (MRP, ERP, CRM systems)
Strong communication and analytics skills
Process oriented and data driven
Project Management experience is a plus
Product Master, material and BOM experience is a plus

The Texas Association of Counties (TAC) is seeking a qualified person for a Sr. Business Intelligence Developer position. Primarily responsible team to support TAC’s business intelligence (BI) efforts of converting data to information and ultimately knowledge for internal and external stakeholders. Responsible for developing solutions to respond to reporting requirements including modeling of target data structures, extraction, transformation and loading of data, creating business metadata, and presentation of data to develop static and interactive reporting, dashboards, pixel-perfect and subscription-based reports as needed. Serves to establish and support a central repository in reporting and data administration within TAC.The Sr. Business Intelligence Developer will be expected to:Design data infrastructure to extract and organize data for authorized individuals to access. Identify TAC’s internal and external data sources, collaborating with department SMEs to determine their data storage and organizational needs and using the information to create and maintain data infrastructure for internal users.Contribute to the creation, maintenance and expansion of the conceptual and logical enterprise data models using modern techniques and methods for data warehousing data mart OLAP systems. Integrating new data source as required by business needs.Develop database solutions to store and retrieve TAC’s data. Support the whole data pipeline creation and successful executions: starting from row data, through structuring data and pushing it to Data Warehouse, Operational Data Store (ODS) and Dashboards. Migrate data from legacy systems to new solutions. Responsible for the entire lifecycle of extract, transform and load (ETL) pipelines creation and maintenance from the concept to PROD release including data analysis and requirement elicitation, implementing data pipelines, testing, gathering and migrating code.May serve as SQL Server Database Administrator which involves database maintenance, tuning, upgrades and problem solving.Convert business needs into data and system requirements, algin business processes with IT systems and manage the flow of data and information within TAC. Understand the logic behind the queries, with relation to the business cases. Working with key stakeholders to understand what data element is valuable for business to represented on the dashboard. Develop presentation layer objects that present data in a manner that is easily understandable to business users for report creation, with the intention of BI self-service within the current analytics package or via a connector.Develop, test and debug and migrate static and interactive reporting, dashboards, pixel-perfect and subscription-based and scheduled reporting to a production environment using appropriate change management techniques. Job Title: Business Intelligence Developer - Remote Within Footprint
Description:
Become a key competitive advantage as we capitalize on it, guiding our strategic direction. Sitting within the Strategic Insights & Analytics team, the Business Intelligence Developer will design and deliver solutions that will enhance Golf Channel Solutions reporting utilizing our internal data warehouse through various platforms (SQL, Oracle, Tableau and SSRS).

The successful candidate is an experienced Business Intelligence Developer who demonstrates in-depth knowledge and understanding of data warehousing and business intelligence and is also capable of collecting and analyzing business requirements through the lens of the development life cycle. He/she must be open-minded, flexible, and prepared to work in a very dynamic, e-commerce environment, supporting multiple business departments with operational reporting requests in a timely manner.
Bring a thorough understanding of business analytics, front-end data reporting, and business intelligence tools to drive the creation of actionable insights and recommendations to the leadership team.
Support the implementation of our Business Intelligence solutions across the business, while streamlining and automating standardized and ad hoc reporting.
Support the Strategic Insights & Analytics team and other stakeholders in evaluating, defining, standardizing, and reporting on key KPI's.
Provide expertise for the design and requirements for both executive and client facing reports, scorecards, and dashboards.
Build relationships and work cross functionally within stakeholder teams (including Data Services, Marketing, Sales and Revenue, Finance, Product, and Support teams).
Support the evaluation, analysis, and implementation of research that will drive intimate insight and knowledge of market dynamics and needs.
Field and provide support for ad hoc data analysis requests/recommendations from the Director of Strategic Insights & Analytics and others on the leadership team.
Qualifications/Requirements
3 years of experience in data analysis, design and development of reporting and business intelligence solutions in a data warehouse environment.
Minimum of 1-3 years development experience with SSRS with the following components: data sets, shared data sources, report part, report builder, and security.
Minimum of 1-3 years development experience with T-SQL scripts.Excellent analytical, interpersonal, and communication skills with clear understanding of business process flow.
Advanced knowledge of performance management solutions for BI architecture and components.Well versed in normalization/de-normalization techniques for optimum performance in relational and dimensional database environments.
Intermediate proficiency in OLAP design and development.Some experience in generating multi-dimensional cubes.
Desired Characteristics
SSRS Certification.UNIX/Linux command knowledge.

The Texas Association of Counties (TAC) is seeking a qualified person for a Sr. Business Intelligence Developer position. Primarily responsible team to support TAC’s business intelligence (BI) efforts of converting data to information and ultimately knowledge for internal and external stakeholders. Responsible for developing solutions to respond to reporting requirements including modeling of target data structures, extraction, transformation and loading of data, creating business metadata, and presentation of data to develop static and interactive reporting, dashboards, pixel-perfect and subscription-based reports as needed. Serves to establish and support a central repository in reporting and data administration within TAC.The Sr. Business Intelligence Developer will be expected to:Design data infrastructure to extract and organize data for authorized individuals to access. Identify TAC’s internal and external data sources, collaborating with department SMEs to determine their data storage and organizational needs and using the information to create and maintain data infrastructure for internal users.Contribute to the creation, maintenance and expansion of the conceptual and logical enterprise data models using modern techniques and methods for data warehousing data mart OLAP systems. Integrating new data source as required by business needs.Develop database solutions to store and retrieve TAC’s data. Support the whole data pipeline creation and successful executions: starting from row data, through structuring data and pushing it to Data Warehouse, Operational Data Store (ODS) and Dashboards. Migrate data from legacy systems to new solutions. Responsible for the entire lifecycle of extract, transform and load (ETL) pipelines creation and maintenance from the concept to PROD release including data analysis and requirement elicitation, implementing data pipelines, testing, gathering and migrating code.May serve as SQL Server Database Administrator which involves database maintenance, tuning, upgrades and problem solving.Convert business needs into data and system requirements, algin business processes with IT systems and manage the flow of data and information within TAC. Understand the logic behind the queries, with relation to the business cases. Working with key stakeholders to understand what data element is valuable for business to represented on the dashboard. Develop presentation layer objects that present data in a manner that is easily understandable to business users for report creation, with the intention of BI self-service within the current analytics package or via a connector.Develop, test and debug and migrate static and interactive reporting, dashboards, pixel-perfect and subscription-based and scheduled reporting to a production environment using appropriate change management techniques. Creates metadata and logical calculations which result in logical columns, calculated metrics, metrics, aggregated columns, hierarchies, etc. Investigates reporting issues and data anomalies with TAC source systems, with communication to end users as to specific problem and facilitate discussion with peers as needed to resolve issues.Maintains all BI platforms through installation, upgrades, patching, etc. This includes ensuring that problems with the platforms are resolved through assistance of the vendor or related parties where support agreements may exist. Maintains TAC databases, through administration and support including, but not limited to, upgrades, patching, etc.Analyzes business needs and develops requirements (alone or in collaboration with a Business Systems/Intelligence Analyst) and prepares technical specifications based on those gathered requirements. As a partner and subject matter expert to the business, establish a mindset that data functions are an integral part of existing business processes, process modifications or process implementations.Develop functional, responsive applications and UIs based on mockups, wireframes, design artifacts and technical requirements to support TAC's business needs.Perform additional job duties as assigned.Experience / Education RequirementsBachelor’s degree in computer science, management information systems, mathematics, computer and information management or related area required.A minimum of five years’ technical experience accessing enterprise data sources and developing enterprise reporting required.Experience and proficiency in insurance, government or financial industries preferred.Other Skills & AbilitiesMust demonstrate understanding of data warehouse concepts, software quality assurance testing, and the software development life cycle process.Position requires strong technical knowledge of the following tools/software applications: SQL Server Management Studio (SSMS) 2016 or greater, SQL Server Business Intelligence Development Studio (BIDS), SQL Server Integration Services (SSIS), SQL Server Reporting Services (SSRS), Visual Studio, IBM Cognos versions 11.1 and greater, and CRM.Must have strong analytical, critical thinking and problem-solving skills.Position requires the ability to work independently and manage complex workload with minimal direction from management.Position requires ability to establish strong working relationships with all teams and management.Position requires excellent communication skills, both written and verbal, and the ability to relate to persons with a variety of cultural, economic and educational backgrounds.Familiarity or exposure to/of industry frameworks such as the Capability Maturity Model Integration (CMMI), the IT Infrastructure Library (ITIL), Control Objectives for Information Technologies (COBIT), the Global Technology Audit Guide (GTAG) and/or techniques defined by the Project Management Institute (PMI) and the Institute of International Business Analysis (the IIBA).Ability to mentor and collaborate with other team members, as needed. This includes assisting and mentoring junior team members to assist with their growth.Position requires skill with research, analysis and reporting, and database management.Must demonstrate ability to understand sophisticated mathematical models and concepts, interpret financial data, and effectively present sophisticated analysis and findings.Must be proficient in use of personal computer and Microsoft Office products including Visio, Word, Excel, and PowerPoint and SharePoint.Job Type: Full-timePay: $105,000.00 - $115,000.00 per yearBenefits:Dental insuranceEmployee assistance programFlexible spending accountHealth insuranceLife insurancePaid time offParental leaveRetirement planTuition reimbursementVision insuranceSchedule:Monday to FridayAbility to commute/relocate:Austin, TX 78701: Reliably commute or planning to relocate before starting work (Required)Work Location: One location

Become a key competitive advantage as we capitalize on it, guiding our strategic direction. Sitting within the Strategic Insights & Analytics team, the Business Intelligence Developer will design and deliver solutions that will enhance Golf Channel Solutions reporting utilizing our internal data warehouse through various platforms (SQL, Oracle, Tableau and SSRS).

The successful candidate is an experienced Business Intelligence Developer who demonstrates in-depth knowledge and understanding of data warehousing and business intelligence and is also capable of collecting and analyzing business requirements through the lens of the development life cycle. He/she must be open-minded, flexible, and prepared to work in a very dynamic, e-commerce environment, supporting multiple business departments with operational reporting requests in a timely manner.
Bring a thorough understanding of business analytics, front-end data reporting, and business intelligence tools to drive the creation of actionable insights and recommendations to the leadership team.
Support the implementation of our Business Intelligence solutions across the business, while streamlining and automating standardized and ad hoc reporting.
Support the Strategic Insights & Analytics team and other stakeholders in evaluating, defining, standardizing, and reporting on key KPI's.
Provide expertise for the design and requirements for both executive and client facing reports, scorecards, and dashboards.
Build relationships and work cross functionally within stakeholder teams (including Data Services, Marketing, Sales and Revenue, Finance, Product, and Support teams).
Support the evaluation, analysis, and implementation of research that will drive intimate insight and knowledge of market dynamics and needs.
Field and provide support for ad hoc data analysis requests/recommendations from the Director of Strategic Insights & Analytics and others on the leadership team.
Qualifications/Requirements
3 years of experience in data analysis, design and development of reporting and business intelligence solutions in a data warehouse environment.
Minimum of 1-3 years development experience with SSRS with the following components: data sets, shared data sources, report part, report builder, and security.
Minimum of 1-3 years development experience with T-SQL scripts.Excellent analytical, interpersonal, and communication skills with clear understanding of business process flow.
Advanced knowledge of performance management solutions for BI architecture and components.Well versed in normalization/de-normalization techniques for optimum performance in relational and dimensional database environments.
Intermediate proficiency in OLAP design and development.Some experience in generating multi-dimensional cubes.
Desired Characteristics
SSRS Certification.UNIX/Linux command knowledge.

About Us
NBC Sports Next is where sports and technology intersect. We’re a subdivision of NBC Sports and home to all NBCUniversal digital applications in sports and technology within our three groups: Youth & Recreational Sports; Golf; and Betting, Gaming & Emerging Media.


At NBC Sports Next, we make playing sports better through innovative technology and immersive experiences for athletes, coaches, players and fans. We equip more than 30MM players, coaches, athletes, sports administrators and fans in 40 countries with more than 25 sports solution products, including SportsEngine, the largest youth sports club, league and team management platform; GolfNow, the leading online tee time marketplace and provider of golf course operations technology; GolfPass the ultimate golf membership that connects golfers to exclusive content, tee time credits, and coaching, tips; TeamUnify, swim team management services; GoMotion, sports and fitness business software solutions; and NBC Sports Edge, a leading platform for fantasy sports information and betting-focused tools.


At NBC Sports Next we’re fueled by our mission to innovate, create larger-than-life events and connect with sports fans through technology that provides the ultimate in immersive experiences.

About Celsius Network
Celsius addresses the financial needs of today’s consumers worldwide through a democratized interest income and lending platform accessible via mobile and desktop app. With a mission to put unparalleled economic freedom in the hands of the people, and a core belief that financial services should only do what is in the best interests of the community, Celsius is a modern earning and lending platform where membership provides access to curated financial services that are not available through traditional financial institutions. Crypto holders can earn yield on the digital assets in their account with Celsius, and can borrow fiat or stablecoins against their crypto collateral at the lowest interest rates in the space.


The Celsius team is committed to doing good and doing well. We believe in the power of disruption and the importance of decentralization to create a new system that acts in the best interest of everyone. Each member of our team brings something unique and innovative to the table, but the common thread that links us together is our passion for blockchain, equality, and leading the next financial revolution that changes the equation to bring power back to the people.


Position: Data Analytics Developer
Responsibilities:

Collect, analyze and structure data to develop insights about key business questions of material interest to the concerning department.
Collaborate with the concerned team to develop and set up dashboards and reports that create insight, intelligence, and forecastability.
Create reports based on both internal and external data sources as per the requirements of the concerning team.
Perform extended research projects on particular topics of interest with a particular focus on business impact and the results of key market events and business decisions.
Create data governance standards for reports and dashboards in collaboration with the data analytics team for the consumption of data across specific departments within Celsius (i.e. Compliance, Marketing, et cetera.)
Present findings from data mining in a narrative that is clear and easily digestible by various stakeholders regardless of their background in data analysis. This means clear charts, easy to understand metrics along with strong presentation skills, and ability to think on your feet to respond to questions.
Develop, deploy and maintain various pipelines for automating various dashboards for concerned departments.
Continuously work to maintain flow of data sources and increase data quality, integrity, and reliability from existing data sources.
Requirements:

2+ years of experience in data analytics, data engineering, or a related field in a high stakes environment with demonstrated history of project ownership and execution.
Interest and Passion for Celsius’ mission
Must be fluent in data analysis to filter out noise and deliver actionable insights
Excellent Python skills with aptitude in data analytics packages such as pandas, numpy, sk-learn, and others.
Excellent Tableau skills both in terms of technical competency and design aptitude.
Excellent SQL skills
Knowledge of Google APIs (Sheets, Apps Script, et cetera) along with Google Cloud console.
Knowledge and understanding of AWS Services (Lambdas, EC2, IAM)
Excellent written and verbal communication skills in a narrative story format with a business mindset.
Knowledge and experience with blockchain technology and the crypto ecosystem.
Meticulous attention to detail and resourcefulness
Strong multi-tasking skills along with ownership of a wide variety of tasks and responsibilities
Must take ownership for results and rapidly experiment and iterate to match a changing company.

Business Intelligence Developer - Remote Opportunity
 -
 (
 210004H4
 )

 Description

 Job Summary:
 KinderCare Education (KCE) is currently building out a new Business Intelligence solution, primarily utilizing Microsoft Power BI and SSRS for presentation and SQL and SSIS for the back end.
 KCE is looking for a hands-on Business Intelligence Developer (MSBI Stack), who thrives in a collaborative work environment. This role involves working across the entire BI lifecycle, from source data analysis, Extract Transform Load (ETL) development, to analysis and reporting implementation, specifically with Microsoft Power BI, SSIS, SSRS. The ideal candidate would be a self-starter, thorough in their work, and willing to quickly learn and excel in an Agile team.
 The primary responsibility of the Business Intelligence Developer is the design, programming, testing, integration and production support of the Business Intelligence Next Generation (BING) platform at KinderCare Education.

 What You’ll Do
 :
 Provide Business Intelligence solutions including datasets, analytics, dashboards, and reports to support KCE in making informed decisions that increase the bottom line through improved quality and services.
 Design, develop, deploy, and tune Power BI datasets and dataflows.
 Write and optimize DAX queries and edit/manage Power Query M formulas.
 Design, develop, and deploy SQL Server Reporting Services (SSRS) Reports preferred.
 Design, develop, and deploy ETL processes using SQL Server Integration Services (SSIS) preferred.
 Write and optimize SQL stored procedures preferred.
 Build adequate logging and traceability to ensure ability to troubleshoot issues in a production environment.
 Analyze and verify technical requirements for completeness, consistency, feasibility, and testability.
 Apply software engineering concepts and best practices to design a solution that meets operational requirements, such as scalability, maintainability, extensibility, and flexibility.
 Communicate changes, enhancements, and modifications – verbally or through written documentation to project managers, sponsors and other stakeholders.
 Will be on call once a month during off hours as part of the level 3 production support escalation pool to ensure nightly jobs are successful.

 Qualifications

 Who You Are:
 2+ years’ experience delivering Power BI solutions, including custom DAX queries and editing Power Query M formulas.
 2+ years’ experience delivering Business Intelligence solutions using SQL, SSIS, and SSRS preferred.
 Ability to problem-solve in addition to a good grasp of both the technical and business factors of Business Intelligence Solutions Delivery.
 Strong understanding of Business Intelligence / Data Warehouse concepts, methods, and tools.
 Proven experience designing, developing and deploying Enterprise Business Intelligence solutions to Production.
 Write high quality code that is robust, performant, and easy to maintain
 High Proficiency in Microsoft Business Intelligence toolset, including:
 Strong knowledge of Data Warehousing; Must have a solid understanding of star-schema data modeling
 Power BI, deep knowledge in DAX queries and Power Query M formula
 SSRS preferred
 SSIS preferred
 Able to build out automated data validation and building in adequate controls to ensure ongoing data quality

 Who We Are:
 The IT team at Kindercare creates digital experiences that help working parents stay informed on their child’s early education and so much more. Headquartered in Portland, Oregon, KinderCare operates more than 1,500 early learning centers and employs more than 32,000 team members. In 2021, KinderCare earned its fifth Gallup Exceptional Workplace Award – one of only four companies worldwide to win this award for five consecutive years. Our devoted family of education providers leads the nation in accreditation and includes KinderCare® Learning Centers, KinderCare Education at Work®, Champions® Before- and After-School Programs. We keep this team online and help parents be where their kids are, even from the office.

 KinderCare Education is an Equal Opportunity employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, national origin, age, sex, religion, disability, sexual orientation, marital status, military or veteran status, gender identity or expression, or any other basis protected by local, state, or federal law.

Job Title: Epic Business Intelligence (Clarity and Caboodle) Developer
Description: ***This is NOT a regular BI developer position. It's tied to Epic Systems Corporation applications - Clarity and Caboodle***As an experienced Epic BI (Clarity and Caboodle) developer, you will bring a strong analytical, and problem-solving background with an agile development mindset.
