Job Title: Entry Level - Associate Developer (Commercial): Front End
Description:
Introduction
As an Application Developer, you will lead IBM into the future by translating system requirements into the design and development of customized systems in an agile environment. The success of IBM is in your hands as you transform vital business needs into code and drive innovation. Your work will power IBM and its clients globally, collaborating and integrating code into enterprise systems. You will have access to the latest education, tools and technology, and a limitless career path with the world’s technology leader. Come to IBM and make a global impact!

Your Role and Responsibilities
As an Associate Developer, you’ll help design, develop, and integrate solutions using best practice technologies, tools, techniques, and products our clients demand today. You’ll work with clients, co-creating solutions to major real-world challenges by translating system requirements into the design and development of customized systems in an agile environment.

Work you could do as an Associate Developer:

IBM provides a variety of solutions to clients and our specialized teams serve these needs. As a result, the specific work and technologies vary by the team you may be joining. Below is a list of the types of work Associate Developers do.
Work in an Agile environment to understand requirements, design, code and test innovative applications, and support those applications for our highly valued customers.
Employ IBM's Design Thinking to create products that provide a great user experience along with high performance, security, quality, and stability.
Work with a variety of relational databases (SQL, Postgres, DB2, MongoDB), operating systems (Linux, Windows, iOS, Android), and modern UI frameworks (Backbone.js, AngularJS, React, Ember.js, Bootstrap, and JQuery).
Work across the entire system architecture, from backend to front end, to design, develop, and support high quality, scalable products and interfaces.
Create everything from mockups and UI components to algorithms and data structures as you deliver a viable product.
Locations:
Atlanta, GA
Cambridge, MA
Chicago, IL
Dallas, TX
Houston, TX
New York, NY
San Francisco, CA
Washington DC

Required Technical and Professional Expertise

Have flexibility to work across architecture - building both front end and backend.
Have knowledge of application and web development in HTML and CSS.
Are skilled in programming languages like Java, Ruby, Python, Javascript, HTML, CSS.
Have knowledge of modern UI frameworks such as Angular.js and React.
Work in Java to implement server-side or application logic, develop databases, and design architectures.
Have exposure to Cloud – AWS, Azure, Google Could or IBM Cloud.
Have work experience or internship in corporate development environment.
Willingness to travel up to 100% of the time.
Preferred Majors:
Computer Science, Computer Information Systems, or Computer Engineering (if demonstrated strong current language programming experience)

Preferred Technical and Professional Expertise

Have an interest in, understanding of, or experience with Design Thinking Methodology.
Have an interest in, understanding of, or experience with Agile development methodology.
Experience in following a structure methodology.
Initiative to actively seek new knowledge and improve skills.
Strong interpersonal skills with ability to collaborate and work effectively with individuals, strengthening relationships to achieve win-win solutions.
Ability to communicate complex situations clearly and simply by listening actively and conveying difficult messages in a positive manner.
A passion for innovative ideas, coupled with the ability and assimilate different points of view.
About Business UnitIBM Services is a team of business, strategy and technology consultants that design, build, and run foundational systems and services that is the backbone of the world's economy. IBM Services partners with the world's leading companies in over 170 countries to build smarter businesses by reimagining and reinventing through technology, with its outcome-focused methodologies, industry-leading portfolio and world class research and operations expertise leading to results-driven innovation and enduring excellence.
This job requires you to be fully COVID-19 vaccinated prior to your start date, where legally permissible. Proof of vaccination status will be required. If you are unable to be vaccinated due to medical, pregnancy or religious reasons, we offer accommodations in accordance with applicable law.
Your Life @ IBMAre you craving to learn more? Prepared to solve some of the world's most unique challenges? And ready to shape the future for millions of people? If so, then it's time to join us, express your individuality, unleash your curiosity and discover new possibilities.

Every IBMer, and potential ones like yourself, has a voice, carves their own path, and uses their expertise to help co-create and add to our story. Together, we have the power to make meaningful change – to alter the fabric of our clients, of society and IBM itself, to create a truly positive impact and make the world work better for everyone.

It's time to define your career.

About IBMIBM’s greatest invention is the IBMer. We believe that through the application of intelligence, reason and science, we can improve business, society and the human condition, bringing the power of an open hybrid cloud and AI strategy to life for our clients and partners around the world.Restlessly reinventing since 1911, we are not only one of the largest corporate organizations in the world, we’re also one of the biggest technology and consulting employers, with many of the Fortune 50 companies relying on the IBM Cloud to run their business. At IBM, we pride ourselves on being an early adopter of artificial intelligence, quantum computing and blockchain. Now it’s time for you to join us on our journey to being a responsible technology innovator and a force for good in the world.

Location StatementIBM offers a wide range of resources for eligible IBMers to thrive both inside and outside of work. In addition to a competitive benefits program consisting of medical and life insurance, retirement plans, and time off, eligible employees may also have access to:


12 weeks of paid parental bonding leave. Family care options are also available to support eligible employees during COVID-19.World-class training and educational resources on our personalized, AI-driven learning platform. IBM's learning culture supports your restless attitude to grow your skills and build the depth and scale of knowledge needed to achieve your career goals.Well-being programs to support mental and physical health.Financial programs that empower you to plan, save, and manage your money (including expert financial counseling, 401(k), IBM stock discount, etc.).Select educational reimbursement opportunities.Diverse and inclusive employee resource groups where you can network and connect with IBMers across the globe.Giving and volunteer programs to benefit charitable organizations and local communities.Discounts on retail products, services, and experiences.
We consider qualified applicants with criminal histories, consistent with applicable law.

IBM will not be providing visa sponsorship for this position now or in the future. Therefore, in order to be considered for this position, you must have the ability to work without a need for current or future visa sponsorship.

Being You @ IBMIBM is committed to creating a diverse environment and is proud to be an equal opportunity employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, gender, gender identity or expression, sexual orientation, national origin, genetics, pregnancy, disability, age, veteran status, or other characteristics. IBM is also committed to compliance with all fair employment practices regarding citizenship and immigration status.

The Cloud Marketing web experience team is looking for a business intelligence leader to help support the rapid growth of our portfolio of Cloud Marketing websites.
Our Team
The Global Demand Center (GDC) Cloud Marketing team has a vision to create world class websites by inspiring, educating, and supporting customers throughout their digital experience. We are a fast-paced group with a focus on getting things done, simplifying anything and everything, and having fun doing it. You will be in the middle of it all, helping to make decisions that impact customer experiences, acquisition funnels, and global web experiences.
Role Overview
This role will own and drive the transformation of our Cloud web business intelligence teams by planning, designing, operating, and managing our Business Intelligence and web analytics programs. This team is looking for an experienced professional with excellent analytical skills and strong business acumen to develop and implement BI management disciplines, tools and reporting mechanisms in a fast-paced and innovative environment with global remit. This role requires someone with strong relationship building skills who will work with stakeholders across multiple stakeholder teams.
Responsibilities
Responsibilities
Develop a deep understanding of the cloud marketing business and our needs for decision making tools using data and insights.
Partner with co-workers and our analytics counterparts in planning, prioritization, and modernization of reporting solutions focusing on scalable design, performance, security, and storytelling.
Help manage our data and reporting roadmap, looking ahead to determine upcoming needs and partner with partner analytics teams to develop a plan that would assist in meeting those needs.
Modernize the current reporting infrastructure leveraging latest and advanced features

Stay connected on leading BI products, and know about the latest capabilities, features and technology updates on the product roadmap. Come up with creative ways to incorporate relevant features in reporting solutions.
Execute user research using design thinking methodology or other relevant methodologies to determine the best user experience while designing reporting solutions
Define the metrics for measuring the success of projects, develop and present the metrics monthly/quarterly to the leadership team
Lead projects ranging from ad-hoc business analysis to driving infrastructure requirements to enable proper data collection, manipulation, and reporting.
Break through communication issues and effectively develop relationships with stakeholders at all levels of the organization.
Competencies
Adaptability: regularly scan the environment to help anticipate changes that could affect key projects and effectively change plans, goals, actions, or priorities to respond to changing situations
Collaboration: maintain a broader perspective and identify and evaluate opportunities to enhance the business through cross-group collaboration. Incorporate diverse perspectives to thoroughly address complex business issues.
Customer Focus: Gathers customer impressions of products and services and integrates this feedback into decision making. Seeks information about the underlying needs of customers.
Judgment: lead peers in scoping problems by identifying key issues, inputs, stakeholders, and outcomes. Apply a broad functional knowledge base to solve problems.
Qualifications
Required Qualifications
5+ years' experience as a business intelligence analyst (preferably in a web marketing or eCommerce setting) including hands on experience with BI tools (Adobe, SQL based, Power Pivot, Power BI, Tableau etc)
2+ years of experience as a business intelligence report author/developer (preferably using Adobe and the Microsoft BI stack)
Preferred Qualifications
Experience in working or supporting web and/or eCom organizations
Ability to translate business context and needs into self-service reporting solutions.
Excellent communication, inter-personal, and cross group collaboration skills.
High attention to detail including proven ability to manage multiple priorities simultaneously.
Self-starter with a drive to succeed in a quickly changing business environment.
Comfort with high levels of ambiguity and proven ability to have impact & influence.
Microsoft is an equal opportunity employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to age, ancestry, color, family or medical care leave, gender identity or expression, genetic information, marital status, medical condition, national origin, physical or mental disability, political affiliation, protected veteran status, race, religion, sex (including pregnancy), sexual orientation, or any other characteristic protected by applicable laws, regulations and ordinances. We also consider qualified applicants regardless of criminal histories, consistent with legal requirements. If you need assistance and/or a reasonable accommodation due to a disability during the application or the recruiting process, please send a request via the Accommodation request form.

General Statement of Duties
This position is responsible for proactively identifying opportunities for producing analysis of health outcomes, quality of care, financial analysis, population health and/or health care utilization metrics. This position is considered an expert resource for developing, designing, and creating state of the art data visualizations and standardized reporting solutions. This position creates and maintains standards for visualizations, reporting, automation and other coding assets. The core function of this position is to support actionable decision making by business end users while reducing need for ad-hoc analysis requests. This person gathers requirements from users, designs solutions, and utilizes BI software and automation skills to develop, test, and deploy reporting products. This position collaborates closely with data analysts and subject matter experts to develop high quality reusable data products.
Essential Position Functions
Lead and direct efforts for complex reporting projects such as building models, algorithms, data products, etc.; expertly manage stakeholders, cross-functional team relationships and set appropriate expectations; summarize and communicate outcomes of analysis projects.
Develop appropriate subject matter, domain expertise and serve as an expert resource.
Collaborate with other subject matter experts and data analysts to identify opportunities for building repeatable data products.
Articulate value and develop business case to obtain support from management to build proposed data products.
Contribute to development of strategies and approaches for building cohesive and reusable analytics solutions to reduce need for ad-hoc requests and to empower business users.
Lead gathering of requirements and design of solutions; provide guidance, set standards and solve problems as necessary.
Expertly utilize visualization tool such as Tableau to build visualizations compliant with design standards. Advocate and improve design standards for visualizations.
Utilize SQL skills for identifying and shaping data for developing solutions.
Utilize automation and general programming skills to automate data pipelines and handsfree operations of data products.
Build and publish customized interactive BI reports and dashboards along with data refresh scheduling using the full extent of the BI solution.
Effectively utilize features and best practices of the BI solution and visual analytics to maximize the impact and utility of visualization products
Prepare reports, graphs, tables and other summarizations that are complete, thorough and easily understood by those receiving and/or reviewing the information.
Create user and testing documentation for data products; create standards for documentation and review documentation created by others to ensure high quality and adherence to standards.
Create and maintain technical documentation such as data dictionaries, business glossaries, metric definitions and other data resources.
Provide follow-on support for end-users after training.
Effectively collaborate with other teams with-in organization to develop strong data pipelines and reusable data products.
Remain current with technology and the latest analytical methods; maintain willingness to learn new skills.
Contribute and actively participate in community of practice to improve skills and capabilities of all analysts at Health Share of Oregon.
Participate in code reviews and other activities to ensure high standard of quality is maintained.

Essential Department and Organizational Functions
Propose and implement process improvements.
Meet deadlines for completion of workload.
Maintain agreed upon work schedule.
Demonstrate cooperation and teamwork.
Provide cross-training on specific job responsibilities.
Meet identified business goals that contribute to departmental goals.
Perform other duties as assigned.

Knowledge, Skills and Abilities Required
Technical:
Expert understanding of Tableau Desktop/Creator products and SQL; ability to assist in developing best practices for Tableau
Ability to lead training sessions for other Tableau users
Strong skills in developing high quality data visualizations and assisting with development and standards to meet quality standards
Strong skills in developing data products, including the ability to make sound design decisions in developing maintainable products
Familiarity in automation of analysis tasks using general purpose programming language such as Python, PowerShell, etc.; ability to assist in developing guidelines and standards for code development
Skills in shaping data for analysis purposes
Ability to follow standards for data architecture and database design
Knowledge of agile development processes
The following is also preferred:
Knowledge of Managed Care
Knowledge of Medicaid and/or Medicare programs
Knowledge of financial matters in the health care industry
Knowledge of medical and/or pharmacy claims
Communication:
Strong communication skills, including listening, verbal, written, customer service, meeting facilitation, and presentations
Ability to clearly articulate policies, instructions, goals, and objectives.
Able to convey appropriate level of detail effectively to all levels of the organization including non-technical staff

Other:
Ability to mentor other analysts relating to technical skills and organizational information
Excellent critical thinking skills
Possess a high degree of initiative and motivation
Ability to manage multiple tasks
Ability to effectively collaborate with coworkers, staff, leaders, and executives across all departments

Skilled in deploying solutions that leverage Tableau Best Practices.

Job Title: Business Intelligence Developer - Portland or Eugene, OR
Description:
Integrates business intelligence technology with traditional institutional research to expand the design, delivery, and maintenance of information. Develop data visualizations, analyses, and reports that support decision making and planning.
Design, implement, and support business intelligence dashboards and data visualizations.
Identify data quality issues and work to resolve issues and processes as needed.
Collaborate to administer polices, standards and procedures for data analysis and modeling, and data element standardization and use to ensure accurate, useful and readily accessible data.
Develop and implement data models and validation procedures that will best meet the decision support needs of the campus.
Determine testing needed to assure the functionality and integrity of reporting solutions, create test plans, and evaluate testing results taking corrective action as necessary
Maintain reports and manage related intranet sites.
Write queries, develop reports and conduct analyses for Institutional Research.
Assist in support and training with end users; provide user assistance and direction for self-service reporting options.
Performs other job related duties as required.
EEO/AA

Qualifications
Masters and 3 years experience
Requires application of advanced principles, techniques, and theory in a professional discipline or a thorough general business management knowledge. Knowledge of this level is typically obtained through a directly job-related Master's degree or equivalent formal training in a recognized field of specialization that is directly related to the type of work being performed. Requires a minimum of three (3) years of directly job-related experience.

Preferred Skills: Knowledge and experience in data extraction and programming tools found in SQL, PHP, Python, Javascript, or R. Experience using statistical tools such as SAS, SPSS, STATA as well as data visualization tools such as Tableau or Power BI.

Experience will be considered in lieu of education.

Job Posting: Oct 28, 2021, 1:38:12 PM

The Opportunity
Investment Management is looking for an energetic individual with strong analytical skills to join the team as a Data Analyst - Business Intelligence (BI) Developer on the Investment Reporting & Communications (IR&C) team. You will be responsible for the creating, publishing, and optimizing Investment Management’s reporting and analytics, collaborating with business partners throughout the enterprise – including enterprise technology and data science.
The Team
The IR&C team is responsible for communicating the General Investment Account’s strategy, asset allocation, risk exposures, and transaction activity in support of the Chief Investment Officer’s report backs to the Investment Committee of the Board of Directors, rating agencies, and business units. The team is currently under-going a multi-year data and reporting modernization project and is actively looking for a data analyst who enjoys solving complex problems, understands business goals, and manages multiple priorities.
The Impact
This role is hands-on, developing and delivering highly intuitive analytical solutions optimizing the use of dashboards and visualization for investment portfolio reporting & analysis. You will be the subject matter expert for the current reporting application and new tools while applying existing knowledge, and teaching others.
Your responsibilities would include, but are not limited to:
Build and deploy highly interactive dashboards, reports, and other visualizations that are easy to understand, enable self-service, and provide secure and efficient access to data
Continuously improve and enhance the performance, capabilities, and functional coverage of analytics solutions
Partner with IR&C team to translate requirements into technical specifications
Extract and analyze data from investment repositories, third-party vendors, and external managers based on ad-hoc user requests
Create ETL and manage change control for dimensions and other report derivations
Conduct unit testing and troubleshooting
Manage weekly report development meetings and communications
Manage report life cycle and promotion process using Atlassian JIRA
Track investment new field requests, data quality requests and resolution, and downstream project dependencies
The Minimum Qualifications
Bachelor’s degree in Information Technology, Computer Science, CIS, Engineering, Math or related major
Minimum of 5 years BI/Analytics experience with increasing responsibilities implementing medium and large-scale projects and business intelligence solutions
At least 3 years of experience with MicroStrategy or comparable BI tool (IBM Cognos, Tableau, etc.)
Experience working with complex data structures and datasets
The Ideal Qualifications
Master’s degree Information Technology, Computer Science, CIS, Engineering, Math or related major
8 years BI/Analytics experience with increasing responsibilities implementing medium and large-scale projects and business intelligence solutions
6 years of experience with MicroStrategy or comparable BI tool (IBM Cognos, Tableau, etc.)
5 years Investment Management related experience
What to Expect as Part of MassMutual and the Team
Regular meetings with the IR&C Team
Focused one-on-one meetings with your manager
Access to mentorship opportunities
Networking opportunities including access to Asian, Hispanic/Latinx, African American, women, LGBTQ, Veteran and disability-focused Business Resource Groups
Access to learning content on Degreed and other informational platforms
Your ethics and integrity will be valued by a company with a strong and stable ethical business with industry leading pay and benefits
About MassMutual
We’ve been around since 1851. During our history, we’ve helped millions of people find financial freedom, offer financial protection, and plan for the future.

Description:

The BI Developer at radius will be part of the Business Intelligence & Analytics (BI) team. The team focuses on high-impact issues that increase radius financial group’s overall performance. The BI team is responsible for data management, data governance, business reporting & dashboards, and data & opportunity analytics, which informs strategic and tactical decisions.
The BI Developer is responsible for building and possessing deep knowledge of complex and specialized data and ensuring the high quality, accurate, and timely delivery of information. The role requires the automation and maintenance of reports and dashboards, the identification and integration of multiple data sources, and the ability to drive solutions from concept through execution.
In addition to all duties prescribed by company policies and applicable laws and regulations, Employee shall have the following additional duties (collectively, “Duties”), subject to change:
Design, build and deploy BI solutions (e.g. reporting tools).
Evaluate and improve existing BI systems.
Collaborate across the company to implement reporting and data requirements in accordance with end user’s information needs.
Design and build data management solutions focused on long-term data integrity and system health.
Determine, enforce and document database policies, procedures, and standards.
Conduct unit testing and troubleshooting.
Monitor database performance, implement changes, and apply new patches and versions when required.
Handles special assignments and projects involving independent research and developments as assigned.
Embody radius’ core values. customer-obsessed, team-inspired, results-driven, character matters, kinda curious.
. Requirements:
3 or more years of experience related to the listed responsibilities.
Degree in computer science or other quantitative disciplines with a strong academic record.
Background in data warehouse design (e.g. dimensional modeling) and data mining.
In-depth understanding of database management systems, online analytical processing (OLAP), and ETL (Extract, transform, load) framework.
Knowledge of SQL queries, relational databases (Oracle, SQL Server), SQL Server Reporting Services (SSRS), and SQL Server Integration Services (SSIS).
Experience with data visualization suites (DOMO, Power BI, Tableau) and major BI platforms.
Hands-on experience with database standards and end-user applications.
Excellent knowledge of data backup, recovery, security, and integrity.
Non-Technical Qualifications:
Highly analytical and a problem solver.
Entrepreneurial spirit and growth mindset with a positive attitude.
Familiarity with the mortgage lending industry and financial products.
Strong business and technical acumen.
Excellent communication and writing skills.
Ability to solve practical problems.

Ibotta is seeking a Senior Financial Business Intelligence Developer to join our innovative team and contribute to our mission to Make Every Purchase Rewarding.

This position is located in Denver, Colorado or with the option of full-time remote. Candidates must live in the United States.

What you will be doing:

Embrace and uphold Ibotta's Core Values: Integrity, Boldness, Ownership, Teamwork, Transparency & Advocate for Savers
Automate reporting of financial information including performance metrics and supporting special projects or analysis
Implement data driven solutions that drive action and reduce manual efforts
Partner with organizations to identify automation opportunities and take the lead on making them happen
Continually grow Ibotta's understanding of financial information
Implement best practices to improve efficiencies and data quality
Create and maintain internal documentation on tools and data sets

What we are looking for:

Technical Skills: Advanced level understanding of SQL within any of the industry leading platforms (SQL Server, Oracle, Snowflake, etc.); experience using reporting technologies such as Looker, Tableau, PowerBI or similar visualization platform
5-7+ years of experience in Data Analytics, Financial Reporting or automation
5+ years developing and maintaining ETL processes
Creative thinking problem solver who learns fast
Deep knowledge and experience in Finance and Accounting analyses
Bachelor or Master's degree in Finance, Mathematics or Business preferred
Strong communication skills, able to explain technical concepts in common terms
Ability to work independently with little guidance or oversight

About Us:

Built in Denver, CO, Ibotta ("I bought a...") is a free mobile shopping app that gives users cash back on groceries and more. Through our partnerships with brands and retailers like Procter & Gamble, Kraft Heinz, Kellogg, Amazon, Walmart, Target and Uber, we've delivered over $1B million in cumulative cash rewards to our Savers. Guided by our values and our mission to make every purchase rewarding, we come to work energized by the business problems we get to solve, the technology we get to build, and the people we get to innovate (and have fun) with. Ibotta made Inc.'s 2020 list of the 5000 fastest-growing private companies in the U.S. for the third consecutive year. In 2019, we became the first mobile consumer technology company in Colorado to achieve $1B in valuation.

Additional Details:

This position is located in Denver, CO or with the option of full-time remote and includes competitive pay, flexible time off, benefits package (including medical, dental, vision), Lifestyle Spending Account, 401k match, profit sharing and equity.
Base compensation range: $90,000 - $120,000. Total compensation for this role also includes a variable component in addition to base compensation. This compensation range is specific to the state of Colorado's local labor market and may vary for employees living in other areas.

Aderas, Inc. is seeking an Oracle Business Intelligence Enterprise Developer to support USTRANSCOM in sustaining and modernizing the Transportation Financial Management System (TFMS).

Primary Job Duties:

Work within a team environment to provide technical support for Oracle Business Intelligence Enterprise Edition (OBIEE) 12c build, located at Scott AFB, TFMS.
Familiar with change management process flows (any methodology - Agile, Sigma Six, Waterfall, etc.), and with CM software (Jira, GitLab, Serena, etc.)
Perform OBIEE source data analysis (core source system is currently Oracle EBS).
Design and implement Extract Transform and Load (ETL) processes, data feeding, cleansing, archiving, and profiling using Oracle Data Integrator (ODI) as the data movement tool.
Physical layer: Design and develop physical tables in the data warehouse.
RPD build: Design and develop logical tables and measures in the BMM layer, within star schemas, that support the OBIEE presentation layer.
Use current industry best-practices when designing Star Schemas and data modeling/data architecture concepts in the OBIEE Oracle Data warehouse environment.
Design, build, and maintain metadata solutions (hierarchies) that drive reporting.
Clear understanding of drill down in hierarchies, and how metadata dimensions in star schemas support presentation-layer reporting.
Presentation layer: assist with the design and build of dashboards, reports, graphs, maps and other presentation-layer objects, in OBIEE.
Perform design, development, and testing that meets/exceeds industry best practice standards for OBIEE.
Approach problem solving creatively and effectively with the ability to support the existing logic and fix any bug or defect issues, and the ability to re-architect or build new, using Oracle implementation experience and knowledge.
Work well as a team to provide timely and accurate resolution for OBIEE/ODI issues
Assist with creating and performing testing scenarios, for example: fail over (moving from one server environment to another), that identify performance issues, that catch any data discrepancies or irregularities, or that properly tie out financial data.
Remain abreast of industry trends, development skills/tools, and best practice standards, and be able to articulate ideas for change in a way that is constructive.

Required Education Work Experience:

Bachelor's degree in Information Technology (IT), Big Data Analytics, Finance, or a directly related field
Minimum of 5 years current experience with OBIEE 11g or 12c, and at least 1-2 years of those 5 years, being experience with version 12c.

Certification Requirements:

CompTIA Security+
Within 6 months - must complete Computing Environment Certification in Army Training and Certification Tracking System (ATCTS).
Oracle Certification in OBIEE is desired.

Clearance: U.S. Citizen, Active Secret Clearance

About the job:

The Red Hat North America (NA) Services Operations team is looking for a Reports Dashboard Developer to join us. In this role, you'll join the NA Services Operations team that is responsible for managing the tools, systems, processes, and data that make the Red Hat Consulting organization more efficient, effective, and data-driven. You’ll develop reporting dashboards which enable analysis on the performance of services deliveries across global and regional services teams. You'll also work closely with the Services Enterprise Data Analytics team, Global Services team, and other internal teams to design dashboards which are used to measure and optimize global Red Hat consulting performance. Successful applicants must reside in a state where Red Hat is registered to do business.
What you will do:
Develop reports through business intelligence tooling, including, but not limited to, Tableau dashboards, focused on answering key business questions
Incorporate advanced Tableau functionality into dashboards including: parameters to change dashboard layouts, level of detail calculations, sets, dual axis charts, and dashboard actions
Present dashboards and ad hoc analyses to key stakeholders in order to increase adoption and understanding of key performance indicators (KPIs) and business drivers
Enable self-service reporting through development and training of our dashboards
Own the data quality assurance process through adoption of proper data hygiene efforts, potentially leading to “services operations-certified” data delivery
Consult with stakeholders to define standard reporting requirements, and work with Consulting Services, Services Operations, and IT to implement changes and enhancements
Work with cross-functional teams and data owners to gather data as required to enable reporting and analysis needed by key stakeholders
What you will bring:
Bachelor's degree in mathematics, statistics, marketing, business administration, or computer science
2+ years of relevant experience in data analysis, statistics, or data modeling
Recent experience using Tableau Desktop to build interactive dashboards using advanced calculated fields like level of detail calculations and parameter or set actions
Recent experience building Tableau Server data sources and publishing content to Tableau Server or Online
Experience with business intelligence, SQL, and statistical analysis tools
Good spreadsheet skills with proven experience managing large data sets and performing analysis
Good communication skills to share and present dashboards with global services teams and leadership
About Red Hat:

Red Hat is the world’s leading provider of enterprise open source software solutions, using a community-powered approach to deliver reliable and high-performing Linux, hybrid cloud, container, and Kubernetes technologies. Red Hat helps customers integrate new and existing IT applications, develop cloud-native applications, standardize on our industry-leading operating system, and automate, secure, and manage complex environments. Award-winning support, training, and consulting services make Red Hat a trusted adviser to the Fortune 500. As a strategic partner to cloud providers, system integrators, application vendors, customers, and open source communities, Red Hat can help organizations prepare for the digital future.

Health Savings Account - high deductible medical plan
Retirement 401(k) with employer match
Paid time off and holidays
Paid parental leave plans for all new parents
Leave benefits including disability, paid family medical leave, and paid military leave
Additional benefits including employee stock purchase plan, family planning reimbursement, tuition reimbursement, transportation expense account, employee assistance program, and more!
Note: These benefits are only applicable to full time, permanent associates at Red Hat located in the United States.

The Business Intelligence Analyst works with the CIO, Director of Business Intelligence, Report developers and end users to identify, document, and translate reporting needs into written requirements. The BI Analyst will also coordinate training and promote adoption of new reports.

Cherry Creek Mortgage, LLC, NMLS #3001, has a 33-year tradition of serving the needs of home buyers across the country. With a reputation built on a passion for responsible lending and dedication to personal relationships, Cherry Creek Mortgage has helped thousands of customers realize their goal of home ownership. Cherry Creek Mortgage’s specialized internal processes and proprietary technology deliver a digital mortgage experience with a personal touch.

The Basics

Ability to create clear business rules for the BI team to translate into technical documents - identifying and defining the mission or operation, and to transform these stakeholder needs into verifiable stakeholder requirements
Train end users on reporting systems.
Participate in promoting user adoption of new reports.
Review and QA new reports with developers and end users.
Ability to analyze and identify statistical trends in data.
QA testing methods
Experience with SQL and relational data
Communication Skills
Ability to communicate through active listening
Ability to train users and promote report adoption

What You Bring

Understanding of the mortgage lending process.
Understanding of business intelligence / reporting technologies.
Ability to interview end users and document their requirements.
Ability to communicate clearly to report developers.
Understanding of report concepts such as KPIs, Data Warehouse,
Effectively conduct training, either remote or in person.

Compensation Details

$55,000 – $75,000 per year.

What We Bring

Cherry Creek Mortgage offers an extensive benefits package, including medical, dental, vision and 401k match!
Flexible paid time off policy, including 10 paid holidays.

Working Conditions
Work is performed in climate controlled indoor administrative office setting. The noise level in the work environment is usually quiet to moderate, depending upon office or meeting location. Workplace is in Greenwood Village, Colorado. May entertain remote work upon successful onboarding period.

Physical Demands
While performing the duties of this job, the employee is regularly required to communicate. The employee frequently is required to remain stationary. The employee is occasionally required to stand; walk; use hands to finger, handle, or feel; reach with hands and arms; stoop, kneel, crouch, or crawl. The employee must occasionally lift and/or move 10 pounds. Vision: Close and distance required with ability to see objects in presence of glare or bright lighting (e.g., computer screen). Speech/Hearing: Frequently interact with management, vendors, coworkers, industry constituents, clients and the public.

Description

We are a global team responsible for deploying office technology into our new construction office builds around the globe and manage major initiatives in Enterprise Engineering Operations. The office technology that we deploy includes circuits and network, audio visual and video conferencing systems, end-user IT, digital wayfinding, production events spaces, specialty demo spaces and more. We partner with teams across Enterprise Engineering to ensure we deliver technology solutions that enable employees to collaborate and work effectively.

The Business Intelligence (BI) Team is a small team. We are moving fast and have high expectations. You will be constantly challenged both intellectually and technically. We are seeking a Senior Developer who will assist a Program Manager to implement many BI programs. Other than creating dashboards and reports at various levels, the other responsibilities include every aspect in creating the data warehousing from scratch and interacting with brilliant stakeholders. We are also moving into machine learning and process mining. Come and join us if you want to learn, grow, and create a world class BI organization together.

The candidate is expected to learn our business and technical environment quickly and deliver quality products immediately. The ideal candidate will be a self-starter, versatile in many BI tools and environments, familiar with the best practices in BI, and be able to adopt fast based on the past experiences. The candidate needs to woo us with the technical know-hows, the can-do attitude, strong communication skills, teamwork, meeting SLAs, and the leadership.

Before the interviews, all candidates are expected to show their technical knowledge by achieving high scores in SQL and Python tests. All candidates are also expected to show their own BI dashboard designs, explain the reasoning behind graphs on the dashboards, provide insights gained from the dashboards, and possible improvements. No exceptions.

Responsibilities
Collect and analyze business requirements, identify metrics and KPIs with stakeholders, design prototypes, and author deliverables using Agile principles
Develop a deep understanding of business domain knowledge and BI environment. Share knowledge with BI Team and other stakeholders
Work across both internal teams and external cross-functional partners
Contribute to data warehouse data models, ETLs, and metadata management
Participate in BI tools POC when needed
Resolve production issues related to BI
Identify and resolve data integrity issues
Enforce the best practices on UX designs
Create one-time analysis
Create machine learning models
Provide both verbal and written weekly status updates to all stakeholders
Initiate BI projects when needs arise without being asked
Must Take the Tests Before Interviews
Must demonstrate the high proficiency in SQL
Must demonstrate the high proficiency in Python
Must Produce Works and Demonstrate the Following Before Interviews
At least 2 dashboards the candidate designed and created
Explain reasons for the dashboards
Explain the UX of the dashboards
Explain the graphs and the reasoning to pick the graphs
Explain the insights gained from the graphs and the dashboards
Explain possible improvements may need
Minimum Qualifications
5+ years in evaluating/designing/recommending/building of effective data visualization in Tableau and other tools
5+ years of expert knowledge in writing SQL
5+ years in data warehouse environment and using very large datasets
5+ years in designing / creating data warehouse and ETL processes
5+ years in relational DB
3+ years in Presto and Hive
3+ years in Python and/or R
Strong knowledge in data warehouse architecture

Preferred Qualifications

ThoughtFocus is a privately held IT services, software engineering and business process management firm with offices in the US, India and the Philippines. It helps clients in the financial services, manufacturing, education, aerospace and technology industries with their key business and technology challenges. ThoughtFocus brings critical program acceleration to client initiatives while minimizing costs and risks with intellectual capital, technical and process frameworks, operating models and software infrastructure.

The Updox/MDTech/AlertMD group of brands, part of the EverHealth within EverCommerce, is looking for a Senior Business Intelligence Developer to develop and implement strategic and analytic projects.
You:
Reporting to the SVP of Operations, the Senior BI Developer / Analyst will be responsible for the development and implementation of business requirements for enterprise wide, graphics-based business intelligence solutions that deliver information and enables self-service to end users. This journey will include the development of and maintenance of a data warehouse for reporting and analytics. You will have the opportunity to influence critical foundational questions as the Business Intelligence team grows.
Us:
As part of the EverHealth portfolio, Updox, AlertMD, and MDTech provide next-generation virtual care, patient engagement and office productivity solutions that enable practices to reduce costs and drive revenue. Our tools have a presence in physician offices, hospitals, ancillary care providers, surgical centers, and billing and coding companies nationwide.
EverHealth provides modern end-to-end solutions for healthcare providers. We serve 72,000 healthcare practices and counting. Our open, connected ecosystem of solutions and services helps providers engage patients, increase revenue, improve business efficiency, and remain market competitive .
Where:
Our teams are dispersed across the U.S., though the Updox office is located in the heart of Dublin, Ohio at Bridge Park. While we’d prefer someone in the Dublin, OH area, this role can be based anywhere in the United States – if you’re close to any EverCommerce office, we can set you up in-office or you can work 100% remotely. You must be eligible to work in the United States without sponsorship to qualify for this role.
Responsibilities:
You will work with all levels of the organization to turn requirements into valuable insights to both external and internal clients.
Work with business analysts, end-users and cross-functional teams to deliver value through Enterprise reporting
Build efficient Dimensional models across different domains, help enable self-service reporting platform
Administer & maintain reporting servers, perform software upgrades and maintenance
Utilize strong SQL Development experience to build efficient ad-hoc queries & stored procedures
Leveraging Matillion, you will be responsible for developing and maintaining ELT/ ETL processes from our different data sources to our data warehouse in Snowflake
Present solutions to a wide variety of technical audience and sr. leadership team
Explore new tools & technologies, make recommendations for improvements and strategic direction of Business Intelligence.
Requirements:
Bachelor's Degree in Information Systems, Computer Science or relevant work experience
5+ years of experience as a MySQL developer, Data Warehouse Developer, Data Warehouse Architect, ETL Developer
5+ years of experience with MySQL, SQL Server, AWS, Snowflake, Matillion, and Looker
5+ years of experience in a lead role designing BI solutions
Self-starter with experience in open-source environments. Someone that is resourceful and creative in their solutioning.
Experience developing database standards such as, object definition and naming, best practices, etc.
Database Administration experience desired. Experience with native database utilities for: backup, restore, reorg, export, import, performance monitoring and troubleshooting.
Good understanding of data warehouse design (Kimball and/or Inmon).
Experience with building predictive models and implementing results directly back into the product.
You will become a subject matter expert on all BI reporting systems and methodologies, as well as provide recommendations on making improvements.

Robust health and wellness benefits

Description:
The Center for Information Technology Services (CITS) has an exciting opportunity available for a Business Intelligence Report Writer for Data Analytics and Reporting. The selected candidate will be part of the newly formed data analytics and reporting office, and primarily responsible for developing reports and expanding UMB’s enterprise data, analytics, and reporting platform. This individual supports and maintains the Quantum Analytics reporting application. The selected candidate will have the opportunity to learn the Oracle Analytics Cloud platform for developing reports and analytics components. This position will support the university’s effort to document data definitions and reports using a cloud-based data documentation system (Datacookbook.com). Other duties include supporting data quality efforts to test reports and data. We are looking for a highly creative individual that is eager to learn and possesses a good work ethic.
The Report Writer will design, develop, fix, test, and assist in the implementation of functional aspects of reports. The position will receive guidance as needed to become proficient in the requisite duties. The associate developer will troubleshoot, resolve issues, and escalate complex matters to the appropriate team members.
UMB offers a comprehensive and competitive benefits package to eligible employees. This position receives an annual leave package starting with 22 accrued vacation days, 14 floating and observed holidays, 15 sick days, and 3 personal days; comprehensive health insurance and retirement options; professional learning and development opportunities; flexible schedules and teleworking options; and tuition remission for employees and their dependents at any of the Campus System of Maryland schools.
UMB requires all faculty, staff, and students to be vaccinated against COVID-19. Exemptions for medical or religious reasons will be processed through Human Resources.
Primary Duties:
Design, develop, fix, test, and assist in the implementation of functional aspects of reports.
Translate business requirements into specifications to implement reporting solutions that enable data-driven management practices.
Assist in the configuration, development, and coordination of dashboards and reports created from multiple data sources to support decision making and planning at all levels of the university.
Troubleshoot, resolve issues, and escalate complex matters to the appropriate team members.
Assist with documenting data elements, report specifications, and report implementations. Escalate complex matters to the appropriate team members.
Create and execute test plans, evaluates results and documents new features for report enhancements.
Performs other duties as assigned.
Qualifications

Education: Bachelor’s degree in Information Technology, Computer Science, Data Science, Statistics, Accounting, Business, Finance, or a related field.
Experience: Related experience working with applications and/or using data analysis including extracting, converting, and transforming data from applications is preferred.
Other: Related experience may be substituted for education.

General knowledge and understanding of SQL and database technology.
Knowledge, Skills, and Abilities:
Knowledge of position requirements. Knowledge of all applicable requirements, regulations, and laws. Skill in effective use of applicable technology/systems. Ability to effectively communicate both verbal and written thoughts, ideas, and facts. Ability to work cooperatively with others and independently. Ability to demonstrate, understand, apply, and adhere to the UMB Core Values of Respect and Integrity, Well-being and Sustainability, Equity and Justice, and Innovation and Discovery.
Hiring Range: Approximately $55,000 - $61,000, commensurate with education and experience.

Job Purpose

As a Business Intelligence Developer, you will be part of the technology team responsible for data modeling, application development, technical product assistance and tuning to meet performance and functional requirements. The ideal candidate self-motivated with a proven success managing stakeholders at all levels. The Business Intelligence Developer will play a key role in building state-of-the-art business intelligence solutions that deliver business insights and support data-driven decision making.

Responsibilities

Apply data analysis and data modelling techniques, based upon a detailed understanding of the corporate information requirements, to establish, modify or maintain data structures and their associated components.

Evaluate and gain an understanding of business requirements and translate them into business solutions - providing technical input during the planning, analysis and design phases of complex and sophisticated Business Intelligence solutions.

Manage and maintain environments (Development, UAT and Production) including installation, configuration, patching, maintenance, user management and report management.

Create proactive monitoring services to capture and report availability and performance characteristics.

Design, develop and test Business Intelligence reports, dashboards and back-end components.

Gather and document business requirements and translate business requirements into technical requirements, prototypes and end state products.

Provide time and effort estimates and lead projects of various complexities.

Document development work and provide status on progress.

Support stakeholders and business users to define data and analytic requirements.

Develop and implement various operational and sales Tableau dashboards.

Process and analyze large volumes of data, from various outputs using your findings to support the business in understanding information.

Knowledge and Experience

Bachelor’s degree in statistics, quantitative, engineering, math, science, economics, finance or a related quantitative discipline

3+ years of overall Business Intelligence technology experience in SAP Business Objects, Looker or any similar BI tool (experience should include server administration and security, reports and metadata design and development)

Job Title: Entry Level - Associate Developer (Commercial): Front End
Description:
Introduction
As an Application Developer, you will lead IBM into the future by translating system requirements into the design and development of customized systems in an agile environment. The success of IBM is in your hands as you transform vital business needs into code and drive innovation. Your work will power IBM and its clients globally, collaborating and integrating code into enterprise systems. You will have access to the latest education, tools and technology, and a limitless career path with the world’s technology leader. Come to IBM and make a global impact!

Your Role and Responsibilities
As an Associate Developer, you’ll help design, develop, and integrate solutions using best practice technologies, tools, techniques, and products our clients demand today. You’ll work with clients, co-creating solutions to major real-world challenges by translating system requirements into the design and development of customized systems in an agile environment.

Work you could do as an Associate Developer:

IBM provides a variety of solutions to clients and our specialized teams serve these needs. As a result, the specific work and technologies vary by the team you may be joining. Below is a list of the types of work Associate Developers do.
Work in an Agile environment to understand requirements, design, code and test innovative applications, and support those applications for our highly valued customers.
Employ IBM's Design Thinking to create products that provide a great user experience along with high performance, security, quality, and stability.
Work with a variety of relational databases (SQL, Postgres, DB2, MongoDB), operating systems (Linux, Windows, iOS, Android), and modern UI frameworks (Backbone.js, AngularJS, React, Ember.js, Bootstrap, and JQuery).
Work across the entire system architecture, from backend to front end, to design, develop, and support high quality, scalable products and interfaces.
Create everything from mockups and UI components to algorithms and data structures as you deliver a viable product.
Locations:
Atlanta, GA
Cambridge, MA
Chicago, IL
Dallas, TX
Houston, TX
New York, NY
San Francisco, CA
Washington DC

Required Technical and Professional Expertise

Have flexibility to work across architecture - building both front end and backend.
Have knowledge of application and web development in HTML and CSS.
Are skilled in programming languages like Java, Ruby, Python, Javascript, HTML, CSS.
Have knowledge of modern UI frameworks such as Angular.js and React.
Work in Java to implement server-side or application logic, develop databases, and design architectures.
Have exposure to Cloud – AWS, Azure, Google Could or IBM Cloud.
Have work experience or internship in corporate development environment.
Willingness to travel up to 100% of the time.
Preferred Majors:
Computer Science, Computer Information Systems, or Computer Engineering (if demonstrated strong current language programming experience)

Preferred Technical and Professional Expertise

Have an interest in, understanding of, or experience with Design Thinking Methodology.
Have an interest in, understanding of, or experience with Agile development methodology.
Experience in following a structure methodology.
Initiative to actively seek new knowledge and improve skills.
Strong interpersonal skills with ability to collaborate and work effectively with individuals, strengthening relationships to achieve win-win solutions.
Ability to communicate complex situations clearly and simply by listening actively and conveying difficult messages in a positive manner.
A passion for innovative ideas, coupled with the ability and assimilate different points of view.
About Business UnitIBM Services is a team of business, strategy and technology consultants that design, build, and run foundational systems and services that is the backbone of the world's economy. IBM Services partners with the world's leading companies in over 170 countries to build smarter businesses by reimagining and reinventing through technology, with its outcome-focused methodologies, industry-leading portfolio and world class research and operations expertise leading to results-driven innovation and enduring excellence.
This job requires you to be fully COVID-19 vaccinated prior to your start date, where legally permissible. Proof of vaccination status will be required. If you are unable to be vaccinated due to medical, pregnancy or religious reasons, we offer accommodations in accordance with applicable law.
Your Life @ IBMAre you craving to learn more? Prepared to solve some of the world's most unique challenges? And ready to shape the future for millions of people? If so, then it's time to join us, express your individuality, unleash your curiosity and discover new possibilities.

Every IBMer, and potential ones like yourself, has a voice, carves their own path, and uses their expertise to help co-create and add to our story. Together, we have the power to make meaningful change – to alter the fabric of our clients, of society and IBM itself, to create a truly positive impact and make the world work better for everyone.

It's time to define your career.

About IBMIBM’s greatest invention is the IBMer. We believe that through the application of intelligence, reason and science, we can improve business, society and the human condition, bringing the power of an open hybrid cloud and AI strategy to life for our clients and partners around the world.Restlessly reinventing since 1911, we are not only one of the largest corporate organizations in the world, we’re also one of the biggest technology and consulting employers, with many of the Fortune 50 companies relying on the IBM Cloud to run their business. At IBM, we pride ourselves on being an early adopter of artificial intelligence, quantum computing and blockchain. Now it’s time for you to join us on our journey to being a responsible technology innovator and a force for good in the world.

Dell Technologies is driven by data. Our business is built on the understanding that data creates value and drives progress. So we take the stewardship of our data very seriously. That’s the vital role played by Business Intelligence teams within Business Support. Internal clients across Dell rely on us to analyze, test, validate and maintain the integrity of data. We make use of leading-edge software and tools to collect, mine and interpret data and the statistical analyses and reports we produce inform decisions with a global impact.
Join us to do the best work of your career and make a profound social impact as a Sr. Business Intelligence Advisoron our Marketing Strategy & Operations teamlocated in Dallas, Texas, Round Rock, Texas, Atlanta, Georgia or other remote US locations.
What you’ll achieve
As a Sr. Business Intelligence Advisor you will participate in multiple programs, projects and initiatives affecting area goals and objectives. She/he will work on new practices and methodologies for working with the Dell Technologies data. They will also work with data engineers, technical project managers, developers to create new visualization tools, applications, solutions and features that support sophisticated analytics sourced from databases and other sources to enhance our customer data quality. She/he will assist in driving initiatives both internally and within cross-functional teams within Dell Technologies.
You Will:
Be instrumental in applying data quality and data lineage techniques to empower our teams to make confident data driven decisions
Develop, document, maintain and socialize guidelines around data quality/governance best practices
Be a subject matter expert to liaise within the organization and our business stakeholders to develop Key Performance Indicators (KPI's) for continuous improvements efforts surrounding data quality and governance
Understanding of how to turn insights into action related to our program business opportunities focused on people, process, technology
Take the first step towards your dream career
Every Dell Technologies team member brings something unique to the table. Here’s what we are looking for with this role:
Essential Requirements:
Advanced skills with data quality, lineage and governance tools (i.e. Enterprise Data Management Tools, Collibra, Manta, etc.)
Teradata / Greenplum Experience (SQL)
Expertise with exploratory data analysis to recognize data quality opportunities with outstanding attention to detail
Ability to solve business problems independently and in an agile team environment
Passionate about working/collaborating with teams and business stakeholders to build strong rapports
Here’s our story; now tell us yours
Dell Technologies helps organizations and individuals build a brighter digital tomorrow. Our company is made up of more than 150,000 people, located in over 180 locations around the world. We’re proud to be a diverse and inclusive team and have an endless passion for our mission to drive human progress.
What’s most important to us is that you are respected, feel like you can be yourself and have the opportunity to do the best work of your life - while still having a life. We offer excellent benefits, bonus programs, flexible work arrangements, a variety of career development opportunities, employee resource groups, and much more.
We started with computers, but we didn’t stop there. We are helping customers move into the future with multi-cloud, AI and machine learning through the most innovative technology and services portfolio for the data era. Join us and become a part of what’s next in technology, starting today.
You can also learn more about us by reading our latest Diversity and Inclusion Report and our plan to make the world a better place by 2030 here.

Description:

Questline is hiring a Data ETL/BI Developer who will be responsible for providing organization-wide support for various SQL data mining, ETL process, BI reporting and visualization needs. They will architect and maintain Questline’s BI and reporting data infrastructure, develop recurring ETL processes, conduct ad-hoc query and data mining requests, and advance Questline BI reporting and visualization capabilities. They will work closely with other Questline functional groups to answer key questions using data, SQL queries, BI tools, and statistical analysis methods.
Preferred Candidates will live in the Columbus area and be able to work a remote/hybrid schedule. Fully remote candidates will be considered.
USA work authorization is a precondition for employment. Questline does not sponsor employment visas.
ETL process management. Collaborate with internal stakeholders to identify reporting and analytics needs, design required business logic, optimize and automate the processes, and maintain documentation and change control of the processes on an ongoing basis.Data modeling and warehouse architecture. Perform the data modeling necessary to support evolving data storage and processing needs.ETL development and testing. Develop, test and maintain numerous business-critical integration and ETL processes. Build automated ETL processes using SQL Server Integration Services and T-SQL to power custom report delivery, BI reporting and ad-hoc analysis requests.BI reporting and visualization. Description

We are a global team responsible for deploying office technology into our new construction office builds around the globe and manage major initiatives in Enterprise Engineering Operations. The office technology that we deploy includes circuits and network, audio visual and video conferencing systems, end-user IT, digital wayfinding, production events spaces, specialty demo spaces and more. We partner with teams across Enterprise Engineering to ensure we deliver technology solutions that enable employees to collaborate and work effectively.

The Business Intelligence (BI) Team is a small team. We are moving fast and have high expectations. You will be constantly challenged both intellectually and technically. We are seeking a Senior Developer who will assist a Program Manager to implement many BI programs. Other than creating dashboards and reports at various levels, the other responsibilities include every aspect in creating the data warehousing from scratch and interacting with brilliant stakeholders. We are also moving into machine learning and process mining. Come and join us if you want to learn, grow, and create a world class BI organization together.

The candidate is expected to learn our business and technical environment quickly and deliver quality products immediately. The ideal candidate will be a self-starter, versatile in many BI tools and environments, familiar with the best practices in BI, and be able to adopt fast based on the past experiences. The candidate needs to woo us with the technical know-hows, the can-do attitude, strong communication skills, teamwork, meeting SLAs, and the leadership.

Before the interviews, all candidates are expected to show their technical knowledge by achieving high scores in SQL and Python tests. All candidates are also expected to show their own BI dashboard designs, explain the reasoning behind graphs on the dashboards, provide insights gained from the dashboards, and possible improvements. No exceptions.

Responsibilities
Collect and analyze business requirements, identify metrics and KPIs with stakeholders, design prototypes, and author deliverables using Agile principles
Develop a deep understanding of business domain knowledge and BI environment. Share knowledge with BI Team and other stakeholders
Work across both internal teams and external cross-functional partners
Contribute to data warehouse data models, ETLs, and metadata management
Participate in BI tools POC when needed
Resolve production issues related to BI
Identify and resolve data integrity issues
Enforce the best practices on UX designs
Create one-time analysis
Create machine learning models
Provide both verbal and written weekly status updates to all stakeholders
Initiate BI projects when needs arise without being asked
Must Take the Tests Before Interviews
Must demonstrate the high proficiency in SQL
Must demonstrate the high proficiency in Python
Must Produce Works and Demonstrate the Following Before Interviews
At least 2 dashboards the candidate designed and created
Explain reasons for the dashboards
Explain the UX of the dashboards
Explain the graphs and the reasoning to pick the graphs
Explain the insights gained from the graphs and the dashboards
Explain possible improvements may need
Minimum Qualifications
5+ years in evaluating/designing/recommending/building of effective data visualization in Tableau and other tools
5+ years of expert knowledge in writing SQL
5+ years in data warehouse environment and using very large datasets
5+ years in designing / creating data warehouse and ETL processes
5+ years in relational DB
3+ years in Presto and Hive
3+ years in Python and/or R
Strong knowledge in data warehouse architecture
Strong knowledge in statistics and machine learning
Strong time management skills
Self-starter with min supervision
Ability to deliver in a rapidly changing environment
Preferred Qualifications
Knowledge of process modeling
Knowledge of continuous improvements
Education & Certifications
Bachelor’s degree in engineering, computer science, or related fields
Master’s degree in engineering, computer science, or related fields preferred
Tableau certification(s) preferred
Who We Are:

ThoughtFocus is a privately held IT services, software engineering and business process management firm with offices in the US, India and the Philippines. It helps clients in the financial services, manufacturing, education, aerospace and technology industries with their key business and technology challenges. ThoughtFocus brings critical program acceleration to client initiatives while minimizing costs and risks with intellectual capital, technical and process frameworks, operating models and software infrastructure.
We have 1,300+ employees globally and are growing rapidly across all office locations. In the US, ThoughtFocus has facilities in California, New York, New Jersey, Wisconsin, Georgia and Texas. As an organization, ThoughtFocus strives to build lasting relationships. ThoughtFocus was founded in 2004 and continues to be an employee-owned company with a minority investment from the Blackstone Group.

Life at ThoughtFocus

Seeking a Senior SQL Developer to provide Enterprise Data Warehouse (EDW) support to the Office of Information Systems (TC) within the Drug Enforcement Administration (DEA). The DEA’s SQL Server-based EDW is used by a majority of DEA’s applications and is a critical component of statistical reporting.

Develop SQL Script and create SSIS packages for ETL work.
Be able to write SSRS reports or facilitate data access by other means as needed.

Bachelor’s degree in IT, Computer Engineering, or a related discipline.
Minimum of 8 years of experience in the design, development, and implementation of SQL Server databases creating and maintaining T-SQL Procedures, functions, packages, and triggers.
Minimum of 2 years of experience with SSIS packages for data manipulation and loading.
Minimum of 2 years of experience with the SQL Server 2012 environment.
Previous experience with Business Intelligence, Kimball Modeling and/or elastic search is desired.
Ability to obtain and maintain a DoD government secret (or higher) clearance

Agile development environment.
MS Team Foundation Server or Azure DevOps Server.
Highly skilled at SQL Script development.
Ability to create reports via SSRS; solid understanding of a variety of BI tools.
Experience with SSIS.
Knowledge of Kimball methodology desired.

Overview
The purpose of Dignity Management Services Organization (Dignity MSO) is to build a system-wide integrated physician-centric, full-service management service organization structure. We offer a menu of management and business services that will leverage economies of scale across provider types and geographies and will lead the effort in developing Dignity ’s Medicaid population care management pathways. Dignity MSO offers an outstanding Total Rewards package that integrates competitive pay with a state-of-the-art, flexible & Welfare benefits package. We also offer a 401k retirement plan with a generous employer-match. Other benefits include Paid Time Off and Sick Leave.

Job Purpose

As a Business Intelligence Developer, you will be part of the technology team responsible for data modeling, application development, technical product assistance and tuning to meet performance and functional requirements. The ideal candidate self-motivated with a proven success managing stakeholders at all levels. The Business Intelligence Developer will play a key role in building state-of-the-art business intelligence solutions that deliver business insights and support data-driven decision making.

Responsibilities

Apply data analysis and data modelling techniques, based upon a detailed understanding of the corporate information requirements, to establish, modify or maintain data structures and their associated components.

Evaluate and gain an understanding of business requirements and translate them into business solutions - providing technical input during the planning, analysis and design phases of complex and sophisticated Business Intelligence solutions.

Manage and maintain environments (Development, UAT and Production) including installation, configuration, patching, maintenance, user management and report management.

Create proactive monitoring services to capture and report availability and performance characteristics.

Design, develop and test Business Intelligence reports, dashboards and back-end components.

Gather and document business requirements and translate business requirements into technical requirements, prototypes and end state products.

Provide time and effort estimates and lead projects of various complexities.

Document development work and provide status on progress.

Support stakeholders and business users to define data and analytic requirements.

Develop and implement various operational and sales Tableau dashboards.

Process and analyze large volumes of data, from various outputs using your findings to support the business in understanding information.

Knowledge and Experience

Bachelor’s degree in statistics, quantitative, engineering, math, science, economics, finance or a related quantitative discipline

3+ years of overall Business Intelligence technology experience in SAP Business Objects, Looker or any similar BI tool (experience should include server administration and security, reports and metadata design and development)

2+ years of experience in the development of analytics solutions leveraging tools like Tableau Desktop and Tableau Online

2+ years of experience in implementing workflows using Alteryx for data preparation

1+ years of experience in Python scripting and proficiency in modules related to data analysis

Extensive experience in analyzing data using SQL, developing complex SQL queries and leveraging SQL in Tableau

Deep understanding of data governance

Deep understanding of data modeling

Advanced communication skills with the ability to summarize findings and present in a clear concise manner to peers, manager and others

Ability to actualize requirements

The purpose of Dignity Management Services Organization (Dignity MSO) is to build a system-wide integrated physician-centric, full-service management service organization structure. We offer a menu of management and business services that will leverage economies of scale across provider types and geographies and will lead the effort in developing Dignity ’s Medicaid population care management pathways. Dignity MSO is dedicated to providing quality managed care administrative and clinical services to medical groups, hospitals, plans and employers with a business objective to excel in coordinating patient care in a manner that supports containing costs while continually improving quality of care and levels of service. Dignity MSO accomplishes this by capitalizing on industry-leading technology and integrated administrative powered by local human resources that put patient care first.
What We Offer
Dignity MSO offers an outstanding Total Rewards package that integrates competitive pay with a state-of-the-art, flexible & Welfare benefits package. Our cafeteria-style benefit program gives employees the ability to choose the benefits they want from a variety of options, including medical, dental and vision plans, for the employee and their dependents, Spending Account (HSA), Life Insurance and Long Term Disability. We also offer a 401k retirement plan with a generous employer-match. Other benefits include Paid Time Off and Sick Leave.
Responsibilities

What You’ll be Responsible For in this Role – Your Contribution & Career Journey
The Business Intelligence Developer develops reports and warehouses to monitor Dignity Management Services Organization's key performance indicators and meet reporting requirements by providing the necessary to business stakeholders. This role is responsible for creating and maintaining computer-based analytics solutions to support the company's financial, clinical, and operational .
The Business Intelligence Developer III Designs, develops, tests, documents, implements and maintains warehouses and reports. Consults with current and proposed users to discuss and document requests for new and/or modified system changes, identifies design alternatives and recommends computer-based solutions.
Performing validation on the warehouse , populating cubes for online analytical processing (OLAP) as required by company analysis needs. Writing SQL statements to generate proper extracts and end users on 3rd-party OLAP tools.
Writing SQL statements to generate proper extracts. Monitors and works EDI transaction sets on a daily basis ensuring accurate and timely communication of . Prepares routine project descriptions and needs assessments for new and/or enhanced system modifications.
Benefits Include: Benefits include Medical, Dental, Vision, Paid Time Off, Holidays, Retirement Program, Disability Plans, Tuition Reimbursement, Adoption Assistance, Employee Assistance Program (EAP), Discount Programs, Life Insurance Plans, Worker Compensation, Voluntary Benefits.
Compensation Range: $37.00 to $53.00 hourly rates, annualized.
This is a remote work opportunity
