Job Title: Business Intelligence Analyst, Senior - Workforce Optimizati...
Description:
Job Summary
The Business Analyst provides analytical support through the analysis and interpretation of data in support of cross-functional business operations. Identifies opportunities for improvements and works cross-functionally to develop business solutions. Provides analytical support to projects including cost/benefit analysis and formulation of success measures prior to project launch and the calculation of ROI upon completion. Role may at times establishing project plans as it relates to data capture and storage and thus will need to coordinate on projects with internal and external resources.
Collects, validates, analyzes, and organizes data into curated data sources for use in operational, compliance and strategic analysis. Designs, develops, tests, and deploys reports/dashboards for Customer Experience leadership to assist in their decision-making process. The Business Analyst will make presentations to various levels of management to demonstrate reports, explain calculations and assumptions.
The Business Analyst is an individual contributor supporting Customer Experience reporting function which includes Compliance, Quality, Customer Feedback and Operations. The ensure reports/dashboards keep to CMS/State/Commercial specifications, are current, and validates results with the business. Provides technical expertise as it relates to Customer Experience data sources and manages relationships with business users with regards to their data needs. Provides analysis and estimates on steady state and future requests.
Responsibilities
Primary developer of our existing on prem data mart (Microsoft SQL server) and will assist in transition to HDFS data mart
Takes requirements from business leaders and translates that into hard requirements for development including ETL scripts, views, stored procedures as well as front end Tableau workbooks
Responsible for tracking, reporting, and analyzing the performance of call center activities, survey feedback, ad-hoc analytic requests, and development/automation of reports.
Develops, prepares and analyzes reports with complex analysis and data for management review, and presents to various levels of management. Defines business requirements and provides analysis to increase operational efficiency.
Analyzes external and internal customer data using database queries (SQL), and statistical analysis tools (Python, Tableau)
Identifies opportunities for improvement in operational performance and notifies management of issues and problems requiring immediate attention. Evaluates customer interaction behavior and feedback to provide insights and recommendations for further enhancements to the overall customer experience.
Works cross-functionally. Creates PowerPoint presentations to provide analytical insights for various customer experience stakeholders.
Advises other business functions as a knowledge resource for contact center data including call metrics, desktop analytics, quality monitoring and customer experience data.
Extending company’s data with third party sources of information when needed
Processing, cleansing, and verifying the integrity of data used for analysis.
Analysis of varying types of business data to determine trends, identify strategic insights and growth opportunities.
Plays a part in shaping the business’s data infrastructure, inclusive of data-warehousing, reporting, and analytics platforms.
Provide expertise on mathematical concepts for the broader analytics team and inspire adoption of advanced analytics across the organization.
Knowledge and Experience
At least 5 years of work experience in data analysis and visualization (academic equivalent will be considered) with focus on health care, call center, voice of the customer preferred.
Excellent SQL Skills including the creation, update and dropping of tables
Intermediate/advanced Python with experience Writing and maintaining ETL Jobs in Airflow preferred
Advanced/Expert Tableau Skills
Excellent analytical skills and a high degree of business acumen.
Strong organizational, communication and presentation skills.
Proven ability in handling concurrent projects with attention to detail and accuracy.
Expert working knowledge on the extraction, interpretation, and preparation of both quantitative and qualitative data.
Demonstrated ability and comfort working with ambiguous data from numerous data sources (home grown, file, database, cloud, API, etc.).
Experience building and automating management level reporting.
Proficiency in Microsoft Office Suite (Excel, PowerPoint) and database management tools (SQL Server Management Studio, Toad, DBeaver).
Bachelor’s degree (Master’s preferred) in a quantitative discipline or graduate degree.
Experience with Avaya, Verint or SSIS a plus

This is an exciting opportunity that requires a lot of interaction with internal and external business partners and building the right solutions that empower the business teams in taking better decisions. In a fast-paced environment, you will have an opportunity to work with lot of tools and technologies and will be challenged to think outside the box.

Develop a fundamental understanding of cross-functional business processes (ERP and other) to support reporting initiatives.
Create reports, dashboards, and analysis that cater to the needs of different levels of users in various business functions.

Ownership, enhancements, and maintenance of the existing reporting portfolio, schedules and documentation.
Educating & Training the user community on Business Objects and Analytics.
Collaborate with global, virtual teams, be able to work on a flexible schedule and juggle multiple priorities.
Essential Functions:
Multi-tasking: Ability to handle multiple tasks at any one time and prioritize effectively
Accuracy: Ability to ensure information, facts and figures are accurate and free from mistakes
Sense of Urgency: Ability to respond as needed within appropriate timeframe
Problem Solving: Analytical thinker with ability to solve problems and seek support/help when needed
Organization: Ability to organize effectively
Team-Player: Ability to work both within and across teams to ensure work is completed with appropriate input from others
Decision Making: Ability to make decisions on work issues that impact the successful completion of tasks
Focus: Ability to work calmly & effectively under pressure to tight deadlines
Customer Service: focused with demonstrable ‘soft skills’ and empathy with user’s issues
Delivery: Delivery focused with a commitment to get the job done
Extra Mile: Going above and beyond to exceed customer expectations
Communication Skills: Strong written & verbal communication skills

Education: Bachelor’s degree or equivalent work experience
Intermediate knowledge of SQL is desired
Working knowledge of Business Objects Suite (Webi, IDT, CMC)
Experience in Tableau, building advanced analytics and managing Tableau Online preferred
Working experience or knowledge of SAP ERP
Prior working experience with SAP HANA, and modeling is desired
Basic Knowledge on BI, reporting, data warehousing, cloud infrastructure and analytics concepts
Ability to lead cross functional meetings and assist in developing content
Working closely with users to collect and document business requirements
Documenting requirements as user stories that communicate the expectations of the business to the project team, developers, and/or vendors
Ability to quickly understand new business data and processes to detect areas of improvement

The Business Intelligence Engineer is responsible for the design, code, and testing of Business Intelligence solutions that enable data driven decision making for our associates at SECURA Insurance. This includes researching, designing, documenting, and modifying data specifications throughout the production lifecycle. We rely on our BI Engineers to be thought leaders in this space and keep up with current technologies and trends in Business Intelligence.

This position will be part of a dedicated project team focused entirely on growth in a core business area. The emphasis of this team will be to implement a new suite of insurance software to lay the groundwork for future growth. Specifically, this position will be leaned on to help execute the technical vision of this implementation.

The preferred location of this position is for our corporate office in Neenah, WI, but we will consider a remote\work from home arrangement for the right candidate.

Prepares solutions by determining and designing system specifications, establishing and following standards

Participate in the 24x7 on-call support rotation

5 years SQL Server experience in a data warehousing capacity
Applied knowledge of data modeling principles

Proficient in data discovery and visualization tools
Excellent understanding of coding methods and best practices
Basic knowledge of P&C insurance
Well-developed analytical and problem-solving skills
Ability to work in a team environment

Excellent oral and written communication skills
Ability to work under pressure to meet deadlines, yet maintain quality work

Experience with Visual Studio

Experience with Azure BI Stack

Experience with Agile processes

The Business Intelligence Engineer is responsible for the design, code, and testing of Business Intelligence solutions that enable data driven decision making for our associates at SECURA Insurance. This includes researching, designing, documenting, and modifying data specifications throughout the production lifecycle. We rely on our BI Engineers to be thought leaders in this space and keep up with current technologies and trends in Business Intelligence.

This position will be part of a dedicated project team focused entirely on growth in a core business area. The emphasis of this team will be to implement a new suite of insurance software to lay the groundwork for future growth. Specifically, this position will be leaned on to help execute the technical vision of this implementation.

The preferred location of this position is for our corporate office in Neenah, WI, but we will consider a remote\work from home arrangement for the right candidate.

DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES:

Develop, maintain and optimize current data pipeline which includes, but isn’t limited to data from our policy administration, claims, agent facing portals, and third party data assets
Develop SQL stored procedures, functions, views, tables, triggers, and ETL packages
Knowledge and understanding of best practices for development including query optimization, version control, code reviews, and technical documentation
Analyze and propose improvements to existing Data Structures and Data Movement Processes
Consistently develop and maintain BI solutions according to specifications
Documents and demonstrates solutions by developing documentation, flowcharts, layouts, diagrams, charts, code comments and clear code
Prepares solutions by determining and designing system specifications, establishing and following standards
Perform assigned project tasks in a highly interactive team environment while maintaining a productive and positive atmosphere
Provide technical leadership and mentoring to less experienced BI developers
Develops software solutions by studying information needs; conferring with users; studying systems flow, data usage, and work processes; investigating problem areas; Collaborating on solutions to those identified problem areas and following the software development lifecycle
Stay current with P&C insurance knowledge and industry technology and utilize that knowledge with existing productivity tools, standards, and procedures to contribute to the cost-effective operation of the department and company
Participate in the 24x7 on-call support rotation

ESSENTIAL:

Bachelor's degree in computer science or information systems or associates degree with equivalent experience
5 years SQL Server experience in a data warehousing capacity
Applied knowledge of data modeling principles
Advanced knowledge in SQL and other databases
Intermediate to advanced knowledge of database structure, design, and access methods
Proficient in data discovery and visualization tools
Excellent understanding of coding methods and best practices
Basic knowledge of P&C insurance
Well-developed analytical and problem-solving skills
Ability to work in a team environment
Good organization/prioritization skills
Excellent oral and written communication skills
Ability to work under pressure to meet deadlines, yet maintain quality work

Experience with Visual Studio

Experience with Azure BI Stack
Experience with XML and JSON
Experience with Agile processes
2+ years’ experience in insurance industry

Job Title: Azure Developer – Business Intelligence and Analytics
Description:
Job Description:
Azure Developer – Business Intelligence and Analytics
The Ferguson IT, Business Intelligence & Analytics team is looking to add a REMOTE Azure Developer to the Enterprise Information Management organization. The BI Developer will provide enterprise-wide data warehouse expertise with emphasis on data design, access, usage, and quality of information. The BI Developer will work in support of all managers and users requiring data for all areas of the Business.
**Position is approved to sit 100% remote. If local to the Newport News, VA area, you will have the option for in-office work out of our new HQ3 facility.**
DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES:

Develop ETL jobs to move, transform and deliver data for end user consumption.
Developer software tools to automate, improve, or change business processes and procedures.
Based on previous experience, provide input and best practice feedback for the software development life cycle methodologies, processes, and procedures
Design and implement unit testing procedures.
Analyze existing code and make updates to improve performance.
Perform detailed code reviews, with a strong emphasis on structural issues, code maintainability and performance.
Provide estimates for development work and adhere to deadlines.
Stay up to date with current technology improvements and suggest alternate solutions.
Ensures optimum service to all internal and external partners in response to all requests for service and information.
Works closely with the team and reporting officials to resolve data discrepancies as requested by management.
Data Modeling BI and Data warehousing solutions.
Assists in implanting effective business analytics practices that drive improved decision making, efficiency and performance.
Communicates with nontechnical business users to determine specific business requirements for reports and business intelligence solutions.
Processes data extracts using data retrieval and management tools.
Assists with all other duties as assigned.
QUALIFICATIONS AND REQUIREMENTS:
Experience with building, deploying, and maintaining solutions in a cloud environment (AWS, Azure and Oracle).
Experience with automation scripting in both Windows and Linux environments
Experience with Python and SQL.
Experience with PySpark or Scala in Databricks is highly desirable.
Aptitude for analyzing data and business processes.
Understanding of REST web services and architecture technologies including Flask, Javascript, XML, and JSON.
Ability to build technical designs from functional requirements.
Experience building efficient and durable ETL/ELT pipelines.
Direct experience in Oracle Enterprise Cloud Services is highly desirable.
Experience with Oracle tools preferred: BIP, OTBI and OIC.
Experience with big data technologies like Hadoop/HDFS, Hive and Spark.

RWC is looking for a Jr. Business Intelligence Analyst to join our Analytics team in the Americas. This is an exciting opportunity that requires a lot of interaction with internal and external business partners and building the right solutions that empower the business teams in taking better decisions. In a fast-paced environment, you will have an opportunity to work with lot of tools and technologies and will be challenged to think outside the box.
We are looking for a problem solver and an innovative thinker, to work alongside a lean and agile team of analysts and architects. Developing sound functional and systems knowledge, support the creation of increased business intelligence and analytics capabilities across the organization and across multiple data sources.
Position Responsibilities:
Partner with end users to understand business challenges, explore and analyze a variety of data sets to provide the right solutions.
Develop a fundamental understanding of cross-functional business processes (ERP and other) to support reporting initiatives.
Create reports, dashboards, and analysis that cater to the needs of different levels of users in various business functions.
Collaboration with the Sr. Business Intelligence Analyst, global Business Intelligence team and the Americas IT team, to help influence analytics strategy, developing requirements, and designing solutions.
Provide support to the executive team by building summaries, management reporting, and what-if analysis.
Ownership, enhancements, and maintenance of the existing reporting portfolio, schedules and documentation.
Educating & Training the user community on Business Objects and Analytics.
Collaborate with global, virtual teams, be able to work on a flexible schedule and juggle multiple priorities.
Essential Functions:
Multi-tasking: Ability to handle multiple tasks at any one time and prioritize effectively
Accuracy: Ability to ensure information, facts and figures are accurate and free from mistakes
Sense of Urgency: Ability to respond as needed within appropriate timeframe
Problem Solving: Analytical thinker with ability to solve problems and seek support/help when needed
Organization: Ability to organize effectively
Team-Player: Ability to work both within and across teams to ensure work is completed with appropriate input from others
Decision Making: Ability to make decisions on work issues that impact the successful completion of tasks
Focus: Ability to work calmly & effectively under pressure to tight deadlines
Customer Service: focused with demonstrable ‘soft skills’ and empathy with user’s issues
Delivery: Delivery focused with a commitment to get the job done
Extra Mile: Going above and beyond to exceed customer expectations
Communication Skills: Strong written & verbal communication skills
Education, Knowledge, Skills and Expertise:
Education: Bachelor’s degree or equivalent work experience
Intermediate knowledge of SQL is desired
Working knowledge of Business Objects Suite (Webi, IDT, CMC)
Experience in Tableau, building advanced analytics and managing Tableau Online preferred
Working experience or knowledge of SAP ERP
Prior working experience with SAP HANA, and modeling is desired
Basic Knowledge on BI, reporting, data warehousing, cloud infrastructure and analytics concepts
Ability to lead cross functional meetings and assist in developing content
Working closely with users to collect and document business requirements
Documenting requirements as user stories that communicate the expectations of the business to the project team, developers, and/or vendors
Ability to quickly understand new business data and processes to detect areas of improvement
Working Conditions & Physical Demands:
This position will be an in-office environment with occasional project-based travel required.
Travel requirement - 20% domestic, international trips possible
Physical demands - Job requires both sitting and standing. Excellent vision, hearing, speech, and motor skills are required to perform essential functions of the job.

Job Title: Entry Level - Associate Developer (Commercial): Front End
Description:
Introduction
As an Application Developer, you will lead IBM into the future by translating system requirements into the design and development of customized systems in an agile environment. The success of IBM is in your hands as you transform vital business needs into code and drive innovation. Your work will power IBM and its clients globally, collaborating and integrating code into enterprise systems. You will have access to the latest education, tools and technology, and a limitless career path with the world’s technology leader. Come to IBM and make a global impact!

Your Role and Responsibilities
As an Associate Developer, you’ll help design, develop, and integrate solutions using best practice technologies, tools, techniques, and products our clients demand today. You’ll work with clients, co-creating solutions to major real-world challenges by translating system requirements into the design and development of customized systems in an agile environment.

Work you could do as an Associate Developer:

IBM provides a variety of solutions to clients and our specialized teams serve these needs. As a result, the specific work and technologies vary by the team you may be joining. Below is a list of the types of work Associate Developers do.
Work in an Agile environment to understand requirements, design, code and test innovative applications, and support those applications for our highly valued customers.
Employ IBM's Design Thinking to create products that provide a great user experience along with high performance, security, quality, and stability.
Work with a variety of relational databases (SQL, Postgres, DB2, MongoDB), operating systems (Linux, Windows, iOS, Android), and modern UI frameworks (Backbone.js, AngularJS, React, Ember.js, Bootstrap, and JQuery).
Work across the entire system architecture, from backend to front end, to design, develop, and support high quality, scalable products and interfaces.
Create everything from mockups and UI components to algorithms and data structures as you deliver a viable product.
Locations:
Atlanta, GA
Cambridge, MA
Chicago, IL
Dallas, TX
Houston, TX
New York, NY
San Francisco, CA
Washington DC

Required Technical and Professional Expertise

Have flexibility to work across architecture - building both front end and backend.
Have knowledge of application and web development in HTML and CSS.
Are skilled in programming languages like Java, Ruby, Python, Javascript, HTML, CSS.
Have knowledge of modern UI frameworks such as Angular.js and React.
Work in Java to implement server-side or application logic, develop databases, and design architectures.
Have exposure to Cloud – AWS, Azure, Google Could or IBM Cloud.
Have work experience or internship in corporate development environment.
Willingness to travel up to 100% of the time.
Preferred Majors:
Computer Science, Computer Information Systems, or Computer Engineering (if demonstrated strong current language programming experience)

Preferred Technical and Professional Expertise

Have an interest in, understanding of, or experience with Design Thinking Methodology.
Have an interest in, understanding of, or experience with Agile development methodology.
Experience in following a structure methodology.
Initiative to actively seek new knowledge and improve skills.
Strong interpersonal skills with ability to collaborate and work effectively with individuals, strengthening relationships to achieve win-win solutions.
Ability to communicate complex situations clearly and simply by listening actively and conveying difficult messages in a positive manner.
A passion for innovative ideas, coupled with the ability and assimilate different points of view.
About Business UnitIBM Services is a team of business, strategy and technology consultants that design, build, and run foundational systems and services that is the backbone of the world's economy. IBM Services partners with the world's leading companies in over 170 countries to build smarter businesses by reimagining and reinventing through technology, with its outcome-focused methodologies, industry-leading portfolio and world class research and operations expertise leading to results-driven innovation and enduring excellence.

It's time to define your career.

At IBM, we pride ourselves on being an early adopter of artificial intelligence, quantum computing and blockchain. Now it’s time for you to join us on our journey to being a responsible technology innovator and a force for good in the world.

Job DescriptionCognowiz is seeking a BI Developer to join our team in support of several customers.As a BI Developer, you'll be part of an agile team dedicated to continuous improvement and innovation.You will participate in detailed technical design, development and implementation of applications using existing and emerging technology platforms.You'll have the opportunity to mentor other engineers and develop your technical knowledge and skills to keep your mind and our business on the cutting edge of technology.RESPONSIBILITIES: * Create necessary documentation for all charts and dashboards using multiple data sources* Write, interpret, and optimize complex queries working with large sets of data* Document written technical requirements and test plans* Develop and maintain tableau visualizations and reports; Develop ad-hoc Business Objects Web Intelligence Reports* Obtain data from internal systems and assist in the development of reports in Tableau for reporting as needed* Design and implement proof of concept solutions and create advanced BI visualizations* Prepare and maintain database documentation and standards; develop and maintain technical and analytical documentationSKILLS & REQUIREMENTS* BA/BS Bachelor's Degree and a minimum of four (4) years of professional experience* Experience in Creating Executive/Summary level dashboards.* Knowledge of best practices in data visualization and Business IntelligenceJob Type: Full-timeSalary: $70,000.00 per yearSchedule:8 hour shift

What are we building?

Based in Austin, we are a team of designers and developers building a better customer experience in the fast-growing online sports betting space. On the back of a Supreme Court decision in favor of allowing the legalization of mobile sports betting in the USA, states across the country have begun regulating and opening up sports betting. Since 2018, over $25 billion has been legally wagered with the vast majority from mobile devices. While sports betting is a new industry in the US, the legacy technology powering the industry is not. We’re here to change that. We’re a passionate group of sports fans who are building the future of sports betting with customer-focused products and cutting-edge technology.
What’s the position?

We are looking for a senior business intelligence engineer to join our quickly growing product and technology team. As a senior business intelligence engineer, you will be a technical leader designing solutions to inform decisions throughout the organization. The role requires an individual that’s technically talented, able to design BI systems that measure key performance indicators and convey insights to stakeholders with reporting, automation and real-time dashboards, and is passionate about sports. Because we operate with a startup mindset, we will be reliant on not only your BI skills but also your passion and ownership over all aspects of your work.
What are we looking for?

We are looking for a Sr. BI Engineer who is willing to tackle problems with innovative ideas and quality technical implementations to best communicate insights throughout the organization. We believe the perfect candidate is interested in quantifying and communicating business performance but understands how these indicators translate to our ultimate goal: delivering the best customer experience.
The ideal candidate will have:

Degree in Statistics, Mathematics, Computer Science or another quantitative field or 7+ years relevant BI experience
Strong communication skills (both written and verbal)
Extensive experience with visualization and dashboarding tools and libraries (Tableau, Power BI, Looker, D3.js)
Strong SQL skills
Other languages a plus, particularly familiarity with Python
Strong knowledge of data warehousing principles and working with data warehouses
Experience applying quantitative analytics to quantify KPIs around marketing, consumer behavior, product analytics and financial performance
Interest in ML applications to BI and augmented analytics

What’s in it for you?

We offer our employees more than just competitive compensation. Our team benefits include:

Competitive pay and benefits
Flexible vacation allowance
Flexible work from home or office hours
Startup culture backed by a secure, global brand
Opportunity to build products enjoyed by millions as part of a passionate team

Roster of Uniques
We care deeply about every interaction our customers have with us and trust and empower our staff to own and drive their experience. Our vision for our business and customers is built on fostering a diverse and inclusive work environment where regardless of background or beliefs you feel able to be authentic and bring all your talent into play. We want to celebrate you being you (we are an equal opportunities employer).

What are we building?

Based in Austin, we are a team of designers and developers building a better customer experience in the fast-growing online sports betting space. On the back of a Supreme Court decision in favor of allowing the legalization of mobile sports betting in the USA, states across the country have begun regulating and opening up sports betting. Since 2018, over $25 billion has been legally wagered with the vast majority from mobile devices. While sports betting is a new industry in the US, the legacy technology powering the industry is not. We’re here to change that. We’re a passionate group of sports fans who are building the future of sports betting with customer-focused products and cutting-edge technology.
What’s the position?

We are looking for a senior business intelligence engineer to join our quickly growing product and technology team. As a senior business intelligence engineer, you will be a technical leader designing solutions to inform decisions throughout the organization. The role requires an individual that’s technically talented, able to design BI systems that measure key performance indicators and convey insights to stakeholders with reporting, automation and real-time dashboards, and is passionate about sports. Because we operate with a startup mindset, we will be reliant on not only your BI skills but also your passion and ownership over all aspects of your work.
What are we looking for?

We are looking for a Sr. BI Engineer who is willing to tackle problems with innovative ideas and quality technical implementations to best communicate insights throughout the organization. We believe the perfect candidate is interested in quantifying and communicating business performance but understands how these indicators translate to our ultimate goal: delivering the best customer experience.
The ideal candidate will have:

Degree in Statistics, Mathematics, Computer Science or another quantitative field or 7+ years relevant BI experience
Strong communication skills (both written and verbal)
Extensive experience with visualization and dashboarding tools and libraries (Tableau, Power BI, Looker, D3.js)
Strong SQL skills
Other languages a plus, particularly familiarity with Python
Strong knowledge of data warehousing principles and working with data warehouses
Experience applying quantitative analytics to quantify KPIs around marketing, consumer behavior, product analytics and financial performance
Interest in ML applications to BI and augmented analytics

What’s in it for you?

We offer our employees more than just competitive compensation. Our team benefits include:

Competitive pay and benefits

Startup culture backed by a secure, global brand
Opportunity to build products enjoyed by millions as part of a passionate team

Our vision for our business and customers is built on fostering a diverse and inclusive work environment where regardless of background or beliefs you feel able to be authentic and bring all your talent into play. We want to celebrate you being you (we are an equal opportunities employer).

The Department of Corrections is seeking a highly motivated and qualified individual to take on the dynamic role of an IT System Administrator – Journey level - Business Intelligence Developer within our Information Technology Unit.
Please note:
Work may be performed from your home or another offsite location within the state of Washington using a reliable internet or cellular hotspot service. Our mission at the Department of Corrections (DOC) is to 'improve public safety by positively changing lives'. With a vast number of innovative sustainability programs, and evidence-based practices used to reduce recidivism, Washington State is highly regarded as a strong leader in the field of Corrections. For additional information about our agency, please visit doc.wa.gov.
The Data Warehouse Administrator (DWA) position serves as a technical specialist and works closely with customers across the Department to ensure ongoing and timely access to information needed to maintain efficient and effective operations that support the DOC mission of public safety. This position works directly with stakeholders to gather data requirements, business requirements, develops data structures and populates data structures. In performing these functions, the DWA works with IT groups in testing, validating, deploying, and maintaining the data structures. The DWA is responsible for data modeling and database design for the data warehouse and cube environments, performing data migration and conducting data analysis to ensure quality data. The DWA ensures access to current, timely data by staff across the Department, supports the data needed to respond to external inquiries around DOC population, programs, services, and budget and contributes directly to the Department’s mission of improving public safety.
To begin the online Application Process:
Click the green 'Apply' button located at the top right corner of this the job posting. Sign in or create an account.
 The following must be attached to your completed application.

Click "Accept & Submit" to submit your application.

Incomplete application packages may disqualify you from the process.

Duties

Designs, develops, and maintains the BI data infrastructure to support business needs consistently and reliably

Other duties as required

Four (4) years of experience in BI Solutions development using Microsoft SQL Server Services (ETL, SSAS, SSIS, and DB) with developed and proven troubleshooting skills.
Two (2) years of working directly performing Database Administration on production Microsoft SQL Database Server.
Two (2) years of hands-on experience with database design, dimensional modeling, data warehouse and BI/analytic tools.
Two (2) years of hands-on experience using relational data architecture and reporting tools to design and develop data structures to meet agency’s specification.
Experience with BI tools such as Microsoft SQL Server and OLAP cube.
Proficient in SQL – Query development and performance improvements.
Proficient in ETL and data integration.

 Experience with Agile, Scrum, Iterative, or Waterfall development/project
 methodologies.

Overview

Texas Oncology requires employees to be fully vaccinated for COVID-19 as defined by the CDC, subject to applicable, verified accommodation requests.

Texas Oncology is looking for a Remote Business Intelligence Developer (Senior Engineer) to join our team! This position is remote but will support for our Texas Operations. Texas Oncology is the largest community oncology provider in the country and has approximately 600+ providers in 220+ sites across Texas and southeastern Oklahoma. Our founders pioneered community-based cancer care because they believed in making the best available cancer care accessible to all communities, allowing people to fight cancer at home with the critical support of family and friends nearby. Our mission is still the same today-at Texas Oncology, we use leading-edge technology and research to deliver high-quality, high-touch, evidence-based cancer care to help our patients achieve "More breakthroughs. More victories." ® in their fight against cancer. Today, Texas Oncology treats half of all Texans diagnosed with cancer on an annual basis.

Why work for us?
Come join our team that is responsible for helping lead Texas Oncology in treating more patients diagnosed with cancer than any other provider in Texas. We offer our employees a competitive benefits package that includes Medical, Dental, Vision, Life Insurance, Short-term and Long-term disability coverage, a generous PTO program, a 401k plan that comes with a company match, a Wellness program that rewards you practicing a healthy lifestyle, and lots of other great perks such as Tuition Reimbursement, an Employee Assistance program, and discounts on some of your favorite retailers.

What does the Remote Business Intelligence Developer (Senior Engineer) do?
Under minimal supervision, implements, maintains, and resolves problems with the company's Business Applications. Masters the company's suite of information technologies to enhance business processes, and communications and develops close relationships with users to ensure consistent customer service. Applies information technologies in the timely design, implementation, and installation of high-quality business solutions for the company. Supports and adheres to the US Oncology Compliance Program, to include the Code of Ethics and Business Standards.

Responsibilities


The essential duties and responsibilities:

Build data warehouse for the organization's internal departments utilizing various data warehousing techniques.
Create and improve data solutions that allow for smooth data delivery, and oversees gathering, processing, maintaining, and analyzing huge amounts of data.
Lead the design of the logical data model, as well as the implementation of the physical database structure and the construction and implementation of operational data stores and data marts.
Design, automate and support sophisticated applications for data extraction, transformation, and loading.
Consults with data management teams to get a big-image idea of the data storage needs of the company.
Presents warehousing options to the company based on the storage needs.
Designs and codes the data warehousing system to desired specifications of the company.

Qualifications


The ideal candidate for the Remote Business Intelligence Developer (Senior Engineer) will have the following background and experience:

Bachelor's degree or equivalent experience in Information Technology or Computer Science.
Advanced knowledge of coding languages SQL, XML, API and Java.
Working knowledge of clinical data.
Proficient in warehousing architecture techniques such as EDW, DM, ODS, ROLAP, and MOLAP.
Ability to handle complex clinical data structures.
Ability to analyze and solution the big-picture data needs of a company.
Ability to troubleshoot and solve complex technical problems.
Thorough attention to detail.
Ability to deliver under pressure.

What are we building?

Based in Austin, we are a team of designers and developers building a better customer experience in the fast-growing online sports betting space. On the back of a Supreme Court decision in favor of allowing the legalization of mobile sports betting in the USA, states across the country have begun regulating and opening up sports betting. Since 2018, over $25 billion has been legally wagered with the vast majority from mobile devices. While sports betting is a new industry in the US, the legacy technology powering the industry is not. We’re here to change that. We’re a passionate group of sports fans who are building the future of sports betting with customer-focused products and cutting-edge technology.
What’s the position?

We are looking for a senior business intelligence engineer to join our quickly growing product and technology team. As a senior business intelligence engineer, you will be a technical leader designing solutions to inform decisions throughout the organization. The role requires an individual that’s technically talented, able to design BI systems that measure key performance indicators and convey insights to stakeholders with reporting, automation and real-time dashboards, and is passionate about sports. Because we operate with a startup mindset, we will be reliant on not only your BI skills but also your passion and ownership over all aspects of your work.
What are we looking for?

We are looking for a Sr. BI Engineer who is willing to tackle problems with innovative ideas and quality technical implementations to best communicate insights throughout the organization. We believe the perfect candidate is interested in quantifying and communicating business performance but understands how these indicators translate to our ultimate goal: delivering the best customer experience.
The ideal candidate will have:

Degree in Statistics, Mathematics, Computer Science or another quantitative field or 7+ years relevant BI experience
Strong communication skills (both written and verbal)
Extensive experience with visualization and dashboarding tools and libraries (Tableau, Power BI, Looker, D3.js)
Strong SQL skills
Other languages a plus, particularly familiarity with Python
Strong knowledge of data warehousing principles and working with data warehouses
Experience applying quantitative analytics to quantify KPIs around marketing, consumer behavior, product analytics and financial performance
Interest in ML applications to BI and augmented analytics

Competitive pay and benefits
Flexible vacation allowance
Flexible work from home or office hours
Startup culture backed by a secure, global brand
Opportunity to build products enjoyed by millions as part of a passionate team

We care deeply about every interaction our customers have with us and trust and empower our staff to own and drive their experience. Our vision for our business and customers is built on fostering a diverse and inclusive work environment where regardless of background or beliefs you feel able to be authentic and bring all your talent into play. We want to celebrate you being you (we are an equal opportunities employer).

What Advanced Analytics contributes
Advanced Analytics is responsible for applying quantitative methodologies, techniques and tools to develop best in class analytic solutions that solve complex business problems.
Works with stakeholders to identify business opportunities, goals, or objectives.
Determines if objectives can be met using an analytical approach and develops hypothesis.
Identifies key data requirements and acquires data.
Harmonizes, rescales, and cleans data for statistical techniques.
Applies data visualization techniques to evaluate data for model specification etc.
Builds custom quantitative models by applying advanced statistical methods such as causal and predictive modeling, forecasting, data mining, simulation, and/or optimization.
Demonstrates the ability to perform validation and testing of models to ensure adequacy and determines need for reformulation.
Interprets results of quantitative models, identifies trends, and issues, and develops alternatives to support business objectives.
Demonstrates ability to communicate complex information clearly and concisely to a variety of audiences and mediums.
Partners with stakeholders and technologist to implement/automate/operationalize models into day-to-day business decision making.

augmented Intelligence (augIntel) builds automation, analytics and artificial intelligence solutions that drive success by creating material savings, efficiencies, and revenue growth opportunities. The team drives business innovation by leveraging emerging technologies and turning them into differentiating business capabilities.
Job Overview
Designing, building and operationalizing visualization and user interface (UI) solutions (department, business unit, and enterprise level) leveraging data sourced from Google Cloud Platform and AtScale to transform high volume. highly complex data into actionable insights. Designing and implementing data visualization and user interfaces leveraging tools that connect to GCP cloud tools and services as well as AtScale
Designing and building visualizations in conjunction with machine learning algorithms (process and outputs) and providing visibility to next best actions to take
Working with both business users and developers, draft visualization requirements and provide innovative ideas that are well beyond reporting “what happened?”

Re-engineering business logic imbedded in existing visualizations that need to be integrated into GCP data stores to enable sharing across other business functions

Description:
Job Summary
The Business Analyst provides analytical support through the analysis and interpretation of data in support of cross-functional business operations. Identifies opportunities for improvements and works cross-functionally to develop business solutions. Provides analytical support to projects including cost/benefit analysis and formulation of success measures prior to project launch and the calculation of ROI upon completion. Role may at times establishing project plans as it relates to data capture and storage and thus will need to coordinate on projects with internal and external resources.
Collects, validates, analyzes, and organizes data into curated data sources for use in operational, compliance and strategic analysis. Designs, develops, tests, and deploys reports/dashboards for Customer Experience leadership to assist in their decision-making process. The Business Analyst will make presentations to various levels of management to demonstrate reports, explain calculations and assumptions.
The Business Analyst is an individual contributor supporting Customer Experience reporting function which includes Compliance, Quality, Customer Feedback and Operations. The ensure reports/dashboards keep to CMS/State/Commercial specifications, are current, and validates results with the business. Provides technical expertise as it relates to Customer Experience data sources and manages relationships with business users with regards to their data needs. Provides analysis and estimates on steady state and future requests.
Responsibilities
Primary developer of our existing on prem data mart (Microsoft SQL server) and will assist in transition to HDFS data mart
Takes requirements from business leaders and translates that into hard requirements for development including ETL scripts, views, stored procedures as well as front end Tableau workbooks
Responsible for tracking, reporting, and analyzing the performance of call center activities, survey feedback, ad-hoc analytic requests, and development/automation of reports.
Develops, prepares and analyzes reports with complex analysis and data for management review, and presents to various levels of management. Defines business requirements and provides analysis to increase operational efficiency.
Analyzes external and internal customer data using database queries (SQL), and statistical analysis tools (Python, Tableau)
Identifies opportunities for improvement in operational performance and notifies management of issues and problems requiring immediate attention. Evaluates customer interaction behavior and feedback to provide insights and recommendations for further enhancements to the overall customer experience.
Works cross-functionally. Creates PowerPoint presentations to provide analytical insights for various customer experience stakeholders.
Advises other business functions as a knowledge resource for contact center data including call metrics, desktop analytics, quality monitoring and customer experience data.
Extending company’s data with third party sources of information when needed
Processing, cleansing, and verifying the integrity of data used for analysis.
Analysis of varying types of business data to determine trends, identify strategic insights and growth opportunities.
Plays a part in shaping the business’s data infrastructure, inclusive of data-warehousing, reporting, and analytics platforms.
Provide expertise on mathematical concepts for the broader analytics team and inspire adoption of advanced analytics across the organization.
Knowledge and Experience
At least 5 years of work experience in data analysis and visualization (academic equivalent will be considered) with focus on health care, call center, voice of the customer preferred.
Excellent SQL Skills including the creation, update and dropping of tables
Intermediate/advanced Python with experience Writing and maintaining ETL Jobs in Airflow preferred
Advanced/Expert Tableau Skills
Excellent analytical skills and a high degree of business acumen.
Strong organizational, communication and presentation skills.
Proven ability in handling concurrent projects with attention to detail and accuracy.
Expert working knowledge on the extraction, interpretation, and preparation of both quantitative and qualitative data.

Bachelor’s degree (Master’s preferred) in a quantitative discipline or graduate degree.

Quisitive (TSXV: QUIS) is a premier, global Microsoft partner that harnesses the Microsoft platform and complementary technologies, including custom solutions and first-party offerings, to generate transformational impact for enterprise customers. Our Cloud Solutions business focuses on helping enterprises move, operate, and innovate in the three Microsoft clouds. Centering on our LedgerPay product suite, our Payments Solutions business leverages the Microsoft Azure cloud to transform the payment processing industry into an entirely new source of customer engagement and consumer value.

Quisitive is comprised of expert leaders in technology who use cloud-based solutions to drive business value. With a long history and incredible depth of knowledge in Microsoft products, as well as a commitment to continual learning and achievement of advanced specializations, Quisitive provides the highest quality technical expertise to achieve our customers’ goals.

Our Cloud Solutions business encompasses infrastructure, data and analytics, digital workplace, application development, and business applications services that apply the benefits of technology to empower enterprise customers. As a complement to our Cloud Solutions services, Quisitive also develops complete first-party business applications, including emPerform, to better serve our customers and their business goals.

Quisitive’s Payments Solutions business provides payment processing services to both merchants and ISOs. Our flagship product platform LedgerPay is a cloud-based data insights and Payments Intelligence suite that turns everyday transaction data into customer loyalty for merchants.

A quickly growing and evolving organization, Quisitive has made four corporate acquisitions, CRG, Menlo Technologies, Mazik Global and BankCard USA, in the past two years and will continue to add companies with capabilities that allow us to stay a step ahead and best serve our customers in their quest for innovation. Quisitive serves clients globally from nine employee hubs across the world. For more information, visit www.quisitive.com and follow @BeQuisitive.

The Business Analyst 2, GPS (Global People Services) serves as a primary interface between our between our COE and Regional customers and the solution leads (platform developers). Serves as an internal consultant and change agent for assigned HR digital platforms to manage project demand, refine requirements with requestors, balance request priority, set delivery timing expectations, and schedule run the business platform maintenance with our Nissan Digital counterparts. This position easily transitions between technical discussions with developers and business language for requestors to ensure the appropriate solutions are provided on time. This position regularly reviews enhancement backlogs and delivery timelines with Internal GPS teams, Customers, and Nissan Digital to ensure priority requests are moving appropriately and collaborates to ensure global programs are completed on time. This position reviews release cycles and ensures business users are available to perform UAT and confirm successful solution delivery within a narrow time window.

This position also supports program management activities supporting overall management of the project portfolio for GPS and the meeting governance of GPS as a whole. Some of these PMO activities include but are not limited to collaboration meetings among various stakeholders, project status reviews, team performance metrics, global change management, and audit coordination.

Job Functions

The following job function statements describe the general nature and level of work being performed. They are not to be construed as an exhaustive list of all responsibilities, duties and skills required of personnel so classified. The job function statements reflect expectations of the fully trained, proficient incumbent who meets all performance criteria.

The position is an internal consultancy role that is responsible for leading investigation of processes, technology, cost, and strategy while identifying options for improving and bridging the needs of the business with the use of systems and technology while working with the Solutions team to propose appropriate resolution.

Serves as the conduit between the customer community (internal and external customers) and the solutions team through which requirements flow. (business units, technology teams and support teams)

Gains and maintains a working knowledge of high-level product functionality, to aid in interface with business users and collection of technical requirement documents.

Manage client and customer expectations through timely checkpoints to provide status on issues, roadblocks, risks, changes and accomplishments

Escalate issues to management appropriately to support timely resolution and ensure continued progress to project completion

The position will understand, interpret and suggest resolution to technical systematic issues in collaboration with the Solutions Team and communicates these issues effectively to management and peers.

Facilitates and participates in continuous improvement efforts outlined by platform owners.

The position interfaces within several domains, including cross-functional and cross-regional business functions.

Documents maintenance needs and submits technical specifications to the Service Delivery team for execution.

Manages the governance of key GPS responsibilities such as governance meetings, platform audits, knowledge management and enhancement creation access.

Develops and coordinates change management on global program plans aligning with product owners and HR functional users, communications, training, and awareness activities.

Coordinates with other teams on the communication of new product releases and knowledge of new product features and enhancements to support digital HR platforms.

Serves in a product/project management capacity:
Leads system programs that require global coordination and timing alignment.

Coordinates UAT for required configuration changes.

Aids adoption of platform technologies.

Manages project deliverables and deadlines including changes, enhancements, upgrades and implementations.

Supports all activities within assigned area and works closely with peers to support and ensure alignment.

As necessary, performs other related duties of which the above are representative.

Minimum Qualifications

The following qualification statements reflect the minimum skills and abilities required of the qualified applicant.

Bachelor’s degree in Business Administration/Strategy, Information Systems, Finance, Mathematics/Statistics or related field. Advanced degree in related discipline (MBA) preferred.

3+ years of directly related professional level experience.

2+ years of experience in business analyst, product/project management leadership required.

2+ years platform experience including Workday, ServiceNow, or Cornerstone required.

V-Up or Six Sigma certifications are preferred.

Occasional day or overnight travel; global travel may be necessary to support projects.

Ability to work outside standard business hours to collaborate with global counterparts required.

Job Knowledge and Skill:
The candidate must possess the skills to read, understand, lead interpretation of, and communicate technical systematic issues effectively to management and peers.

Possesses excellent communication skills in both written and verbal communication with both technical and non-technical audiences.

Strong analytical and product management skills required, including a thorough understanding of how to interpret customer business needs and translate them into application and operational requirements.

Drive and challenge business units on their assumptions of how they will successfully execute their plans

Ability to lead the teams efforts to establish deliverables and detail customer requirements, constraints, and assumptions with stakeholders and service providers in order to establish the deliverables for the service providers, eliciting requirements using interviews, document analysis, requirements workshops, surveys, site visits, business process descriptions, use cases, scenarios, business analysis, task and workflow analysis.

Supports team building through mutual trust and encourages respect and cooperation among team members.

Demonstrates high ethics and values by inspiring loyalty and trust, handles oneself ethically following core values and beliefs.

Successfully engage in multiple initiatives simultaneously

Experience with cross-functional, cross-affiliate, multi-cultural/global teams on activities/projects

Self-motivated, results-oriented, self-starter with a successful track record, able to manage multiple assignments concurrently with minimal supervision.

Strong emotional intelligence and demonstrated ability to handle highly sensitive and confidential information.

Ability to think critically about a problem and provide a solution. Knowledge and use of PDCA process.

Project management skills help the candidate manage projects, resources, risk, and change.

Interpersonal skills help the candidate work with end users as well as with other Analysts, developers, and other systems professionals.

Must be detail-oriented.

Must be flexible and possess the ability to adapt to changing priorities.

UW-IT is currently looking for a Business Intelligence (BI) Developer who will support the UW-IT work on Finance Transformation, the University’s large-scale project to modernize its finance operations, business systems and processes. The position is a role in the newly established UW-IT FT program (ITF).


The ITF BI Developer will contribute to the UW Finance Transformation Project remediating existing Finance-related BI tools that are impacted by Finance Transformation; this position will need to translate Finance requirements into Workday functionality in a reporting environment. The BI Developer will partner directly with the UW-IT Business Intelligence team, FT stakeholders, and campus users to conduct business analysis, document and articulate findings, produce and maintain BI deliverables, and other duties as assigned. The position requires a depth of knowledge in relational databases, data modeling, BI development, business analysis methods, and the data warehousing software development lifecycle.


REQUIREMENTS:

Bachelor’s Degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, Data Science or a related field, or equivalent experience.

Four years' experience performing progressively more complex and responsible tasks involving development and operations of business intelligence tools.

Experience within a software development lifecycle.

Experience with BI programming languages (SQL, TSQL).

Experience with BI Technologies (SSRS, SSAS).

Familiar with source code management and tools and processes like TFS.

Experience conducting business analysis, designing, prototyping, and developing data cubes and reports.

Demonstrated excellent written and verbal communication and technical documentation skills.

Excellent written/oral communication skills, technical documentation skills, user liaison skills, and personal interaction abilities.

Ability to quickly learn and apply new technologies and skills.

Demonstrated ability to work independently with minimal supervision.

An effective team player who enjoys collaboration.


Equivalent education/experience will substitute for all minimum qualifications except when there are legal requirements, such as a license/certification/registration.


DESIRED:

Strong experience with BI in the Cloud.

Strong experience writing complex SQL queries and tuning for performance.

Working knowledge of MDX, DAX, and Tabular Cubes.

Knowledge of cloud platforms like GCP, AWS, and/or Azure.

Knowledge of scalable and reliable software systems.

Knowledge of software test methodologies and automation tools.

Knowledge of open source software development.

Experience in a major research University setting.

Overview:

The Data Developer is primarily responsible for the organization, alignment, and standardization for reporting and analysis of data from multiple sources, including the design, delivery, and maintenance of the data universe structure. This includes working with the business on terminologies and definitions, data examples, relationships and governance rules. Provides a critical link between the enterprise data warehouse and the analysts. Provides support to analysts and other staff in the creation of meaningful and intuitive “business layer” solutions. Co-develops or develops dashboards, reports, data files, enterprise data warehouse support, and related deliverables, as necessary. Participates in maintenance and support of associated software. The position requires direct interaction with internal Information Services resources, external consultants, and stakeholders across the health system.
Qualifications:

Education
1) Bachelor’s degree in health management, business, statistics, data science, computer science/engineering, or related discipline. May have an equivalent combination of education and/or experience in lieu of specific education.
Experience
1) Prefer at least five years’ experience with data manipulation and visualization, research methodology, applied statistics, and/or business intelligence solutions.
2) Experience with (or working directly with those who perform) business and clinical operations with demonstrated ability to listen to and understand end-user requirements.
3) Experience with (or working directly with those who perform) computer programming, database management.
4) Experience using SQL queries to retrieve and manipulate data from large or complex database structures preferred
5) Experience with Artificial Intelligence/Machine Learning applications using Python, R, or Java preferred.
6) Experience using data lake architecture preferred.
7) Experience with Azure cloud sevice preferred.
8) Prior health care industry experience preferred.
Knowledge, Skills, Abilities

Business Intelligence Engineer is responsible for structuring the strategic design and maintenance of business intelligence applications. Identifies, researches, and resolves technical problems. Additionally, Business Intelligence Engineer typically reports to a supervisor. To be a Business Intelligence Engineer typically requires 4 to 7 years of related experience. Contributes to moderately complex aspects of a project. Work is generally independent and collaborative in nature.
Key Responsibilities Include:
Coordinate with customers and Business Analysts to determine business data reporting and analysis requirements.
Assist in business report generation to internal and external customers for business decision making.
Support Database Administrators and Developers to build data warehousing systems for business intelligence, reporting and analytics.
Assist in data administration, modelling and integration activities in data warehouse systems.
Implement business intelligence solutions to achieve data reporting and analysis goals.
Support the development of business intelligence standards to meet business goals.
Coordinate with the business units to identify new data requirements, analysis strategies and reporting mechanisms.
Assist in design and generation of reports in timely and accurate manner.
Work with the business units to improve business operations.
Train and guide the junior engineers in data reporting and analytical skills.
Recommend enhancements and modifications to optimize business intelligence processes.
Address business intelligence queries and issues in a timely fashion.
Create and execute project plans within allotted budget and timelines.
Maintain documentations for all business intelligence processes.

At Ascensus, technology is more than just a solution. It powers the business that helps millions of people save for what matters—retirement, education, and healthcare. Our technology experts tackle exciting challenges in collaborative teams, but work in an environment where individual and career development is always valued. Technology associates leverage their talents and passion, building new and innovative platforms, creating programs founded in automation in agile frameworks, and driving existing and new markets—all of which supports the rapid growth of a dynamic industry leader.
Section 1: Position Summary
As a Senior Business Intelligence (BI) Developer at Ascensus, you will be working in a high-energy team, using the best engineering practices in the industry today (e.g., unit testing, source control, continuous integration, automation, design patterns). Passion for all aspects of software development is a critical. We are building teams that are empowered to solve the business needs by having a rapid development and deployment pipeline with a focus on automation and releasing software. You will support and receive direction and guidance from the BI Architect and you will provide guidance and direction to BI Developers in the Ascensus Enterprise Information Management (EIM) team.
Section 2: Job Functions, Essential Duties and Responsibilities
BI Analysis
Drive business decisions by providing quantitative and qualitative data analysis and reporting of patterns, insights and trends to decision makers
Collect, aggregate and analyze data from multiple internal and external sources
Produce actionable reports that show key performance indicators
Provide analytics and reporting solutions using metrics across multiple business areas
BI Design and Development
Apply standards and best practices for implementing Ascensus BI tools in support of the EIM vision and reference architecture
Assist with EIM project definition and planning
Conduct data analysis in support of analytic solutions
Create ad hoc reporting solutions and dashboards
Capture, develop and document data definitions
Ensure compliance with deliverable reporting requirements by performing data quality audits and analysis
Implement package deployments and troubleshoot package issues
Modify, install and prepare technical documentation for BI applications
Create and maintain BI documentation for every System Development Life Cycle (SDLC) phase
Participate in creating long term BI application support model.
Ascensus Information Security
Responsible for protecting, securing, and proper handling of all confidential data held by Ascensus to ensure against unauthorized access, improper transmission, and/or unapproved disclosure of information that could result in harm to Ascensus or our clients.
Our I-Client service philosophy and our Core Values of People Matter, Quality First and Integrity Always® should be visible in your actions on a day to day basis showing your support of our organizational culture.
Supervision
N/A
Section 3: Experience, Skills, Knowledge Requirements
Required skills
Bachelor’s degree or equivalent work experience
Excellent analytical skills
Excellent oral and written communication skills including active listening. Asking appropriate questions, clarifying information and writing clear, concise documents.
DAX, Power BI dashboards, SSRS reporting
Designing/Building tabular models using latest version of SSAS
Modeling experience
Administration experience using Power BI
SQL Server latest version
Preferred knowledge, skills and abilities:
10+ years of relevant experience in business intelligence role, including data warehousing and business intelligence tools, techniques and technology
Microsoft Certified Business Intelligence in the above required skills
Experience with Microsoft SSIS
Experience with relational databases: Sybase ASE, Oracle, MySQL and others a plus
Experience with analytic platforms (data mining, predictive modeling) a plus

Join us as we pursue our mission to remove the barriers between data and action, so that everyone thrives in the Data Age. Splunk is filled with people who are passionate about pushing the boundaries of technology in an effort to help our customers succeed. As the world’s first Data-to-Everything Platform, Splunk is creating a world where data provides clarity, elevates discussion and accelerates progress. We invite you to explore what has made us one of the fastest growing technology companies in history, and how you can be an integral part of our journey!
Role
Are you passionate about groundbreaking technology and helping your customers and peers succeed? Would you like the opportunity to work at a fast-growing company that is changing the way that information is used to support business decisions?
Do you enjoy working collaboratively within a team to solve hard problems? Are you passionate about making customers successful? Like rolling up your sleeves and working with products across distributed environments? If you answered yes to these questions, then the Market Strategies and Technical Sales organization has the role for you!
As a Full Stack Developer, you work closely with the Market Strategy and Technical Sales organization as well as Product Management and Engineering teams to understand customer pain points, and design and build custom solutions to solve them.
The ideal candidate is fanatical about making customers successful, has a strong developer skill set, loves building and running distributed systems to solve business problems and deliver the experience for technical sellers to demonstrate value in Splunk’s portfolio across different infrastructure. This role is naturally fanatical about delivering the right tools and environment to demonstrate value across the Splunk portfolio.
Responsibilities
Work closely with members of the Market Strategies and Technical Sales, Product, and CloudOps teams to design and build solutions to solve demonstration problems
Scope and design integrations, workflows, and services aligned with internal customer demonstration requirements
Write cutting-edge frontend code using JS/HTML/CSS within client-side MVC frameworks, and backend code using Python and other scripting languages
Work with demonstration program manager to offer guidance and technical feasibility of internal customer requests
Act as a team technical liaison with other development teams (IT, Engineering, Cloud Ops, external) to improve Splunk demonstration framework over time while helping Splunk achieve its revenue goals and in product experience
Skill Requirements
2+ years of hands-on experience installing, using and configuring a combination of Splunk Enterprise, Splunk Cloud, Splunk IT Service Intelligence, SignalFx Infrastructure Monitoring, SignalFx Microservices APM and/or VictorOps, or equivalent.
Experience with Python, Go, JavaScript (including Node.js and React), HTML, CSS
Experience working and scripting within multiple operating systems, particularly Linux and Windows
Experience with cyber security
Experience working with Big Data platforms and tool sets such as Hadoop, Spark, Cassandra, etc.
Excellent problem-solving skills with great attention to detail
Preferred:
Experience developing software for enterprise
Experience with systems interoperability, integration and networking
Knowledge of data structures, storage systems, cloud infrastructure, front-end frameworks, and other technical tools
Education Requirements
Bachelor of Science degree in Computer Science or related discipline or equivalent work experience,

Job Summary
The Business Analyst provides analytical support through the analysis and interpretation of data in support of cross-functional business operations. Identifies opportunities for improvements and works cross-functionally to develop business solutions. Provides analytical support to projects including cost/benefit analysis and formulation of success measures prior to project launch and the calculation of ROI upon completion. Role may at times establishing project plans as it relates to data capture and storage and thus will need to coordinate on projects with internal and external resources.
Collects, validates, analyzes, and organizes data into curated data sources for use in operational, compliance and strategic analysis. Designs, develops, tests, and deploys reports/dashboards for Customer Experience leadership to assist in their decision-making process. The Business Analyst will make presentations to various levels of management to demonstrate reports, explain calculations and assumptions.
The Business Analyst is an individual contributor supporting Customer Experience reporting function which includes Compliance, Quality, Customer Feedback and Operations. The ensure reports/dashboards keep to CMS/State/Commercial specifications, are current, and validates results with the business. Provides technical expertise as it relates to Customer Experience data sources and manages relationships with business users with regards to their data needs. Provides analysis and estimates on steady state and future requests.
Responsibilities
Primary developer of our existing on prem data mart (Microsoft SQL server) and will assist in transition to HDFS data mart
Takes requirements from business leaders and translates that into hard requirements for development including ETL scripts, views, stored procedures as well as front end Tableau workbooks
Responsible for tracking, reporting, and analyzing the performance of call center activities, survey feedback, ad-hoc analytic requests, and development/automation of reports.
Develops, prepares and analyzes reports with complex analysis and data for management review, and presents to various levels of management. Defines business requirements and provides analysis to increase operational efficiency.
Analyzes external and internal customer data using database queries (SQL), and statistical analysis tools (Python, Tableau)
Identifies opportunities for improvement in operational performance and notifies management of issues and problems requiring immediate attention. Evaluates customer interaction behavior and feedback to provide insights and recommendations for further enhancements to the overall customer experience.
Works cross-functionally. Creates PowerPoint presentations to provide analytical insights for various customer experience stakeholders.
Advises other business functions as a knowledge resource for contact center data including call metrics, desktop analytics, quality monitoring and customer experience data.
Extending company’s data with third party sources of information when needed
Processing, cleansing, and verifying the integrity of data used for analysis.
Analysis of varying types of business data to determine trends, identify strategic insights and growth opportunities.
Plays a part in shaping the business’s data infrastructure, inclusive of data-warehousing, reporting, and analytics platforms.
Provide expertise on mathematical concepts for the broader analytics team and inspire adoption of advanced analytics across the organization.
Knowledge and Experience
At least 5 years of work experience in data analysis and visualization (academic equivalent will be considered) with focus on health care, call center, voice of the customer preferred.
Excellent SQL Skills including the creation, update and dropping of tables
Intermediate/advanced Python with experience Writing and maintaining ETL Jobs in Airflow preferred
Advanced/Expert Tableau Skills
Excellent analytical skills and a high degree of business acumen.
Strong organizational, communication and presentation skills.
Proven ability in handling concurrent projects with attention to detail and accuracy.
Expert working knowledge on the extraction, interpretation, and preparation of both quantitative and qualitative data.
Demonstrated ability and comfort working with ambiguous data from numerous data sources (home grown, file, database, cloud, API, etc.).
Experience building and automating management level reporting.
Proficiency in Microsoft Office Suite (Excel, PowerPoint) and database management tools (SQL Server Management Studio, Toad, DBeaver).
Bachelor’s degree (Master’s preferred) in a quantitative discipline or graduate degree.
Experience with Avaya, Verint or SSIS a plus
