Job Title: Business Intelligence Analyst - Fully Remote Position
Description:
At Shutterfly, we’re all about people — bringing them together, making them feel welcome, and connecting them to experiences. We make our customers’ memories last a lifetime by capturing, preserving, and sharing them through photography and personalized products. Through our family of brands, trend setting products, cutting edge technology, and best in class customer service, we help our customers, and each other, share life’s joy.

What You'll Do Here:
The Business Intelligence team partners with Shutterfly’s Marketing, Finance, Operations and Business teams to design and develop reports and dashboards that drive business decisions. The Sr. Business Intelligence Developer supports Business partners by utilizing knowledge of company data structure and experience with BI tools to provide insightful reporting solutions using Tableau. This role requires an individual with strong technical and analytical skills, good communication skills and ability to learn new technologies quickly. The ideal candidate is a self-motivated team player who is detail oriented, enjoys problem solving, can work independently and understands the full BI reporting development process. This role will spend time in both a project management capacity where others will develop the report as well as developing reports themselves.
What You'll Bring:
Great to Haves (Your Skills)
You have demonstrated the ability to manage BI projects from start to finish, gather information and requirements from business partners on BI initiatives, translate requirements into project plans, track project status within Jira, set expectations and communicate with business partners, and ensure final deliverables meet business partner’s needs.
You have designed, developed, and maintained reporting and business intelligence solutions using Tableau reporting software while leveraging visualization best practices.
You have written complex SQL queries to build performant extracts in Tableau.
You have participated in QC/QA and UAT processes.
You have worked with data teams to deliver solutions for reporting needs.
Great to Haves (Your Background)
Bachelor’s Degree in quantitative field and 3+ years’ experience in business intelligence, primarily working with the latest versions of Tableau.
Advanced Tableau user with experience designing dashboards leveraging visualization best practices.
Proficient with SQL; familiar with database design; experience working with large data sets.
Excellent communication and project management skills.
Detail oriented with ability to independently validate / triangulate data and analysis.
Able to prioritize multiple requests while completing deliverables on time. Self-motivated and can work independently. Ability to troubleshoot, track, and resolve day-to-day issues.
Must be comfortable with unstructured, fast-moving and constantly evolving high growth environment. Passion for excellence and continuous improvement.
If this aligns to your career goals, skills and experience, we want to work with you!
We are unable to provide visa sponsorship or transfers for this role at this time. No candidates requiring visa sponsorship or transfer will be considered.

Job Title: Entry Level - Associate Developer (Commercial): Front End
Description:
Introduction
As an Application Developer, you will lead IBM into the future by translating system requirements into the design and development of customized systems in an agile environment. The success of IBM is in your hands as you transform vital business needs into code and drive innovation. Your work will power IBM and its clients globally, collaborating and integrating code into enterprise systems. You will have access to the latest education, tools and technology, and a limitless career path with the world’s technology leader. Come to IBM and make a global impact!

Your Role and Responsibilities
As an Associate Developer, you’ll help design, develop, and integrate solutions using best practice technologies, tools, techniques, and products our clients demand today. You’ll work with clients, co-creating solutions to major real-world challenges by translating system requirements into the design and development of customized systems in an agile environment.

Work you could do as an Associate Developer:

IBM provides a variety of solutions to clients and our specialized teams serve these needs. As a result, the specific work and technologies vary by the team you may be joining. Below is a list of the types of work Associate Developers do.
Work in an Agile environment to understand requirements, design, code and test innovative applications, and support those applications for our highly valued customers.
Employ IBM's Design Thinking to create products that provide a great user experience along with high performance, security, quality, and stability.
Work with a variety of relational databases (SQL, Postgres, DB2, MongoDB), operating systems (Linux, Windows, iOS, Android), and modern UI frameworks (Backbone.js, AngularJS, React, Ember.js, Bootstrap, and JQuery).
Work across the entire system architecture, from backend to front end, to design, develop, and support high quality, scalable products and interfaces.
Create everything from mockups and UI components to algorithms and data structures as you deliver a viable product.
Locations:
Atlanta, GA
Cambridge, MA
Chicago, IL
Dallas, TX
Houston, TX
New York, NY
San Francisco, CA
Washington DC

Required Technical and Professional Expertise

Have flexibility to work across architecture - building both front end and backend.
Have knowledge of application and web development in HTML and CSS.
Are skilled in programming languages like Java, Ruby, Python, Javascript, HTML, CSS.
Have knowledge of modern UI frameworks such as Angular.js and React.
Work in Java to implement server-side or application logic, develop databases, and design architectures.
Have exposure to Cloud – AWS, Azure, Google Could or IBM Cloud.
Have work experience or internship in corporate development environment.
Willingness to travel up to 100% of the time.
Preferred Majors:
Computer Science, Computer Information Systems, or Computer Engineering (if demonstrated strong current language programming experience)

Preferred Technical and Professional Expertise

Have an interest in, understanding of, or experience with Design Thinking Methodology.
Have an interest in, understanding of, or experience with Agile development methodology.
Experience in following a structure methodology.
Initiative to actively seek new knowledge and improve skills.
Strong interpersonal skills with ability to collaborate and work effectively with individuals, strengthening relationships to achieve win-win solutions.
Ability to communicate complex situations clearly and simply by listening actively and conveying difficult messages in a positive manner.
A passion for innovative ideas, coupled with the ability and assimilate different points of view.
About Business UnitIBM Services is a team of business, strategy and technology consultants that design, build, and run foundational systems and services that is the backbone of the world's economy. IBM Services partners with the world's leading companies in over 170 countries to build smarter businesses by reimagining and reinventing through technology, with its outcome-focused methodologies, industry-leading portfolio and world class research and operations expertise leading to results-driven innovation and enduring excellence.
This job requires you to be fully COVID-19 vaccinated prior to your start date, where legally permissible. Proof of vaccination status will be required. If you are unable to be vaccinated due to medical, pregnancy or religious reasons, we offer accommodations in accordance with applicable law.

Every IBMer, and potential ones like yourself, has a voice, carves their own path, and uses their expertise to help co-create and add to our story. Together, we have the power to make meaningful change – to alter the fabric of our clients, of society and IBM itself, to create a truly positive impact and make the world work better for everyone.

It's time to define your career.

Now it’s time for you to join us on our journey to being a responsible technology innovator and a force for good in the world.

This role will own and drive the transformation of our Cloud web business intelligence teams by planning, designing, operating, and managing our Business Intelligence and web analytics programs. Responsibilities

Job Description

The Nevada System of Higher Education (NSHE) invites applications and nominations for the position of Workday Business Intelligence Developer. This is a renewable, full-time, non-tenured, administrative position and reports to the Assistant Director for Development and Integration. The position may be located in either Reno or Las Vegas, Nevada. The NSHE is comprised of eight institutions: two universities, a state college, four community colleges and a research institute. The public system of higher education in Nevada continues to experience growth with significant opportunities in serving over 105,000 students and 12,000 employees.


The position will support the NSHE Workday system environment and provide continuing data reporting and business intelligence support of Workday's cloud-based administrative solution creating a unified Human Resources, Payroll and Financial Management system for the Nevada System of Higher Education.

SALARY GRADE: C (starting salary range approximately $70,000 - $90,000 and benefits package that includes health, dental, vision, life and retirement.)

APPROXIMATE STARTING DATE: September 1, 2021

MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS: Successful candidates must have an earned Bachelor's Degree in Information Systems or a related field with five years of directly applicable experience. Alternatively, ten or more years of direct experience in Enterprise Resource Planning (ERP) systems (Workday, PeopleSoft, SAP, Oracle, Salesforce, Netsuite, Taleo, or other SaaS and On-Premise ERP systems) and at least two years of formal education or training in a related field may be substituted for a Bachelor's Degree.

Preferred experience:

5+ years developing reporting solutions with ERP software
5+ years Human Resource, Payroll or Financial software application experience
5+ Years Business Intelligence reporting experience
5+ Years Data warehousing experience and/or Big Data
EDI, Web Services, XML, XSLT, Java experience
Workday, PeopleSoft, SAP, Oracle OBIEE, Salesforce, Netsuite, Taleo, or other SaaS and On-Premise ERP systems and reporting
The incumbent must have the ability and interest to learn new techniques, tools and methodologies
Background and experience in higher education and/or expertise for a large enterprise or university

KNOWLEDGE, SKILLS, AND ABILITIES: Successful candidates must possess the following knowledge, skills and abilities. It is recommended that applicants for this position address each of the following items in the letter of application:

Strong analysis and ability to creatively solve complex problems;
excellent verbal and written communication skills;
strong interpersonal skills and tact;
strong customer service and service management focus
ability to function in a team;
ability to understand the technical aspects of the information technology services provided by SCS;
ability to understand SCS resources and procedures;
ability and interest to learn new techniques, tools and methodologies.

RESPONSIBILITIES: The duties of this position will include, but not be limited to, the following areas of responsibility:

The major purpose of this position is to develop, support, and maintain various types of data reports, queries, and extracts for the Workday enterprise system environment. Responsibilities will include design and analysis, gathering functional requirements, maintaining documentation, and development skills using various types of analytics tools and Workday reporting features. Design timely and accurate dashboards, reports, presentations and visual aids used to educate, inform and influence the decisions of HR/Finance and business leaders within NSHE. Analyze existing production reporting and programming logic to provide more efficient operations or to identify difficulties. Revise logic and procedures involved, as necessary. Identify the data model and security requirements including role-based permissions for HR and Financial reporting solutions. Provide necessary statutory and legally required reports globally as mandated by government agencies, state agencies and /or work councils. Develop, test and evaluate reports, dashboard and big datasets. Effectively communicate with NSHE stakeholders throughout the development processes.

TO APPLY: The application process will be handled through the HR Search on-line search process. Application materials must include a current resume, detailed cover letter, and names, addresses, and telephone numbers of four professional references willing to be contacted. Applicants should fully describe qualifications and experience, since the initial review will serve to evaluate applicants based on documented, relevant qualifications and professional work experience. Materials should be addressed to Sherry Olson, Director of Human Resources, and are to be submitted via on-line application at https://nshe.nevada.edu/administration/human-resources. For assistance with NSHE's on-line applicant portal, contact Sherry Olson at (775) 784- 4901 or solson@nshe.nevada.edu


Application Deadline: Applications may be submitted until the position is filled; however, to ensure full consideration, applications should be submitted by August 15, 2021.

For more information about the Nevada System of Higher Education, please visit our website at www.nevada.edu. The Nevada System of Higher Education hires only United States citizens and aliens lawfully authorized to work in the U.S.

Job Title: Business Intelligence Analyst, Senior - Workforce Optimizati...
Description:
Job Summary
The Business Analyst provides analytical support through the analysis and interpretation of data in support of cross-functional business operations. Identifies opportunities for improvements and works cross-functionally to develop business solutions. Provides analytical support to projects including cost/benefit analysis and formulation of success measures prior to project launch and the calculation of ROI upon completion. Role may at times establishing project plans as it relates to data capture and storage and thus will need to coordinate on projects with internal and external resources.
Collects, validates, analyzes, and organizes data into curated data sources for use in operational, compliance and strategic analysis. Designs, develops, tests, and deploys reports/dashboards for Customer Experience leadership to assist in their decision-making process. The Business Analyst will make presentations to various levels of management to demonstrate reports, explain calculations and assumptions.
The Business Analyst is an individual contributor supporting Customer Experience reporting function which includes Compliance, Quality, Customer Feedback and Operations. The ensure reports/dashboards keep to CMS/State/Commercial specifications, are current, and validates results with the business. Provides technical expertise as it relates to Customer Experience data sources and manages relationships with business users with regards to their data needs. Provides analysis and estimates on steady state and future requests.
Responsibilities
Primary developer of our existing on prem data mart (Microsoft SQL server) and will assist in transition to HDFS data mart
Takes requirements from business leaders and translates that into hard requirements for development including ETL scripts, views, stored procedures as well as front end Tableau workbooks
Responsible for tracking, reporting, and analyzing the performance of call center activities, survey feedback, ad-hoc analytic requests, and development/automation of reports.
Develops, prepares and analyzes reports with complex analysis and data for management review, and presents to various levels of management. Defines business requirements and provides analysis to increase operational efficiency.
Analyzes external and internal customer data using database queries (SQL), and statistical analysis tools (Python, Tableau)
Identifies opportunities for improvement in operational performance and notifies management of issues and problems requiring immediate attention. Evaluates customer interaction behavior and feedback to provide insights and recommendations for further enhancements to the overall customer experience.
Works cross-functionally. Creates PowerPoint presentations to provide analytical insights for various customer experience stakeholders.
Advises other business functions as a knowledge resource for contact center data including call metrics, desktop analytics, quality monitoring and customer experience data.
Extending company’s data with third party sources of information when needed
Processing, cleansing, and verifying the integrity of data used for analysis.
Analysis of varying types of business data to determine trends, identify strategic insights and growth opportunities.
Plays a part in shaping the business’s data infrastructure, inclusive of data-warehousing, reporting, and analytics platforms.
Provide expertise on mathematical concepts for the broader analytics team and inspire adoption of advanced analytics across the organization.
Knowledge and Experience
At least 5 years of work experience in data analysis and visualization (academic equivalent will be considered) with focus on health care, call center, voice of the customer preferred.
Excellent SQL Skills including the creation, update and dropping of tables
Intermediate/advanced Python with experience Writing and maintaining ETL Jobs in Airflow preferred
Advanced/Expert Tableau Skills
Excellent analytical skills and a high degree of business acumen.
Strong organizational, communication and presentation skills.
Proven ability in handling concurrent projects with attention to detail and accuracy.
Expert working knowledge on the extraction, interpretation, and preparation of both quantitative and qualitative data.
Demonstrated ability and comfort working with ambiguous data from numerous data sources (home grown, file, database, cloud, API, etc.).
Experience building and automating management level reporting.
Proficiency in Microsoft Office Suite (Excel, PowerPoint) and database management tools (SQL Server Management Studio, Toad, DBeaver).
Bachelor’s degree (Master’s preferred) in a quantitative discipline or graduate degree.
Experience with Avaya, Verint or SSIS a plus

About JSSI. . .For over 30 years, Jet Support Services, Inc. (JSSI), has been the leading independent provider of maintenance support and financial services to the business aviation industry. The company offers hourly cost maintenance programs to manage the often unpredictable costs of operating virtually all makes and models of aircraft, engines and auxiliary power units (APUs). JSSI is responsible for maintaining in excess of 2,000 business jets, turboprops, regional jets and helicopters across the globe and serves customers through its unique infrastructure of expert technical advisors.JSSI’s portfolio of companies leverage this extensive technical knowledge, maintenance buying power and data to support every stage of the aircraft life cycle, from aircraft acquisition to disassembling and parting out the aircraft. JSSI Parts & Leasing sells aircraft parts, provides lease engines and APUs, and offers supply chain solutions as a service to large fleet operators. Additionally, JSSI’s technical experience and global reach powers a complete range of consulting and digital services utilized by operators, aircraft brokers, and service providers across the industry.In 2020, JSSI was recognized as a US Best Managed Company.Other JSSI services:*JSSI Parts & Leasing provides aircraft parts, leasing and supply chain solutions. An extensive inventory of over 25,000 aircraft parts, engines and APUs is available across multiple makes and models of commercial and business jets, turboprops and helicopters. A qualified global vendor network sources additional assets for anything that flies.*JSSI Advisory Services utilizes JSSI’s technical expertise and global network to inspect aircraft, perform ASA-certified appraisals, assist with maintenance cost planning, manage maintenance events, audit invoices, and provide insurance claims management.*Conklin & de Decker enables aircraft owners and operators to make more informed decisions. More than 35 years of objective and impartial data powers digital tools to analyze aircraft ownership options with the most accurate performance and comparison data available, review critical state tax information, and streamline MRO business processes and track maintenance with Aerotrac software.For more information, visit jetsupport.com.Jet Support Services, Inc. Overview

The DFCI Enterprise Data Warehouse(EDW) ETL Developer is a critical member of the Informatics & Analytics team supporting the implementation and on-going development and operations of the EDW in support of the overall DFCI mission to improve quality and manage healthcare expense trends. This is a hands-on position that requires a technical and functional understanding of data warehousing and healthcare analytics. Responsibilities include analyzing business requirements, and architecting, designing, developing, and unit testing integration solutions to meet customer needs.
The role is expected to understand and apply best practices and provide expertise in acquiring data from source systems to build database analytic content. As such, it is expected that the individual will understand the full lifecycle of enterprise data warehouse and business intelligence projects. The individual in this position will interact with directors, leads, architects, consultants, business analysts, co-developers and business/clinical users. The successful candidate will be an experienced developer with extensive enterprise background using MS SQL Server. The ETL Developer will be required to identify business requirements, develop data models, perform data analysis, write advanced SQL queries and triggers, design and code complex stored procedures, and maintain and performance tune existing databases.
At Dana-Farber Cancer Institute, we work every day to create an innovative, caring, and inclusive environment where every patient, family, and staff member feels they belong. As relentless as we are in our mission to reduce the burden of cancer for all, we are equally committed to diversifying our faculty and staff. Cancer knows no boundaries and when it comes to hiring the most dedicated and diverse professionals, neither do we. If working in this kind of organization inspires you, we encourage you to apply.

Requirements

Integrates source system data into the EDW, including initial development of extraction/integration routines
Designs, builds and maintains data warehouse solutions to support Reporting and Analytics projects
Work with end users, business analysts, technical staff, and other project team members to plan, design, develop, implement, and enhance application processes and overall data and process flow and user interface applications
Works with teams to integrate data across clinical, administrative, and financial source systems including the management of critical master data
Support on-going production operations and maintenance of current and legacy systems
Support troubleshooting and problem resolution activities as needed, including acting as an escalation point for technical and process issues
Self-starter with a strong desire to learn and apply the latest technologies related to database solutions
Participate in the design, development and implementation of the Health Catalyst Platform supporting Clinical and Research Analytics
Creating Source Marts for different Sources using the Source Mart Designer Tool
Work with Business Users and DW Architects to create and deploy Subject Area Marts using SAM designer
Use the EDW Console (part of the Health Catalyst family of products) to configure batches, execute ETL tasks and monitor health of the EDW
Applies design principals and architectural standards, including those that support security and auditing requirements
Develops strong working relationships with key project team members and customers to ensure activities are aligned with business objectives
Diagnose and resolve database access and performance issues

Qualifications

Bachelor’s degree preferably in computer science or management Information Systems
Minimum 4 years experience in data warehouse architecture, design, development and data integration
6+ years of related professional experience including 4+ years in data warehousing development in large reporting environment(s) related to clinical, biological, and genomics data
Strong understanding of Data Architecture, ETL Architecture, SQL Server security, performance monitoring and optimizing
Strong experience with Microsoft SSIS, SSRS, Microsoft T-SQL
Experience working with relational databases including SQL Server and Oracle
4+ years of writing complex SQL, T-SQL
Experience working with Epic and Peoplesoft
Must have a strong understanding of Kimball approach to data warehousing using denormalized star schemas and snowflakes
Hands on experience performance tuning database applications including indexing, with ability to interpret execution plans
Prior experience working with healthcare financial and revenue cycle systems is strongly preferred
Experience with medical/clinical data exchange standards, such as FHIR and HL7

Job Description

The Nevada System of Higher Education (NSHE) invites applications and nominations for the position of Workday Business Intelligence Developer. This is a renewable, full-time, non-tenured, administrative position and reports to the Assistant Director for Development and Integration. The position may be located in either Reno or Las Vegas, Nevada. The NSHE is comprised of eight institutions: two universities, a state college, four community colleges and a research institute. The public system of higher education in Nevada continues to experience growth with significant opportunities in serving over 105,000 students and 12,000 employees.


The position will support the NSHE Workday system environment and provide continuing data reporting and business intelligence support of Workday's cloud-based administrative solution creating a unified Human Resources, Payroll and Financial Management system for the Nevada System of Higher Education.

SALARY GRADE: C (starting salary range approximately $70,000 - $90,000 and benefits package that includes health, dental, vision, life and retirement.)

APPROXIMATE STARTING DATE: September 1, 2021

MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS: Successful candidates must have an earned Bachelor's Degree in Information Systems or a related field with five years of directly applicable experience. Alternatively, ten or more years of direct experience in Enterprise Resource Planning (ERP) systems (Workday, PeopleSoft, SAP, Oracle, Salesforce, Netsuite, Taleo, or other SaaS and On-Premise ERP systems) and at least two years of formal education or training in a related field may be substituted for a Bachelor's Degree.

Preferred experience:

5+ years developing reporting solutions with ERP software
5+ years Human Resource, Payroll or Financial software application experience
5+ Years Business Intelligence reporting experience
5+ Years Data warehousing experience and/or Big Data
EDI, Web Services, XML, XSLT, Java experience
Workday, PeopleSoft, SAP, Oracle OBIEE, Salesforce, Netsuite, Taleo, or other SaaS and On-Premise ERP systems and reporting
The incumbent must have the ability and interest to learn new techniques, tools and methodologies
Background and experience in higher education and/or expertise for a large enterprise or university

KNOWLEDGE, SKILLS, AND ABILITIES: Successful candidates must possess the following knowledge, skills and abilities. It is recommended that applicants for this position address each of the following items in the letter of application:

Strong analysis and ability to creatively solve complex problems;
excellent verbal and written communication skills;
strong interpersonal skills and tact;
strong customer service and service management focus
ability to function in a team;
ability to understand the technical aspects of the information technology services provided by SCS;
ability to understand SCS resources and procedures;
ability and interest to learn new techniques, tools and methodologies.

RESPONSIBILITIES: The duties of this position will include, but not be limited to, the following areas of responsibility:

The major purpose of this position is to develop, support, and maintain various types of data reports, queries, and extracts for the Workday enterprise system environment. Responsibilities will include design and analysis, gathering functional requirements, maintaining documentation, and development skills using various types of analytics tools and Workday reporting features. Design timely and accurate dashboards, reports, presentations and visual aids used to educate, inform and influence the decisions of HR/Finance and business leaders within NSHE. Identify the data model and security requirements including role-based permissions for HR and Financial reporting solutions. Provide necessary statutory and legally required reports globally as mandated by government agencies, state agencies and /or work councils. Develop, test and evaluate reports, dashboard and big datasets. Effectively communicate with NSHE stakeholders throughout the development processes.

The Opportunity
Investment Management is looking for an energetic individual with strong analytical skills to join the team as a Data Analyst - Business Intelligence (BI) Developer on the Investment Reporting & Communications (IR&C) team. You will be responsible for the creating, publishing, and optimizing Investment Management’s reporting and analytics, collaborating with business partners throughout the enterprise – including enterprise technology and data science.
The Team
The IR&C team is responsible for communicating the General Investment Account’s strategy, asset allocation, risk exposures, and transaction activity in support of the Chief Investment Officer’s report backs to the Investment Committee of the Board of Directors, rating agencies, and business units. The team is currently under-going a multi-year data and reporting modernization project and is actively looking for a data analyst who enjoys solving complex problems, understands business goals, and manages multiple priorities.
The Impact
This role is hands-on, developing and delivering highly intuitive analytical solutions optimizing the use of dashboards and visualization for investment portfolio reporting & analysis. You will be the subject matter expert for the current reporting application and new tools while applying existing knowledge, and teaching others.
Your responsibilities would include, but are not limited to:
Build and deploy highly interactive dashboards, reports, and other visualizations that are easy to understand, enable self-service, and provide secure and efficient access to data
Continuously improve and enhance the performance, capabilities, and functional coverage of analytics solutions
Partner with IR&C team to translate requirements into technical specifications
Extract and analyze data from investment repositories, third-party vendors, and external managers based on ad-hoc user requests
Create ETL and manage change control for dimensions and other report derivations
Conduct unit testing and troubleshooting
Manage weekly report development meetings and communications
Manage report life cycle and promotion process using Atlassian JIRA
Track investment new field requests, data quality requests and resolution, and downstream project dependencies
The Minimum Qualifications
Bachelor’s degree in Information Technology, Computer Science, CIS, Engineering, Math or related major
Minimum of 5 years BI/Analytics experience with increasing responsibilities implementing medium and large-scale projects and business intelligence solutions
At least 3 years of experience with MicroStrategy or comparable BI tool (IBM Cognos, Tableau, etc.)
Experience working with complex data structures and datasets
The Ideal Qualifications
Master’s degree Information Technology, Computer Science, CIS, Engineering, Math or related major
8 years BI/Analytics experience with increasing responsibilities implementing medium and large-scale projects and business intelligence solutions
6 years of experience with MicroStrategy or comparable BI tool (IBM Cognos, Tableau, etc.)
5 years Investment Management related experience
What to Expect as Part of MassMutual and the Team
Regular meetings with the IR&C Team
Focused one-on-one meetings with your manager
Access to mentorship opportunities
Networking opportunities including access to Asian, Hispanic/Latinx, African American, women, LGBTQ, Veteran and disability-focused Business Resource Groups
Access to learning content on Degreed and other informational platforms
Your ethics and integrity will be valued by a company with a strong and stable ethical business with industry leading pay and benefits
About MassMutual
We’ve been around since 1851. During our history, we’ve helped millions of people find financial freedom, offer financial protection, and plan for the future.
Today, we continue to develop meaningful relationships with our customers by building their trust, being knowledge problem solvers and always prioritizing their needs. MassMutual is guided by a single purpose: We help people secure their future and protect the ones they love. Business Intelligence Developer

Multiple Positions: Responsible for the strategic design, development, deployment, and maintenance of business intelligence solutions and applications and analytical reports. Work with analytics team to employ standardized processes using data from participants and affiliates and apply business rules. Work with business users, NEHII stakeholders, business and data analysts, and data engineers and architects to develop business intelligence applications, including data marts, dashboards, reports and alerts, based on defined business functional and technical requirements, and design, develop, and maintain analytical data marts and profile and model data. Develop and analyze business intelligence needs and translate to technical specifications. Provide input on business and technical requirements for the design of BI solutions, interpret requirements to determine optimum solutions, and support development and update of business and technical documentation. Conduct source to target data mapping exercises for data sources. Profile data sets for completeness and validity and build automated SQL scripts to assess same and other data metrics. Support QA to develop and test use case scenarios and testing requirements to ensure data validity and BI solution meets functional requirements. Research, evaluate, and assess the impact of issues identified in data and/or processes. Develop and execute database queries to analyze health data from disparate data sources. Gather and interpret data and aid in decision-making process using statistical techniques and create project visualizations and reports. Develop BI solutions that measure performance and monitor organizational processes against outcome measures and evaluate and improve existing solutions. Design and develop organizational-wide and custom “views” and reports and analyze requirements, processes, and issues to automate reporting and processing. Identify new technology opportunities and provides oversight and resolve complex issues as well as provide guidance and training to junior team members. Identify, acquire, and manage data from various data stores and integrate cross matrix departmental data. Research methodologies to discern trends, anomalies, and areas of opportunity or uncertainty using data mining and modeling and develop new metrics/dashboards and database objects to monitor trends. Develop database objects using SAS and work on relational database, table design and structure, joins, data normalization, and data types. Perform review analyses, including accumulation of data, forecast modeling, reporting, and monitoring of responses and create predictive algorithms to gain insights.

Minimum Requirements: a Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Data Science, Statistics, or a closely related field with five years or a Master's degree in Computer Science, Data Science, Statistics, or a closely related field with two years of experience in business intelligence, data science, or statistics that includes demonstrated analytical, visualization, and problem solving skills; experience in MS Access, MS Excel, MS PowerPoint, SQL databases, Data Marts, SAS, Tableau, scripting tools (i.e. R or Python), and Amazon Web Services; the ability to work in environment using Agile methodologies and principles; and a demonstrated understanding of health data, including managed care, population health, or health insurance operations.

Workday Business Intelligence Developer
Thank you for your interest in employment with Nevada System of Higher Education (NSHE), System Administration and System Computing Services. We want your application process to go smoothly and quickly. We ask that you keep in mind the following when completing your application:

Draft applications are saved automatically and can be accessed through your candidate home account.

If you need assistance or have questions regarding the application process, please contact our Human Resources department at (775) 784-4901.

Job Description

The Nevada System of Higher Education (NSHE) invites applications and nominations for the position of Workday Business Intelligence Developer. This is a renewable, full-time, non-tenured, administrative position and reports to the Assistant Director for Development and Integration. The position may be located in either Reno or Las Vegas, Nevada. The NSHE is comprised of eight institutions: two universities, a state college, four community colleges and a research institute. The public system of higher education in Nevada continues to experience growth with significant opportunities in serving over 105,000 students and 12,000 employees.


The position will support the NSHE Workday system environment and provide continuing data reporting and business intelligence support of Workday's cloud-based administrative solution creating a unified Human Resources, Payroll and Financial Management system for the Nevada System of Higher Education.

SALARY GRADE: C (starting salary range approximately $70,000 - $90,000 and benefits package that includes health, dental, vision, life and retirement.)

APPROXIMATE STARTING DATE: September 1, 2021

MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS: Successful candidates must have an earned Bachelor's Degree in Information Systems or a related field with five years of directly applicable experience. Alternatively, ten or more years of direct experience in Enterprise Resource Planning (ERP) systems (Workday, PeopleSoft, SAP, Oracle, Salesforce, Netsuite, Taleo, or other SaaS and On-Premise ERP systems) and at least two years of formal education or training in a related field may be substituted for a Bachelor's Degree.

Preferred experience:

5+ years developing reporting solutions with ERP software
5+ years Human Resource, Payroll or Financial software application experience
5+ Years Business Intelligence reporting experience
5+ Years Data warehousing experience and/or Big Data
EDI, Web Services, XML, XSLT, Java experience
Workday, PeopleSoft, SAP, Oracle OBIEE, Salesforce, Netsuite, Taleo, or other SaaS and On-Premise ERP systems and reporting
The incumbent must have the ability and interest to learn new techniques, tools and methodologies
Background and experience in higher education and/or expertise for a large enterprise or university

KNOWLEDGE, SKILLS, AND ABILITIES: Successful candidates must possess the following knowledge, skills and abilities. It is recommended that applicants for this position address each of the following items in the letter of application:

Strong analysis and ability to creatively solve complex problems;
excellent verbal and written communication skills;
strong interpersonal skills and tact;
strong customer service and service management focus
ability to function in a team;
ability to understand the technical aspects of the information technology services provided by SCS;
ability to understand SCS resources and procedures;
ability and interest to learn new techniques, tools and methodologies.

RESPONSIBILITIES: The duties of this position will include, but not be limited to, the following areas of responsibility:

The major purpose of this position is to develop, support, and maintain various types of data reports, queries, and extracts for the Workday enterprise system environment. Responsibilities will include design and analysis, gathering functional requirements, maintaining documentation, and development skills using various types of analytics tools and Workday reporting features. Design timely and accurate dashboards, reports, presentations and visual aids used to educate, inform and influence the decisions of HR/Finance and business leaders within NSHE. Analyze existing production reporting and programming logic to provide more efficient operations or to identify difficulties. Revise logic and procedures involved, as necessary. Identify the data model and security requirements including role-based permissions for HR and Financial reporting solutions. Provide necessary statutory and legally required reports globally as mandated by government agencies, state agencies and /or work councils. Develop, test and evaluate reports, dashboard and big datasets. Effectively communicate with NSHE stakeholders throughout the development processes.

TO APPLY: The application process will be handled through the HR Search on-line search process. Application materials must include a current resume, detailed cover letter, and names, addresses, and telephone numbers of four professional references willing to be contacted. Applicants should fully describe qualifications and experience, since the initial review will serve to evaluate applicants based on documented, relevant qualifications and professional work experience. Materials should be addressed to Sherry Olson, Director of Human Resources, and are to be submitted via on-line application at https://nshe.nevada.edu/administration/human-resources. For assistance with NSHE's on-line applicant portal, contact Sherry Olson at (775) 784- 4901 or solson@nshe.nevada.edu


Application Deadline: Applications may be submitted until the position is filled; however, to ensure full consideration, applications should be submitted by August 15, 2021.

For more information about the Nevada System of Higher Education, please visit our website at www.nevada.edu. The Nevada System of Higher Education hires only United States citizens and aliens lawfully authorized to work in the U.S.


NSHE is an equal opportunity and affirmative action employer committed to achieving excellence through diversity. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, age, creed, national origin, veteran status, physical or mental disability, sexual orientation, family medical history or genetic information, gender identity, gender expression, or any other factor protected by anti-discrimination laws. Thank you for your interest in employment with Nevada System of Higher Education (NSHE), System Administration and System Computing Services. We want your application process to go smoothly and quickly. We ask that you keep in mind the following when completing your application:

Job Description

The Nevada System of Higher Education (NSHE) invites applications and nominations for the position of Workday Business Intelligence Developer. This is a renewable, full-time, non-tenured, administrative position and reports to the Assistant Director for Development and Integration. The position may be located in either Reno or Las Vegas, Nevada. The NSHE is comprised of eight institutions: two universities, a state college, four community colleges and a research institute. The public system of higher education in Nevada continues to experience growth with significant opportunities in serving over 105,000 students and 12,000 employees.


The position will support the NSHE Workday system environment and provide continuing data reporting and business intelligence support of Workday's cloud-based administrative solution creating a unified Human Resources, Payroll and Financial Management system for the Nevada System of Higher Education.

SALARY GRADE: C (starting salary range approximately $70,000 - $90,000 and benefits package that includes health, dental, vision, life and retirement.)

APPROXIMATE STARTING DATE: September 1, 2021

MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS: Successful candidates must have an earned Bachelor's Degree in Information Systems or a related field with five years of directly applicable experience. Alternatively, ten or more years of direct experience in Enterprise Resource Planning (ERP) systems (Workday, PeopleSoft, SAP, Oracle, Salesforce, Netsuite, Taleo, or other SaaS and On-Premise ERP systems) and at least two years of formal education or training in a related field may be substituted for a Bachelor's Degree.

Preferred experience:

5+ years developing reporting solutions with ERP software
5+ years Human Resource, Payroll or Financial software application experience
5+ Years Business Intelligence reporting experience
5+ Years Data warehousing experience and/or Big Data
EDI, Web Services, XML, XSLT, Java experience
Workday, PeopleSoft, SAP, Oracle OBIEE, Salesforce, Netsuite, Taleo, or other SaaS and On-Premise ERP systems and reporting
The incumbent must have the ability and interest to learn new techniques, tools and methodologies
Background and experience in higher education and/or expertise for a large enterprise or university

KNOWLEDGE, SKILLS, AND ABILITIES: Successful candidates must possess the following knowledge, skills and abilities. It is recommended that applicants for this position address each of the following items in the letter of application:

Strong analysis and ability to creatively solve complex problems;
excellent verbal and written communication skills;
strong interpersonal skills and tact;
strong customer service and service management focus
ability to function in a team;
ability to understand the technical aspects of the information technology services provided by SCS;
ability to understand SCS resources and procedures;
ability and interest to learn new techniques, tools and methodologies.

RESPONSIBILITIES: The duties of this position will include, but not be limited to, the following areas of responsibility:

The major purpose of this position is to develop, support, and maintain various types of data reports, queries, and extracts for the Workday enterprise system environment. Responsibilities will include design and analysis, gathering functional requirements, maintaining documentation, and development skills using various types of analytics tools and Workday reporting features. Design timely and accurate dashboards, reports, presentations and visual aids used to educate, inform and influence the decisions of HR/Finance and business leaders within NSHE. Analyze existing production reporting and programming logic to provide more efficient operations or to identify difficulties. Revise logic and procedures involved, as necessary. Identify the data model and security requirements including role-based permissions for HR and Financial reporting solutions. Provide necessary statutory and legally required reports globally as mandated by government agencies, state agencies and /or work councils. Develop, test and evaluate reports, dashboard and big datasets. Effectively communicate with NSHE stakeholders throughout the development processes.

TO APPLY: The application process will be handled through the HR Search on-line search process. Application materials must include a current resume, detailed cover letter, and names, addresses, and telephone numbers of four professional references willing to be contacted. Applicants should fully describe qualifications and experience, since the initial review will serve to evaluate applicants based on documented, relevant qualifications and professional work experience. Materials should be addressed to Sherry Olson, Director of Human Resources, and are to be submitted via on-line application at https://nshe.nevada.edu/administration/human-resources. For assistance with NSHE's on-line applicant portal, contact Sherry Olson at (775) 784- 4901 or solson@nshe.nevada.edu


Application Deadline: Applications may be submitted until the position is filled; however, to ensure full consideration, applications should be submitted by August 15, 2021.
